5551 
5552 SDValue SITargetLowering::getSegmentAperture(unsigned AS, const SDLoc &DL,
5553  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5554  if (Subtarget->hasApertureRegs()) {
5555  const unsigned ApertureRegNo = (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS)
5556  ? AMDGPU::SRC_SHARED_BASE
5557  : AMDGPU::SRC_PRIVATE_BASE;
5558  // Note: this feature (register) is broken. When used as a 32-bit operand,
5559  // it returns a wrong value (all zeroes?). The real value is in the upper 32
5560  // bits.
5561  //
5562  // To work around the issue, directly emit a 64 bit mov from this register
5563  // then extract the high bits. Note that this shouldn't even result in a
5564  // shift being emitted and simply become a pair of registers (e.g.):
5565  // s_mov_b64 s[6:7], src_shared_base
5566  // v_mov_b32_e32 v1, s7
5567  //
5568  // FIXME: It would be more natural to emit a CopyFromReg here, but then copy
5569  // coalescing would kick in and it would think it's okay to use the "HI"
5570  // subregister directly (instead of extracting the HI 32 bits) which is an
5571  // artificial (unusable) register.
5572  // Register TableGen definitions would need an overhaul to get rid of the
5573  // artificial "HI" aperture registers and prevent this kind of issue from
5574  // happening.
5575  SDNode *Mov = DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B64, DL, MVT::i64,
5576  DAG.getRegister(ApertureRegNo, MVT::i64));
5577  return DAG.getNode(
5578  ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i32,
5579  DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i64,
5580  {SDValue(Mov, 0), DAG.getConstant(32, DL, MVT::i64)}));
5581  }
5582 
5583  // For code object version 5, private_base and shared_base are passed through
5584  // implicit kernargs.
5585  const Module *M = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getParent();
5586  if (AMDGPU::getCodeObjectVersion(*M) >= AMDGPU::AMDHSA_COV5) {
5587  ImplicitParameter Param =
5588  (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS) ? SHARED_BASE : PRIVATE_BASE;
5589  return loadImplicitKernelArgument(DAG, MVT::i32, DL, Align(4), Param);
5590  }
5591 
5592  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5593  SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
5594  Register UserSGPR = Info->getQueuePtrUserSGPR();
5595  if (UserSGPR == AMDGPU::NoRegister) {
5596  // We probably are in a function incorrectly marked with
5597  // amdgpu-no-queue-ptr. This is undefined.
5598  return DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32);
5599  }
5600 
5601  SDValue QueuePtr = CreateLiveInRegister(
5602  DAG, &AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass, UserSGPR, MVT::i64);
5603 
5604  // Offset into amd_queue_t for group_segment_aperture_base_hi /
5605  // private_segment_aperture_base_hi.
5606  uint32_t StructOffset = (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS) ? 0x40 : 0x44;
5607 
5608  SDValue Ptr =
5609  DAG.getObjectPtrOffset(DL, QueuePtr, TypeSize::Fixed(StructOffset));
5610 
5611  // TODO: Use custom target PseudoSourceValue.
5612  // TODO: We should use the value from the IR intrinsic call, but it might not
5613  // be available and how do we get it?
5614  MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo(AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS);
5615  return DAG.getLoad(MVT::i32, DL, QueuePtr.getValue(1), Ptr, PtrInfo,
5616  commonAlignment(Align(64), StructOffset),
5617  MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable |
5618  MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant);
5619 }
5620 
5621 /// Return true if the value is a known valid address, such that a null check is
5622 /// not necessary.
5623 static bool isKnownNonNull(SDValue Val, SelectionDAG &DAG,
5624  const AMDGPUTargetMachine &TM, unsigned AddrSpace) {
5625  if (isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Val) || isa<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Val) ||
5626  isa<BasicBlockSDNode>(Val))
5627  return true;
5628 
5629  if (auto *ConstVal = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Val))
5630  return ConstVal->getSExtValue() != TM.getNullPointerValue(AddrSpace);
5631 
5632  // TODO: Search through arithmetic, handle arguments and loads
5633  // marked nonnull.
5634  return false;
5635 }
5636 
5637 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerADDRSPACECAST(SDValue Op,
5638  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5639  SDLoc SL(Op);
5640  const AddrSpaceCastSDNode *ASC = cast<AddrSpaceCastSDNode>(Op);
5641 
5642  SDValue Src = ASC->getOperand(0);
5643  SDValue FlatNullPtr = DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i64);
5644  unsigned SrcAS = ASC->getSrcAddressSpace();
5645 
5646  const AMDGPUTargetMachine &TM =
5647  static_cast<const AMDGPUTargetMachine &>(getTargetMachine());
5648 
5649  // flat -> local/private
5650  if (SrcAS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) {
5651  unsigned DestAS = ASC->getDestAddressSpace();
5652 
5653  if (DestAS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS ||
5654  DestAS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) {
5655  SDValue Ptr = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MVT::i32, Src);
5656 
5657  if (isKnownNonNull(Src, DAG, TM, SrcAS))
5658  return Ptr;
5659 
5660  unsigned NullVal = TM.getNullPointerValue(DestAS);
5661  SDValue SegmentNullPtr = DAG.getConstant(NullVal, SL, MVT::i32);
5662  SDValue NonNull = DAG.getSetCC(SL, MVT::i1, Src, FlatNullPtr, ISD::SETNE);
5663 
5664  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, SL, MVT::i32, NonNull, Ptr,
5665  SegmentNullPtr);
5666  }
5667  }
5668 
5669  // local/private -> flat
5670  if (ASC->getDestAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) {
5671  if (SrcAS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS ||
5672  SrcAS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) {
5673 
5674  SDValue Aperture = getSegmentAperture(ASC->getSrcAddressSpace(), SL, DAG);
5675  SDValue CvtPtr =
5676  DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SL, MVT::v2i32, Src, Aperture);
5677  CvtPtr = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i64, CvtPtr);
5678 
5679  if (isKnownNonNull(Src, DAG, TM, SrcAS))
5680  return CvtPtr;
5681 
5682  unsigned NullVal = TM.getNullPointerValue(SrcAS);
5683  SDValue SegmentNullPtr = DAG.getConstant(NullVal, SL, MVT::i32);
5684 
5685  SDValue NonNull
5686  = DAG.getSetCC(SL, MVT::i1, Src, SegmentNullPtr, ISD::SETNE);
5687 
5688  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, SL, MVT::i64, NonNull, CvtPtr,
5689  FlatNullPtr);
5690  }
5691  }
5692 
5693  if (SrcAS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT &&
5694  Op.getValueType() == MVT::i64) {
5695  const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info =
5696  DAG.getMachineFunction().getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
5697  SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(Info->get32BitAddressHighBits(), SL, MVT::i32);
5698  SDValue Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SL, MVT::v2i32, Src, Hi);
5699  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i64, Vec);
5700  }
5701 
5702  if (ASC->getDestAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT &&
5703  Src.getValueType() == MVT::i64)
5704  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MVT::i32, Src);
5705 
5706  // global <-> flat are no-ops and never emitted.
5707 
5708  const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
5709  DiagnosticInfoUnsupported InvalidAddrSpaceCast(
5710  MF.getFunction(), "invalid addrspacecast", SL.getDebugLoc());
5711  DAG.getContext()->diagnose(InvalidAddrSpaceCast);
5712 
5713  return DAG.getUNDEF(ASC->getValueType(0));
5714 }
5715 
5716 // This lowers an INSERT_SUBVECTOR by extracting the individual elements from
5717 // the small vector and inserting them into the big vector. That is better than
5718 // the default expansion of doing it via a stack slot. Even though the use of
5719 // the stack slot would be optimized away afterwards, the stack slot itself
5720 // remains.
5721 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerINSERT_SUBVECTOR(SDValue Op,
5722  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5723  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5724  SDValue Ins = Op.getOperand(1);
5725  SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(2);
5726  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
5727  EVT InsVT = Ins.getValueType();
5728  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
5729  unsigned InsNumElts = InsVT.getVectorNumElements();
5730  unsigned IdxVal = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx)->getZExtValue();
5731  SDLoc SL(Op);
5732 
5733  for (unsigned I = 0; I != InsNumElts; ++I) {
5734  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT, Ins,
5735  DAG.getConstant(I, SL, MVT::i32));
5736  Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, VecVT, Vec, Elt,
5737  DAG.getConstant(IdxVal + I, SL, MVT::i32));
5738  }
5739  return Vec;
5740 }
5741 
5742 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op,
5743  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5744  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5745  SDValue InsVal = Op.getOperand(1);
5746  SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(2);
5747  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
5748  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
5749  unsigned VecSize = VecVT.getSizeInBits();
5750  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits();
5751  SDLoc SL(Op);
5752 
5753  // Specially handle the case of v4i16 with static indexing.
5754  unsigned NumElts = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
5755  auto KIdx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Idx);
5756  if (NumElts == 4 && EltSize == 16 && KIdx) {
5757  SDValue BCVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i32, Vec);
5758 
5759  SDValue LoHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, BCVec,
5760  DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32));
5761  SDValue HiHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, BCVec,
5762  DAG.getConstant(1, SL, MVT::i32));
5763 
5764  SDValue LoVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i16, LoHalf);
5765  SDValue HiVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i16, HiHalf);
5766 
5767  unsigned Idx = KIdx->getZExtValue();
5768  bool InsertLo = Idx < 2;
5769  SDValue InsHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::v2i16,
5770  InsertLo ? LoVec : HiVec,
5771  DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, InsVal),
5772  DAG.getConstant(InsertLo ? Idx : (Idx - 2), SL, MVT::i32));
5773 
5774  InsHalf = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i32, InsHalf);
5775 
5776  SDValue Concat = InsertLo ?
5777  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i32, SL, { InsHalf, HiHalf }) :
5778  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i32, SL, { LoHalf, InsHalf });
5779 
5780  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VecVT, Concat);
5781  }
5782 
5783  // Static indexing does not lower to stack access, and hence there is no need
5784  // for special custom lowering to avoid stack access.
5785  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Idx))
5786  return SDValue();
5787 
5788  // Avoid stack access for dynamic indexing by custom lowering to
5789  // v_bfi_b32 (v_bfm_b32 16, (shl idx, 16)), val, vec
5790 
5791  assert(VecSize <= 64 && "Expected target vector size to be <= 64 bits");
5792 
5793  MVT IntVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(VecSize);
5794 
5795  // Convert vector index to bit-index and get the required bit mask.
5796  assert(isPowerOf2_32(EltSize));
5797  const auto EltMask = maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(EltSize);
5798  SDValue ScaleFactor = DAG.getConstant(Log2_32(EltSize), SL, MVT::i32);
5799  SDValue ScaledIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, MVT::i32, Idx, ScaleFactor);
5800  SDValue BFM = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, IntVT,
5801  DAG.getConstant(EltMask, SL, IntVT), ScaledIdx);
5802 
5803  // 1. Create a congruent vector with the target value in each element.
5804  SDValue ExtVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, IntVT,
5805  DAG.getSplatBuildVector(VecVT, SL, InsVal));
5806 
5807  // 2. Mask off all other indicies except the required index within (1).
5808  SDValue LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SL, IntVT, BFM, ExtVal);
5809 
5810  // 3. Mask off the required index within the target vector.
5811  SDValue BCVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, IntVT, Vec);
5812  SDValue RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SL, IntVT,
5813  DAG.getNOT(SL, BFM, IntVT), BCVec);
5814 
5815  // 4. Get (2) and (3) ORed into the target vector.
5816  SDValue BFI = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, SL, IntVT, LHS, RHS);
5817 
5818  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VecVT, BFI);
5819 }
5820 
5821 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(SDValue Op,
5822  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5823  SDLoc SL(Op);
5824 
5825  EVT ResultVT = Op.getValueType();
5826  SDValue Vec = Op.getOperand(0);
5827  SDValue Idx = Op.getOperand(1);
5828  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
5829  unsigned VecSize = VecVT.getSizeInBits();
5830  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
5831 
5832  DAGCombinerInfo DCI(DAG, AfterLegalizeVectorOps, true, nullptr);
5833 
5834  // Make sure we do any optimizations that will make it easier to fold
5835  // source modifiers before obscuring it with bit operations.
5836 
5837  // XXX - Why doesn't this get called when vector_shuffle is expanded?
5838  if (SDValue Combined = performExtractVectorEltCombine(Op.getNode(), DCI))
5839  return Combined;
5840 
5841  if (VecSize == 128 || VecSize == 256) {
5842  SDValue Lo, Hi;
5843  EVT LoVT, HiVT;
5844  std::tie(LoVT, HiVT) = DAG.GetSplitDestVTs(VecVT);
5845 
5846  if (VecSize == 128) {
5847  SDValue V2 = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v2i64, Vec);
5848  Lo = DAG.getBitcast(LoVT,
5849  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i64, V2,
5850  DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32)));
5851  Hi = DAG.getBitcast(HiVT,
5852  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i64, V2,
5853  DAG.getConstant(1, SL, MVT::i32)));
5854  } else {
5855  assert(VecSize == 256);
5856 
5857  SDValue V2 = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v4i64, Vec);
5858  SDValue Parts[4];
5859  for (unsigned P = 0; P < 4; ++P) {
5860  Parts[P] = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i64, V2,
5861  DAG.getConstant(P, SL, MVT::i32));
5862  }
5863 
5864  Lo = DAG.getBitcast(LoVT, DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SL, MVT::v2i64,
5865  Parts[0], Parts[1]));
5866  Hi = DAG.getBitcast(HiVT, DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SL, MVT::v2i64,
5867  Parts[2], Parts[3]));
5868  }
5869 
5870  EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
5871  unsigned NElem = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
5872  assert(isPowerOf2_32(NElem));
5873  SDValue IdxMask = DAG.getConstant(NElem / 2 - 1, SL, IdxVT);
5874  SDValue NewIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, SL, IdxVT, Idx, IdxMask);
5875  SDValue Half = DAG.getSelectCC(SL, Idx, IdxMask, Hi, Lo, ISD::SETUGT);
5876  return DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT, Half, NewIdx);
5877  }
5878 
5879  assert(VecSize <= 64);
5880 
5881  MVT IntVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(VecSize);
5882 
5883  // If Vec is just a SCALAR_TO_VECTOR, then use the scalar integer directly.
5884  SDValue VecBC = peekThroughBitcasts(Vec);
5885  if (VecBC.getOpcode() == ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR) {
5886  SDValue Src = VecBC.getOperand(0);
5887  Src = DAG.getBitcast(Src.getValueType().changeTypeToInteger(), Src);
5888  Vec = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Src, SL, IntVT);
5889  }
5890 
5891  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits();
5892  assert(isPowerOf2_32(EltSize));
5893 
5894  SDValue ScaleFactor = DAG.getConstant(Log2_32(EltSize), SL, MVT::i32);
5895 
5896  // Convert vector index to bit-index (* EltSize)
5897  SDValue ScaledIdx = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, MVT::i32, Idx, ScaleFactor);
5898 
5899  SDValue BC = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, IntVT, Vec);
5900  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, SL, IntVT, BC, ScaledIdx);
5901 
5902  if (ResultVT == MVT::f16) {
5903  SDValue Result = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MVT::i16, Elt);
5904  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, ResultVT, Result);
5905  }
5906 
5907  return DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Elt, SL, ResultVT);
5908 }
5909 
5910 static bool elementPairIsContiguous(ArrayRef<int> Mask, int Elt) {
5911  assert(Elt % 2 == 0);
5912  return Mask[Elt + 1] == Mask[Elt] + 1 && (Mask[Elt] % 2 == 0);
5913 }
5914 
5915 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDValue Op,
5916  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5917  SDLoc SL(Op);
5918  EVT ResultVT = Op.getValueType();
5919  ShuffleVectorSDNode *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op);
5920 
5921  EVT PackVT = ResultVT.isInteger() ? MVT::v2i16 : MVT::v2f16;
5922  EVT EltVT = PackVT.getVectorElementType();
5923  int SrcNumElts = Op.getOperand(0).getValueType().getVectorNumElements();
5924 
5925  // vector_shuffle <0,1,6,7> lhs, rhs
5926  // -> concat_vectors (extract_subvector lhs, 0), (extract_subvector rhs, 2)
5927  //
5928  // vector_shuffle <6,7,2,3> lhs, rhs
5929  // -> concat_vectors (extract_subvector rhs, 2), (extract_subvector lhs, 2)
5930  //
5931  // vector_shuffle <6,7,0,1> lhs, rhs
5932  // -> concat_vectors (extract_subvector rhs, 2), (extract_subvector lhs, 0)
5933 
5934  // Avoid scalarizing when both halves are reading from consecutive elements.
5935  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Pieces;
5936  for (int I = 0, N = ResultVT.getVectorNumElements(); I != N; I += 2) {
5937  if (elementPairIsContiguous(SVN->getMask(), I)) {
5938  const int Idx = SVN->getMaskElt(I);
5939  int VecIdx = Idx < SrcNumElts ? 0 : 1;
5940  int EltIdx = Idx < SrcNumElts ? Idx : Idx - SrcNumElts;
5941  SDValue SubVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, SL,
5942  PackVT, SVN->getOperand(VecIdx),
5943  DAG.getConstant(EltIdx, SL, MVT::i32));
5944  Pieces.push_back(SubVec);
5945  } else {
5946  const int Idx0 = SVN->getMaskElt(I);
5947  const int Idx1 = SVN->getMaskElt(I + 1);
5948  int VecIdx0 = Idx0 < SrcNumElts ? 0 : 1;
5949  int VecIdx1 = Idx1 < SrcNumElts ? 0 : 1;
5950  int EltIdx0 = Idx0 < SrcNumElts ? Idx0 : Idx0 - SrcNumElts;
5951  int EltIdx1 = Idx1 < SrcNumElts ? Idx1 : Idx1 - SrcNumElts;
5952 
5953  SDValue Vec0 = SVN->getOperand(VecIdx0);
5954  SDValue Elt0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT,
5955  Vec0, DAG.getConstant(EltIdx0, SL, MVT::i32));
5956 
5957  SDValue Vec1 = SVN->getOperand(VecIdx1);
5958  SDValue Elt1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT,
5959  Vec1, DAG.getConstant(EltIdx1, SL, MVT::i32));
5960  Pieces.push_back(DAG.getBuildVector(PackVT, SL, { Elt0, Elt1 }));
5961  }
5962  }
5963 
5964  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, SL, ResultVT, Pieces);
5965 }
5966 
5967 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerSCALAR_TO_VECTOR(SDValue Op,
5968  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5969  SDValue SVal = Op.getOperand(0);
5970  EVT ResultVT = Op.getValueType();
5971  EVT SValVT = SVal.getValueType();
5972  SDValue UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(SValVT);
5973  SDLoc SL(Op);
5974 
5975  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> VElts;
5976  VElts.push_back(SVal);
5977  for (int I = 1, E = ResultVT.getVectorNumElements(); I < E; ++I)
5978  VElts.push_back(UndefVal);
5979 
5980  return DAG.getBuildVector(ResultVT, SL, VElts);
5981 }
5982 
5983 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerBUILD_VECTOR(SDValue Op,
5984  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
5985  SDLoc SL(Op);
5986  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
5987 
5988  if (VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v4f16 ||
5989  VT == MVT::v8i16 || VT == MVT::v8f16) {
5990  EVT HalfVT = MVT::getVectorVT(VT.getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT(),
5991  VT.getVectorNumElements() / 2);
5992  MVT HalfIntVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(HalfVT.getSizeInBits());
5993 
5994  // Turn into pair of packed build_vectors.
5995  // TODO: Special case for constants that can be materialized with s_mov_b64.
5996  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> LoOps, HiOps;
5997  for (unsigned I = 0, E = VT.getVectorNumElements() / 2; I != E; ++I) {
5998  LoOps.push_back(Op.getOperand(I));
5999  HiOps.push_back(Op.getOperand(I + E));
6000  }
6001  SDValue Lo = DAG.getBuildVector(HalfVT, SL, LoOps);
6002  SDValue Hi = DAG.getBuildVector(HalfVT, SL, HiOps);
6003 
6004  SDValue CastLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, HalfIntVT, Lo);
6005  SDValue CastHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, HalfIntVT, Hi);
6006 
6007  SDValue Blend = DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::getVectorVT(HalfIntVT, 2), SL,
6008  { CastLo, CastHi });
6009  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Blend);
6010  }
6011 
6012  if (VT == MVT::v16i16 || VT == MVT::v16f16) {
6013  EVT QuarterVT = MVT::getVectorVT(VT.getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT(),
6014  VT.getVectorNumElements() / 4);
6015  MVT QuarterIntVT = MVT::getIntegerVT(QuarterVT.getSizeInBits());
6016 
6017  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Parts[4];
6018  for (unsigned I = 0, E = VT.getVectorNumElements() / 4; I != E; ++I) {
6019  for (unsigned P = 0; P < 4; ++P)
6020  Parts[P].push_back(Op.getOperand(I + P * E));
6021  }
6022  SDValue Casts[4];
6023  for (unsigned P = 0; P < 4; ++P) {
6024  SDValue Vec = DAG.getBuildVector(QuarterVT, SL, Parts[P]);
6025  Casts[P] = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, QuarterIntVT, Vec);
6026  }
6027 
6028  SDValue Blend =
6029  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::getVectorVT(QuarterIntVT, 4), SL, Casts);
6030  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Blend);
6031  }
6032 
6033  assert(VT == MVT::v2f16 || VT == MVT::v2i16);
6034  assert(!Subtarget->hasVOP3PInsts() && "this should be legal");
6035 
6036  SDValue Lo = Op.getOperand(0);
6037  SDValue Hi = Op.getOperand(1);
6038 
6039  // Avoid adding defined bits with the zero_extend.
6040  if (Hi.isUndef()) {
6041  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, Lo);
6042  SDValue ExtLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i32, Lo);
6043  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, ExtLo);
6044  }
6045 
6046  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, Hi);
6047  Hi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i32, Hi);
6048 
6049  SDValue ShlHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, MVT::i32, Hi,
6050  DAG.getConstant(16, SL, MVT::i32));
6051  if (Lo.isUndef())
6052  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, ShlHi);
6053 
6054  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, Lo);
6055  Lo = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i32, Lo);
6056 
6057  SDValue Or = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, SL, MVT::i32, Lo, ShlHi);
6058  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Or);
6059 }
6060 
6061 bool
6062 SITargetLowering::isOffsetFoldingLegal(const GlobalAddressSDNode *GA) const {
6063  // We can fold offsets for anything that doesn't require a GOT relocation.
6064  return (GA->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS ||
6065  GA->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS ||
6066  GA->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT) &&
6067  !shouldEmitGOTReloc(GA->getGlobal());
6068 }
6069 
6070 static SDValue
6071 buildPCRelGlobalAddress(SelectionDAG &DAG, const GlobalValue *GV,
6072  const SDLoc &DL, int64_t Offset, EVT PtrVT,
6073  unsigned GAFlags = SIInstrInfo::MO_NONE) {
6074  assert(isInt<32>(Offset + 4) && "32-bit offset is expected!");
6075  // In order to support pc-relative addressing, the PC_ADD_REL_OFFSET SDNode is
6076  // lowered to the following code sequence:
6077  //
6078  // For constant address space:
6079  // s_getpc_b64 s[0:1]
6080  // s_add_u32 s0, s0, $symbol
6081  // s_addc_u32 s1, s1, 0
6082  //
6083  // s_getpc_b64 returns the address of the s_add_u32 instruction and then
6084  // a fixup or relocation is emitted to replace $symbol with a literal
6085  // constant, which is a pc-relative offset from the encoding of the $symbol
6086  // operand to the global variable.
6087  //
6088  // For global address space:
6089  // s_getpc_b64 s[0:1]
6090  // s_add_u32 s0, s0, $symbol@{gotpc}rel32@lo
6091  // s_addc_u32 s1, s1, $symbol@{gotpc}rel32@hi
6092  //
6093  // s_getpc_b64 returns the address of the s_add_u32 instruction and then
6094  // fixups or relocations are emitted to replace $symbol@*@lo and
6095  // $symbol@*@hi with lower 32 bits and higher 32 bits of a literal constant,
6096  // which is a 64-bit pc-relative offset from the encoding of the $symbol
6097  // operand to the global variable.
6098  //
6099  // What we want here is an offset from the value returned by s_getpc
6100  // (which is the address of the s_add_u32 instruction) to the global
6101  // variable, but since the encoding of $symbol starts 4 bytes after the start
6102  // of the s_add_u32 instruction, we end up with an offset that is 4 bytes too
6103  // small. This requires us to add 4 to the global variable offset in order to
6104  // compute the correct address. Similarly for the s_addc_u32 instruction, the
6105  // encoding of $symbol starts 12 bytes after the start of the s_add_u32
6106  // instruction.
6107  SDValue PtrLo =
6108  DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, MVT::i32, Offset + 4, GAFlags);
6109  SDValue PtrHi;
6110  if (GAFlags == SIInstrInfo::MO_NONE) {
6111  PtrHi = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
6112  } else {
6113  PtrHi =
6114  DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, MVT::i32, Offset + 12, GAFlags + 1);
6115  }
6116  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PC_ADD_REL_OFFSET, DL, PtrVT, PtrLo, PtrHi);
6117 }
6118 
6119 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerGlobalAddress(AMDGPUMachineFunction *MFI,
6120  SDValue Op,
6121  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6122  GlobalAddressSDNode *GSD = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
6123  SDLoc DL(GSD);
6124  EVT PtrVT = Op.getValueType();
6125 
6126  const GlobalValue *GV = GSD->getGlobal();
6127  if ((GSD->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS &&
6128  shouldUseLDSConstAddress(GV)) ||
6129  GSD->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS ||
6130  GSD->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) {
6131  if (GSD->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS &&
6132  GV->hasExternalLinkage()) {
6133  Type *Ty = GV->getValueType();
6134  // HIP uses an unsized array `extern __shared__ T s[]` or similar
6135  // zero-sized type in other languages to declare the dynamic shared
6136  // memory which size is not known at the compile time. They will be
6137  // allocated by the runtime and placed directly after the static
6138  // allocated ones. They all share the same offset.
6139  if (DAG.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSize(Ty).isZero()) {
6140  assert(PtrVT == MVT::i32 && "32-bit pointer is expected.");
6141  // Adjust alignment for that dynamic shared memory array.
6142  MFI->setDynLDSAlign(DAG.getDataLayout(), *cast<GlobalVariable>(GV));
6143  return SDValue(
6144  DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::GET_GROUPSTATICSIZE, DL, PtrVT), 0);
6145  }
6146  }
6147  return AMDGPUTargetLowering::LowerGlobalAddress(MFI, Op, DAG);
6148  }
6149 
6150  if (GSD->getAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS) {
6151  SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, MVT::i32, GSD->getOffset(),
6152  SIInstrInfo::MO_ABS32_LO);
6153  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::LDS, DL, MVT::i32, GA);
6154  }
6155 
6156  if (shouldEmitFixup(GV))
6157  return buildPCRelGlobalAddress(DAG, GV, DL, GSD->getOffset(), PtrVT);
6158  else if (shouldEmitPCReloc(GV))
6159  return buildPCRelGlobalAddress(DAG, GV, DL, GSD->getOffset(), PtrVT,
6160  SIInstrInfo::MO_REL32);
6161 
6162  SDValue GOTAddr = buildPCRelGlobalAddress(DAG, GV, DL, 0, PtrVT,
6163  SIInstrInfo::MO_GOTPCREL32);
6164 
6165  Type *Ty = PtrVT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
6166  PointerType *PtrTy = PointerType::get(Ty, AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS);
6167  const DataLayout &DataLayout = DAG.getDataLayout();
6168  Align Alignment = DataLayout.getABITypeAlign(PtrTy);
6169  MachinePointerInfo PtrInfo
6170  = MachinePointerInfo::getGOT(DAG.getMachineFunction());
6171 
6172  return DAG.getLoad(PtrVT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(), GOTAddr, PtrInfo, Alignment,
6173  MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable |
6174  MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant);
6175 }
6176 
6177 SDValue SITargetLowering::copyToM0(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
6178  const SDLoc &DL, SDValue V) const {
6179  // We can't use S_MOV_B32 directly, because there is no way to specify m0 as
6180  // the destination register.
6181  //
6182  // We can't use CopyToReg, because MachineCSE won't combine COPY instructions,
6183  // so we will end up with redundant moves to m0.
6184  //
6185  // We use a pseudo to ensure we emit s_mov_b32 with m0 as the direct result.
6186 
6187  // A Null SDValue creates a glue result.
6188  SDNode *M0 = DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::SI_INIT_M0, DL, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue,
6189  V, Chain);
6190  return SDValue(M0, 0);
6191 }
6192 
6193 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerImplicitZextParam(SelectionDAG &DAG,
6194  SDValue Op,
6195  MVT VT,
6196  unsigned Offset) const {
6197  SDLoc SL(Op);
6198  SDValue Param = lowerKernargMemParameter(
6199  DAG, MVT::i32, MVT::i32, SL, DAG.getEntryNode(), Offset, Align(4), false);
6200  // The local size values will have the hi 16-bits as zero.
6201  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, SL, MVT::i32, Param,
6202  DAG.getValueType(VT));
6203 }

6205 static SDValue emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
6206  EVT VT) {
6207  DiagnosticInfoUnsupported BadIntrin(DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction(),
6208  "non-hsa intrinsic with hsa target",
6209  DL.getDebugLoc());
6210  DAG.getContext()->diagnose(BadIntrin);
6211  return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
6212 }
6213 
6214 static SDValue emitRemovedIntrinsicError(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
6215  EVT VT) {
6216  DiagnosticInfoUnsupported BadIntrin(DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction(),
6217  "intrinsic not supported on subtarget",
6218  DL.getDebugLoc());
6219  DAG.getContext()->diagnose(BadIntrin);
6220  return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
6221 }
6222 
6223 static SDValue getBuildDwordsVector(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDLoc DL,
6224  ArrayRef<SDValue> Elts) {
6225  assert(!Elts.empty());
6226  MVT Type;
6227  unsigned NumElts = Elts.size();
6228 
6229  if (NumElts <= 12) {
6230  Type = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::f32, NumElts);
6231  } else {
6232  assert(Elts.size() <= 16);
6233  Type = MVT::v16f32;
6234  NumElts = 16;
6235  }
6236 
6237  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> VecElts(NumElts);
6238  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Elts.size(); ++i) {
6239  SDValue Elt = Elts[i];
6240  if (Elt.getValueType() != MVT::f32)
6241  Elt = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::f32, Elt);
6242  VecElts[i] = Elt;
6243  }
6244  for (unsigned i = Elts.size(); i < NumElts; ++i)
6245  VecElts[i] = DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::f32);
6246 
6247  if (NumElts == 1)
6248  return VecElts[0];
6249  return DAG.getBuildVector(Type, DL, VecElts);
6250 }
6251 
6252 static SDValue padEltsToUndef(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL, EVT CastVT,
6253  SDValue Src, int ExtraElts) {
6254  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
6255 
6256  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Elts;
6257 
6258  if (SrcVT.isVector())
6259  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(Src, Elts);
6260  else
6261  Elts.push_back(Src);
6262 
6263  SDValue Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(SrcVT.getScalarType());
6264  while (ExtraElts--)
6265  Elts.push_back(Undef);
6266 
6267  return DAG.getBuildVector(CastVT, DL, Elts);
6268 }
6269 
6270 // Re-construct the required return value for a image load intrinsic.
6271 // This is more complicated due to the optional use TexFailCtrl which means the required
6272 // return type is an aggregate
6273 static SDValue constructRetValue(SelectionDAG &DAG,
6274  MachineSDNode *Result,
6275  ArrayRef<EVT> ResultTypes,
6276  bool IsTexFail, bool Unpacked, bool IsD16,
6277  int DMaskPop, int NumVDataDwords,
6278  const SDLoc &DL) {
6279  // Determine the required return type. This is the same regardless of IsTexFail flag
6280  EVT ReqRetVT = ResultTypes[0];
6281  int ReqRetNumElts = ReqRetVT.isVector() ? ReqRetVT.getVectorNumElements() : 1;
6282  int NumDataDwords = (!IsD16 || (IsD16 && Unpacked)) ?
6283  ReqRetNumElts : (ReqRetNumElts + 1) / 2;
6284 
6285  int MaskPopDwords = (!IsD16 || (IsD16 && Unpacked)) ?
6286  DMaskPop : (DMaskPop + 1) / 2;
6287 
6288  MVT DataDwordVT = NumDataDwords == 1 ?
6289  MVT::i32 : MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, NumDataDwords);
6290 
6291  MVT MaskPopVT = MaskPopDwords == 1 ?
6292  MVT::i32 : MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, MaskPopDwords);
6293 
6294  SDValue Data(Result, 0);
6295  SDValue TexFail;
6296 
6297  if (DMaskPop > 0 && Data.getValueType() != MaskPopVT) {
6298  SDValue ZeroIdx = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
6299  if (MaskPopVT.isVector()) {
6300  Data = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, MaskPopVT,
6301  SDValue(Result, 0), ZeroIdx);
6302  } else {
6303  Data = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MaskPopVT,
6304  SDValue(Result, 0), ZeroIdx);
6305  }
6306  }
6307 
6308  if (DataDwordVT.isVector())
6309  Data = padEltsToUndef(DAG, DL, DataDwordVT, Data,
6310  NumDataDwords - MaskPopDwords);
6311 
6312  if (IsD16)
6313  Data = adjustLoadValueTypeImpl(Data, ReqRetVT, DL, DAG, Unpacked);
6314 
6315  EVT LegalReqRetVT = ReqRetVT;
6316  if (!ReqRetVT.isVector()) {
6317  if (!Data.getValueType().isInteger())
6318  Data = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL,
6319  Data.getValueType().changeTypeToInteger(), Data);
6320  Data = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, ReqRetVT.changeTypeToInteger(), Data);
6321  } else {
6322  // We need to widen the return vector to a legal type
6323  if ((ReqRetVT.getVectorNumElements() % 2) == 1 &&
6324  ReqRetVT.getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits() == 16) {
6325  LegalReqRetVT =
6326  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), ReqRetVT.getVectorElementType(),
6327  ReqRetVT.getVectorNumElements() + 1);
6328  }
6329  }
6330  Data = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LegalReqRetVT, Data);
6331 
6332  if (IsTexFail) {
6333  TexFail =
6334  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, SDValue(Result, 0),
6335  DAG.getConstant(MaskPopDwords, DL, MVT::i32));
6336 
6337  return DAG.getMergeValues({Data, TexFail, SDValue(Result, 1)}, DL);
6338  }
6339 
6340  if (Result->getNumValues() == 1)
6341  return Data;
6342 
6343  return DAG.getMergeValues({Data, SDValue(Result, 1)}, DL);
6344 }
6345 
6346 static bool parseTexFail(SDValue TexFailCtrl, SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue *TFE,
6347  SDValue *LWE, bool &IsTexFail) {
6348  auto TexFailCtrlConst = cast<ConstantSDNode>(TexFailCtrl.getNode());
6349 
6350  uint64_t Value = TexFailCtrlConst->getZExtValue();
6351  if (Value) {
6352  IsTexFail = true;
6353  }
6354 
6355  SDLoc DL(TexFailCtrlConst);
6356  *TFE = DAG.getTargetConstant((Value & 0x1) ? 1 : 0, DL, MVT::i32);
6357  Value &= ~(uint64_t)0x1;
6358  *LWE = DAG.getTargetConstant((Value & 0x2) ? 1 : 0, DL, MVT::i32);
6359  Value &= ~(uint64_t)0x2;
6360 
6361  return Value == 0;
6362 }
6363 
6364 static void packImage16bitOpsToDwords(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Op,
6365  MVT PackVectorVT,
6366  SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &PackedAddrs,
6367  unsigned DimIdx, unsigned EndIdx,
6368  unsigned NumGradients) {
6369  SDLoc DL(Op);
6370  for (unsigned I = DimIdx; I < EndIdx; I++) {
6371  SDValue Addr = Op.getOperand(I);
6372 
6373  // Gradients are packed with undef for each coordinate.
6374  // In <hi 16 bit>,<lo 16 bit> notation, the registers look like this:
6375  // 1D: undef,dx/dh; undef,dx/dv
6376  // 2D: dy/dh,dx/dh; dy/dv,dx/dv
6377  // 3D: dy/dh,dx/dh; undef,dz/dh; dy/dv,dx/dv; undef,dz/dv
6378  if (((I + 1) >= EndIdx) ||
6379  ((NumGradients / 2) % 2 == 1 && (I == DimIdx + (NumGradients / 2) - 1 ||
6380  I == DimIdx + NumGradients - 1))) {
6381  if (Addr.getValueType() != MVT::i16)
6382  Addr = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i16, Addr);
6383  Addr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, Addr);
6384  } else {
6385  Addr = DAG.getBuildVector(PackVectorVT, DL, {Addr, Op.getOperand(I + 1)});
6386  I++;
6387  }
6388  Addr = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::f32, Addr);
6389  PackedAddrs.push_back(Addr);
6390  }
6391 }
6392 
6393 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerImage(SDValue Op,
6394  const AMDGPU::ImageDimIntrinsicInfo *Intr,
6395  SelectionDAG &DAG, bool WithChain) const {
6396  SDLoc DL(Op);
6397  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6398  const GCNSubtarget* ST = &MF.getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
6399  const AMDGPU::MIMGBaseOpcodeInfo *BaseOpcode =
6400  AMDGPU::getMIMGBaseOpcodeInfo(Intr->BaseOpcode);
6401  const AMDGPU::MIMGDimInfo *DimInfo = AMDGPU::getMIMGDimInfo(Intr->Dim);
6402  unsigned IntrOpcode = Intr->BaseOpcode;
6403  bool IsGFX10Plus = AMDGPU::isGFX10Plus(*Subtarget);
6404  bool IsGFX11Plus = AMDGPU::isGFX11Plus(*Subtarget);
6405 
6406  SmallVector<EVT, 3> ResultTypes(Op->values());
6407  SmallVector<EVT, 3> OrigResultTypes(Op->values());
6408  bool IsD16 = false;
6409  bool IsG16 = false;
6410  bool IsA16 = false;
6411  SDValue VData;
6412  int NumVDataDwords;
6413  bool AdjustRetType = false;
6414 
6415  // Offset of intrinsic arguments
6416  const unsigned ArgOffset = WithChain ? 2 : 1;
6417 
6418  unsigned DMask;
6419  unsigned DMaskLanes = 0;
6420 
6421  if (BaseOpcode->Atomic) {
6422  VData = Op.getOperand(2);
6423 
6424  bool Is64Bit = VData.getValueType() == MVT::i64;
6425  if (BaseOpcode->AtomicX2) {
6426  SDValue VData2 = Op.getOperand(3);
6427  VData = DAG.getBuildVector(Is64Bit ? MVT::v2i64 : MVT::v2i32, DL,
6428  {VData, VData2});
6429  if (Is64Bit)
6430  VData = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v4i32, VData);
6431 
6432  ResultTypes[0] = Is64Bit ? MVT::v2i64 : MVT::v2i32;
6433  DMask = Is64Bit ? 0xf : 0x3;
6434  NumVDataDwords = Is64Bit ? 4 : 2;
6435  } else {
6436  DMask = Is64Bit ? 0x3 : 0x1;
6437  NumVDataDwords = Is64Bit ? 2 : 1;
6438  }
6439  } else {
6440  auto *DMaskConst =
6441  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->DMaskIndex));
6442  DMask = DMaskConst->getZExtValue();
6443  DMaskLanes = BaseOpcode->Gather4 ? 4 : llvm::popcount(DMask);
6444 
6445  if (BaseOpcode->Store) {
6446  VData = Op.getOperand(2);
6447 
6448  MVT StoreVT = VData.getSimpleValueType();
6449  if (StoreVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16) {
6450  if (!Subtarget->hasD16Images() || !BaseOpcode->HasD16)
6451  return Op; // D16 is unsupported for this instruction
6452 
6453  IsD16 = true;
6454  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG, true);
6455  }
6456 
6457  NumVDataDwords = (VData.getValueType().getSizeInBits() + 31) / 32;
6458  } else {
6459  // Work out the num dwords based on the dmask popcount and underlying type
6460  // and whether packing is supported.
6461  MVT LoadVT = ResultTypes[0].getSimpleVT();
6462  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16) {
6463  if (!Subtarget->hasD16Images() || !BaseOpcode->HasD16)
6464  return Op; // D16 is unsupported for this instruction
6465 
6466  IsD16 = true;
6467  }
6468 
6469  // Confirm that the return type is large enough for the dmask specified
6470  if ((LoadVT.isVector() && LoadVT.getVectorNumElements() < DMaskLanes) ||
6471  (!LoadVT.isVector() && DMaskLanes > 1))
6472  return Op;
6473 
6474  // The sq block of gfx8 and gfx9 do not estimate register use correctly
6475  // for d16 image_gather4, image_gather4_l, and image_gather4_lz
6476  // instructions.
6477  if (IsD16 && !Subtarget->hasUnpackedD16VMem() &&
6478  !(BaseOpcode->Gather4 && Subtarget->hasImageGather4D16Bug()))
6479  NumVDataDwords = (DMaskLanes + 1) / 2;
6480  else
6481  NumVDataDwords = DMaskLanes;
6482 
6483  AdjustRetType = true;
6484  }
6485  }
6486 
6487  unsigned VAddrEnd = ArgOffset + Intr->VAddrEnd;
6488  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> VAddrs;
6489 
6490  // Check for 16 bit addresses or derivatives and pack if true.
6491  MVT VAddrVT =
6492  Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->GradientStart).getSimpleValueType();
6493  MVT VAddrScalarVT = VAddrVT.getScalarType();
6494  MVT GradPackVectorVT = VAddrScalarVT == MVT::f16 ? MVT::v2f16 : MVT::v2i16;
6495  IsG16 = VAddrScalarVT == MVT::f16 || VAddrScalarVT == MVT::i16;
6496 
6497  VAddrVT = Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart).getSimpleValueType();
6498  VAddrScalarVT = VAddrVT.getScalarType();
6499  MVT AddrPackVectorVT = VAddrScalarVT == MVT::f16 ? MVT::v2f16 : MVT::v2i16;
6500  IsA16 = VAddrScalarVT == MVT::f16 || VAddrScalarVT == MVT::i16;
6501 
6502  // Push back extra arguments.
6503  for (unsigned I = Intr->VAddrStart; I < Intr->GradientStart; I++) {
6504  if (IsA16 && (Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + I).getValueType() == MVT::f16)) {
6505  assert(I == Intr->BiasIndex && "Got unexpected 16-bit extra argument");
6506  // Special handling of bias when A16 is on. Bias is of type half but
6507  // occupies full 32-bit.
6508  SDValue Bias = DAG.getBuildVector(
6509  MVT::v2f16, DL,
6510  {Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + I), DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::f16)});
6511  VAddrs.push_back(Bias);
6512  } else {
6513  assert((!IsA16 || Intr->NumBiasArgs == 0 || I != Intr->BiasIndex) &&
6514  "Bias needs to be converted to 16 bit in A16 mode");
6515  VAddrs.push_back(Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + I));
6516  }
6517  }
6518 
6519  if (BaseOpcode->Gradients && !ST->hasG16() && (IsA16 != IsG16)) {
6520  // 16 bit gradients are supported, but are tied to the A16 control
6521  // so both gradients and addresses must be 16 bit
6522  LLVM_DEBUG(
6523  dbgs() << "Failed to lower image intrinsic: 16 bit addresses "
6524  "require 16 bit args for both gradients and addresses");
6525  return Op;
6526  }
6527 
6528  if (IsA16) {
6529  if (!ST->hasA16()) {
6530  LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Failed to lower image intrinsic: Target does not "
6531  "support 16 bit addresses\n");
6532  return Op;
6533  }
6534  }
6535 
6536  // We've dealt with incorrect input so we know that if IsA16, IsG16
6537  // are set then we have to compress/pack operands (either address,
6538  // gradient or both)
6539  // In the case where a16 and gradients are tied (no G16 support) then we
6540  // have already verified that both IsA16 and IsG16 are true
6541  if (BaseOpcode->Gradients && IsG16 && ST->hasG16()) {
6542  // Activate g16
6543  const AMDGPU::MIMGG16MappingInfo *G16MappingInfo =
6544  AMDGPU::getMIMGG16MappingInfo(Intr->BaseOpcode);
6545  IntrOpcode = G16MappingInfo->G16; // set new opcode to variant with _g16
6546  }
6547 
6548  // Add gradients (packed or unpacked)
6549  if (IsG16) {
6550  // Pack the gradients
6551  // const int PackEndIdx = IsA16 ? VAddrEnd : (ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart);
6552  packImage16bitOpsToDwords(DAG, Op, GradPackVectorVT, VAddrs,
6553  ArgOffset + Intr->GradientStart,
6554  ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart, Intr->NumGradients);
6555  } else {
6556  for (unsigned I = ArgOffset + Intr->GradientStart;
6557  I < ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart; I++)
6558  VAddrs.push_back(Op.getOperand(I));
6559  }
6560 
6561  // Add addresses (packed or unpacked)
6562  if (IsA16) {
6563  packImage16bitOpsToDwords(DAG, Op, AddrPackVectorVT, VAddrs,
6564  ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart, VAddrEnd,
6565  0 /* No gradients */);
6566  } else {
6567  // Add uncompressed address
6568  for (unsigned I = ArgOffset + Intr->CoordStart; I < VAddrEnd; I++)
6569  VAddrs.push_back(Op.getOperand(I));
6570  }
6571 
6572  // If the register allocator cannot place the address registers contiguously
6573  // without introducing moves, then using the non-sequential address encoding
6574  // is always preferable, since it saves VALU instructions and is usually a
6575  // wash in terms of code size or even better.
6576  //
6577  // However, we currently have no way of hinting to the register allocator that
6578  // MIMG addresses should be placed contiguously when it is possible to do so,
6579  // so force non-NSA for the common 2-address case as a heuristic.
6580  //
6581  // SIShrinkInstructions will convert NSA encodings to non-NSA after register
6582  // allocation when possible.
6583  //
6584  // TODO: we can actually allow partial NSA where the final register is a
6585  // contiguous set of the remaining addresses.
6586  // This could help where there are more addresses than supported.
6587  bool UseNSA = ST->hasFeature(AMDGPU::FeatureNSAEncoding) &&
6588  VAddrs.size() >= (unsigned)ST->getNSAThreshold(MF) &&
6589  VAddrs.size() <= (unsigned)ST->getNSAMaxSize();
6590  SDValue VAddr;
6591  if (!UseNSA)
6592  VAddr = getBuildDwordsVector(DAG, DL, VAddrs);
6593 
6594  SDValue True = DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1);
6595  SDValue False = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1);
6596  SDValue Unorm;
6597  if (!BaseOpcode->Sampler) {
6598  Unorm = True;
6599  } else {
6600  auto UnormConst =
6601  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->UnormIndex));
6602 
6603  Unorm = UnormConst->getZExtValue() ? True : False;
6604  }
6605 
6606  SDValue TFE;
6607  SDValue LWE;
6608  SDValue TexFail = Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->TexFailCtrlIndex);
6609  bool IsTexFail = false;
6610  if (!parseTexFail(TexFail, DAG, &TFE, &LWE, IsTexFail))
6611  return Op;
6612 
6613  if (IsTexFail) {
6614  if (!DMaskLanes) {
6615  // Expecting to get an error flag since TFC is on - and dmask is 0
6616  // Force dmask to be at least 1 otherwise the instruction will fail
6617  DMask = 0x1;
6618  DMaskLanes = 1;
6619  NumVDataDwords = 1;
6620  }
6621  NumVDataDwords += 1;
6622  AdjustRetType = true;
6623  }
6624 
6625  // Has something earlier tagged that the return type needs adjusting
6626  // This happens if the instruction is a load or has set TexFailCtrl flags
6627  if (AdjustRetType) {
6628  // NumVDataDwords reflects the true number of dwords required in the return type
6629  if (DMaskLanes == 0 && !BaseOpcode->Store) {
6630  // This is a no-op load. This can be eliminated
6631  SDValue Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(Op.getValueType());
6632  if (isa<MemSDNode>(Op))
6633  return DAG.getMergeValues({Undef, Op.getOperand(0)}, DL);
6634  return Undef;
6635  }
6636 
6637  EVT NewVT = NumVDataDwords > 1 ?
6638  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i32, NumVDataDwords)
6639  : MVT::i32;
6640 
6641  ResultTypes[0] = NewVT;
6642  if (ResultTypes.size() == 3) {
6643  // Original result was aggregate type used for TexFailCtrl results
6644  // The actual instruction returns as a vector type which has now been
6645  // created. Remove the aggregate result.
6646  ResultTypes.erase(&ResultTypes[1]);
6647  }
6648  }
6649 
6650  unsigned CPol = cast<ConstantSDNode>(
6651  Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->CachePolicyIndex))->getZExtValue();
6652  if (BaseOpcode->Atomic)
6653  CPol |= AMDGPU::CPol::GLC; // TODO no-return optimization
6654  if (CPol & ~AMDGPU::CPol::ALL)
6655  return Op;
6656 
6657  SmallVector<SDValue, 26> Ops;
6658  if (BaseOpcode->Store || BaseOpcode->Atomic)
6659  Ops.push_back(VData); // vdata
6660  if (UseNSA)
6661  append_range(Ops, VAddrs);
6662  else
6663  Ops.push_back(VAddr);
6664  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->RsrcIndex));
6665  if (BaseOpcode->Sampler)
6666  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(ArgOffset + Intr->SampIndex));
6667  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(DMask, DL, MVT::i32));
6668  if (IsGFX10Plus)
6669  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(DimInfo->Encoding, DL, MVT::i32));
6670  Ops.push_back(Unorm);
6671  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(CPol, DL, MVT::i32));
6672  Ops.push_back(IsA16 && // r128, a16 for gfx9
6673  ST->hasFeature(AMDGPU::FeatureR128A16) ? True : False);
6674  if (IsGFX10Plus)
6675  Ops.push_back(IsA16 ? True : False);
6676  if (!Subtarget->hasGFX90AInsts()) {
6677  Ops.push_back(TFE); //tfe
6678  } else if (cast<ConstantSDNode>(TFE)->getZExtValue()) {
6679  report_fatal_error("TFE is not supported on this GPU");
6680  }
6681  Ops.push_back(LWE); // lwe
6682  if (!IsGFX10Plus)
6683  Ops.push_back(DimInfo->DA ? True : False);
6684  if (BaseOpcode->HasD16)
6685  Ops.push_back(IsD16 ? True : False);
6686  if (isa<MemSDNode>(Op))
6687  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(0)); // chain
6688 
6689  int NumVAddrDwords =
6690  UseNSA ? VAddrs.size() : VAddr.getValueType().getSizeInBits() / 32;
6691  int Opcode = -1;
6692 
6693  if (IsGFX11Plus) {
6694  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(IntrOpcode,
6695  UseNSA ? AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx11NSA
6696  : AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx11Default,
6697  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
6698  } else if (IsGFX10Plus) {
6699  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(IntrOpcode,
6700  UseNSA ? AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx10NSA
6701  : AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx10Default,
6702  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
6703  } else {
6704  if (Subtarget->hasGFX90AInsts()) {
6705  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(IntrOpcode, AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx90a,
6706  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
6707  if (Opcode == -1)
6708  return makeV_ILLEGAL(Op, DAG);
6709  }
6710  if (Opcode == -1 &&
6711  Subtarget->getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
6712  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(IntrOpcode, AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx8,
6713  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
6714  if (Opcode == -1)
6715  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(IntrOpcode, AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx6,
6716  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
6717  }
6718  assert(Opcode != -1);
6719 
6720  MachineSDNode *NewNode = DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, ResultTypes, Ops);
6721  if (auto MemOp = dyn_cast<MemSDNode>(Op)) {
6722  MachineMemOperand *MemRef = MemOp->getMemOperand();
6723  DAG.setNodeMemRefs(NewNode, {MemRef});
6724  }
6725 
6726  if (BaseOpcode->AtomicX2) {
6727  SmallVector<SDValue, 1> Elt;
6728  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(SDValue(NewNode, 0), Elt, 0, 1);
6729  return DAG.getMergeValues({Elt[0], SDValue(NewNode, 1)}, DL);
6730  }
6731  if (BaseOpcode->Store)
6732  return SDValue(NewNode, 0);
6733  return constructRetValue(DAG, NewNode,
6734  OrigResultTypes, IsTexFail,
6735  Subtarget->hasUnpackedD16VMem(), IsD16,
6736  DMaskLanes, NumVDataDwords, DL);
6737 }
6738 
6739 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerSBuffer(EVT VT, SDLoc DL, SDValue Rsrc,
6740  SDValue Offset, SDValue CachePolicy,
6741  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6742  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6743 
6744  const DataLayout &DataLayout = DAG.getDataLayout();
6745  Align Alignment =
6746  DataLayout.getABITypeAlign(VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext()));
6747 
6748  MachineMemOperand *MMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(
6749  MachinePointerInfo(),
6750  MachineMemOperand::MOLoad | MachineMemOperand::MODereferenceable |
6751  MachineMemOperand::MOInvariant,
6752  VT.getStoreSize(), Alignment);
6753 
6754  if (!Offset->isDivergent()) {
6755  SDValue Ops[] = {
6756  Rsrc,
6757  Offset, // Offset
6758  CachePolicy
6759  };
6760 
6761  // Widen vec3 load to vec4.
6762  if (VT.isVector() && VT.getVectorNumElements() == 3) {
6763  EVT WidenedVT =
6764  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getVectorElementType(), 4);
6765  auto WidenedOp = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(
6766  AMDGPUISD::SBUFFER_LOAD, DL, DAG.getVTList(WidenedVT), Ops, WidenedVT,
6767  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO, 0, WidenedVT.getStoreSize()));
6768  auto Subvector = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, WidenedOp,
6769  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
6770  return Subvector;
6771  }
6772 
6773  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::SBUFFER_LOAD, DL,
6774  DAG.getVTList(VT), Ops, VT, MMO);
6775  }
6776 
6777  // We have a divergent offset. Emit a MUBUF buffer load instead. We can
6778  // assume that the buffer is unswizzled.
6779  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Loads;
6780  unsigned NumLoads = 1;
6781  MVT LoadVT = VT.getSimpleVT();
6782  unsigned NumElts = LoadVT.isVector() ? LoadVT.getVectorNumElements() : 1;
6783  assert((LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i32 ||
6784  LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f32));
6785 
6786  if (NumElts == 8 || NumElts == 16) {
6787  NumLoads = NumElts / 4;
6788  LoadVT = MVT::getVectorVT(LoadVT.getScalarType(), 4);
6789  }
6790 
6791  SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList({LoadVT, MVT::Glue});
6792  SDValue Ops[] = {
6793  DAG.getEntryNode(), // Chain
6794  Rsrc, // rsrc
6795  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
6796  {}, // voffset
6797  {}, // soffset
6798  {}, // offset
6799  CachePolicy, // cachepolicy
6800  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
6801  };
6802 
6803  // Use the alignment to ensure that the required offsets will fit into the
6804  // immediate offsets.
6805  setBufferOffsets(Offset, DAG, &Ops[3],
6806  NumLoads > 1 ? Align(16 * NumLoads) : Align(4));
6807 
6808  uint64_t InstOffset = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ops[5])->getZExtValue();
6809  for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumLoads; ++i) {
6810  Ops[5] = DAG.getTargetConstant(InstOffset + 16 * i, DL, MVT::i32);
6811  Loads.push_back(getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD, DL, VTList, Ops,
6812  LoadVT, MMO, DAG));
6813  }
6814 
6815  if (NumElts == 8 || NumElts == 16)
6816  return DAG.getNode(ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS, DL, VT, Loads);
6817 
6818  return Loads[0];
6819 }
6820 
6821 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerWorkitemID(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Op,
6822  unsigned Dim,
6823  const ArgDescriptor &Arg) const {
6824  SDLoc SL(Op);
6825  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6826  unsigned MaxID = Subtarget->getMaxWorkitemID(MF.getFunction(), Dim);
6827  if (MaxID == 0)
6828  return DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32);
6829 
6830  SDValue Val = loadInputValue(DAG, &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass, MVT::i32,
6831  SDLoc(DAG.getEntryNode()), Arg);
6832 
6833  // Don't bother inserting AssertZext for packed IDs since we're emitting the
6834  // masking operations anyway.
6835  //
6836  // TODO: We could assert the top bit is 0 for the source copy.
6837  if (Arg.isMasked())
6838  return Val;
6839 
6840  // Preserve the known bits after expansion to a copy.
6841  EVT SmallVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), llvm::bit_width(MaxID));
6842  return DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, SL, MVT::i32, Val,
6843  DAG.getValueType(SmallVT));
6844 }
6845 
6846 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(SDValue Op,
6847  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
6848  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
6849  auto MFI = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
6850 
6851  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
6852  SDLoc DL(Op);
6853  unsigned IntrinsicID = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
6854 
6855  // TODO: Should this propagate fast-math-flags?
6856 
6857  switch (IntrinsicID) {
6858  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_implicit_buffer_ptr: {
6859  if (getSubtarget()->isAmdHsaOrMesa(MF.getFunction()))
6860  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6861  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6862  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::IMPLICIT_BUFFER_PTR);
6863  }
6864  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_dispatch_ptr:
6865  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_queue_ptr: {
6866  if (!Subtarget->isAmdHsaOrMesa(MF.getFunction())) {
6867  DiagnosticInfoUnsupported BadIntrin(
6868  MF.getFunction(), "unsupported hsa intrinsic without hsa target",
6869  DL.getDebugLoc());
6870  DAG.getContext()->diagnose(BadIntrin);
6871  return DAG.getUNDEF(VT);
6872  }
6873 
6874  auto RegID = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_dispatch_ptr ?
6875  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::DISPATCH_PTR : AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::QUEUE_PTR;
6876  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT, RegID);
6877  }
6878  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_implicitarg_ptr: {
6879  if (MFI->isEntryFunction())
6880  return getImplicitArgPtr(DAG, DL);
6881  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6882  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::IMPLICIT_ARG_PTR);
6883  }
6884  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_kernarg_segment_ptr: {
6885  if (!AMDGPU::isKernel(MF.getFunction().getCallingConv())) {
6886  // This only makes sense to call in a kernel, so just lower to null.
6887  return DAG.getConstant(0, DL, VT);
6888  }
6889 
6890  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6891  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::KERNARG_SEGMENT_PTR);
6892  }
6893  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_dispatch_id: {
6894  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT, AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::DISPATCH_ID);
6895  }
6896  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp:
6897  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
6898  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq:
6899  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RSQ, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
6900  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_legacy:
6901  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
6902  return emitRemovedIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6903  return SDValue();
6904  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp_legacy:
6905  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
6906  return emitRemovedIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6907  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP_LEGACY, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
6908  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_clamp: {
6909  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
6910  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RSQ_CLAMP, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
6911 
6912  Type *Type = VT.getTypeForEVT(*DAG.getContext());
6913  APFloat Max = APFloat::getLargest(Type->getFltSemantics());
6914  APFloat Min = APFloat::getLargest(Type->getFltSemantics(), true);
6915 
6916  SDValue Rsq = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RSQ, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
6917  SDValue Tmp = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMINNUM, DL, VT, Rsq,
6918  DAG.getConstantFP(Max, DL, VT));
6919  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMAXNUM, DL, VT, Tmp,
6920  DAG.getConstantFP(Min, DL, VT));
6921  }
6922  case Intrinsic::r600_read_ngroups_x:
6923  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6924  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6925 
6926  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6927  SI::KernelInputOffsets::NGROUPS_X, Align(4),
6928  false);
6929  case Intrinsic::r600_read_ngroups_y:
6930  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6931  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6932 
6933  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6934  SI::KernelInputOffsets::NGROUPS_Y, Align(4),
6935  false);
6936  case Intrinsic::r600_read_ngroups_z:
6937  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6938  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6939 
6940  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6941  SI::KernelInputOffsets::NGROUPS_Z, Align(4),
6942  false);
6943  case Intrinsic::r600_read_global_size_x:
6944  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6945  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6946 
6947  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6948  SI::KernelInputOffsets::GLOBAL_SIZE_X,
6949  Align(4), false);
6950  case Intrinsic::r600_read_global_size_y:
6951  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6952  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6953 
6954  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6955  SI::KernelInputOffsets::GLOBAL_SIZE_Y,
6956  Align(4), false);
6957  case Intrinsic::r600_read_global_size_z:
6958  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6959  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6960 
6961  return lowerKernargMemParameter(DAG, VT, VT, DL, DAG.getEntryNode(),
6962  SI::KernelInputOffsets::GLOBAL_SIZE_Z,
6963  Align(4), false);
6964  case Intrinsic::r600_read_local_size_x:
6965  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6966  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6967 
6968  return lowerImplicitZextParam(DAG, Op, MVT::i16,
6969  SI::KernelInputOffsets::LOCAL_SIZE_X);
6970  case Intrinsic::r600_read_local_size_y:
6971  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6972  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6973 
6974  return lowerImplicitZextParam(DAG, Op, MVT::i16,
6975  SI::KernelInputOffsets::LOCAL_SIZE_Y);
6976  case Intrinsic::r600_read_local_size_z:
6977  if (Subtarget->isAmdHsaOS())
6978  return emitNonHSAIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
6979 
6980  return lowerImplicitZextParam(DAG, Op, MVT::i16,
6981  SI::KernelInputOffsets::LOCAL_SIZE_Z);
6982  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workgroup_id_x:
6983  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6984  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::WORKGROUP_ID_X);
6985  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workgroup_id_y:
6986  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6987  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::WORKGROUP_ID_Y);
6988  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workgroup_id_z:
6989  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6990  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::WORKGROUP_ID_Z);
6991  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_lds_kernel_id: {
6992  if (MFI->isEntryFunction())
6993  return getLDSKernelId(DAG, DL);
6994  return getPreloadedValue(DAG, *MFI, VT,
6995  AMDGPUFunctionArgInfo::LDS_KERNEL_ID);
6996  }
6997  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_x:
6998  return lowerWorkitemID(DAG, Op, 0, MFI->getArgInfo().WorkItemIDX);
6999  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_y:
7000  return lowerWorkitemID(DAG, Op, 1, MFI->getArgInfo().WorkItemIDY);
7001  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_z:
7002  return lowerWorkitemID(DAG, Op, 2, MFI->getArgInfo().WorkItemIDZ);
7003  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_wavefrontsize:
7004  return DAG.getConstant(MF.getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>().getWavefrontSize(),
7005  SDLoc(Op), MVT::i32);
7006  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_s_buffer_load: {
7007  unsigned CPol = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(3))->getZExtValue();
7008  if (CPol & ~AMDGPU::CPol::ALL)
7009  return Op;
7010  return lowerSBuffer(VT, DL, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3),
7011  DAG);
7012  }
7013  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fdiv_fast:
7014  return lowerFDIV_FAST(Op, DAG);
7015  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sin:
7016  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::SIN_HW, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
7017 
7018  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cos:
7019  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::COS_HW, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
7020 
7021  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_mul_u24:
7022  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::MUL_U24, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7023  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_mul_i24:
7024  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::MUL_I24, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7025 
7026  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_log_clamp: {
7027  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::VOLCANIC_ISLANDS)
7028  return SDValue();
7029 
7030  return emitRemovedIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, VT);
7031  }
7032  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ldexp:
7033  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::LDEXP, DL, VT,
7034  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7035 
7036  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fract:
7037  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FRACT, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
7038 
7039  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_class:
7040  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, DL, VT,
7041  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7042  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fmas:
7043  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FMAS, DL, VT,
7044  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3),
7045  Op.getOperand(4));
7046 
7047  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fixup:
7048  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP, DL, VT,
7049  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7050 
7051  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_scale: {
7052  const ConstantSDNode *Param = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(3));
7053 
7054  // Translate to the operands expected by the machine instruction. The
7055  // first parameter must be the same as the first instruction.
7056  SDValue Numerator = Op.getOperand(1);
7057  SDValue Denominator = Op.getOperand(2);
7058 
7059  // Note this order is opposite of the machine instruction's operations,
7060  // which is s0.f = Quotient, s1.f = Denominator, s2.f = Numerator. The
7061  // intrinsic has the numerator as the first operand to match a normal
7062  // division operation.
7063 
7064  SDValue Src0 = Param->isAllOnes() ? Numerator : Denominator;
7065 
7066  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE, DL, Op->getVTList(), Src0,
7067  Denominator, Numerator);
7068  }
7069  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_icmp: {
7070  // There is a Pat that handles this variant, so return it as-is.
7071  if (Op.getOperand(1).getValueType() == MVT::i1 &&
7072  Op.getConstantOperandVal(2) == 0 &&
7073  Op.getConstantOperandVal(3) == ICmpInst::Predicate::ICMP_NE)
7074  return Op;
7075  return lowerICMPIntrinsic(*this, Op.getNode(), DAG);
7076  }
7077  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fcmp: {
7078  return lowerFCMPIntrinsic(*this, Op.getNode(), DAG);
7079  }
7080  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ballot:
7081  return lowerBALLOTIntrinsic(*this, Op.getNode(), DAG);
7082  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmed3:
7083  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FMED3, DL, VT,
7084  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7085  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fdot2:
7086  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FDOT2, DL, VT,
7087  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3),
7088  Op.getOperand(4));
7089  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmul_legacy:
7090  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FMUL_LEGACY, DL, VT,
7091  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7092  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sffbh:
7093  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FFBH_I32, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1));
7094  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sbfe:
7095  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::BFE_I32, DL, VT,
7096  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7097  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ubfe:
7098  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::BFE_U32, DL, VT,
7099  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7100  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pkrtz:
7101  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_i16:
7102  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_u16:
7103  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pk_i16:
7104  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pk_u16: {
7105  // FIXME: Stop adding cast if v2f16/v2i16 are legal.
7106  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7107  unsigned Opcode;
7108 
7109  if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pkrtz)
7110  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32;
7111  else if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_i16)
7112  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKNORM_I16_F32;
7113  else if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pknorm_u16)
7114  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKNORM_U16_F32;
7115  else if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pk_i16)
7116  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::CVT_PK_I16_I32;
7117  else
7118  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::CVT_PK_U16_U32;
7119 
7120  if (isTypeLegal(VT))
7121  return DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7122 
7123  SDValue Node = DAG.getNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::i32,
7124  Op.getOperand(1), Op.getOperand(2));
7125  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Node);
7126  }
7127  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmad_ftz:
7128  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FMAD_FTZ, DL, VT, Op.getOperand(1),
7129  Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7130 
7131  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_if_break:
7132  return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::SI_IF_BREAK, DL, VT,
7133  Op->getOperand(1), Op->getOperand(2)), 0);
7134 
7135  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_groupstaticsize: {
7136  Triple::OSType OS = getTargetMachine().getTargetTriple().getOS();
7137  if (OS == Triple::AMDHSA || OS == Triple::AMDPAL)
7138  return Op;
7139 
7140  const Module *M = MF.getFunction().getParent();
7141  const GlobalValue *GV =
7142  M->getNamedValue(Intrinsic::getName(Intrinsic::amdgcn_groupstaticsize));
7143  SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, DL, MVT::i32, 0,
7144  SIInstrInfo::MO_ABS32_LO);
7145  return {DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, GA), 0};
7146  }
7147  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_shared:
7148  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_private: {
7149  SDLoc SL(Op);
7150  unsigned AS = (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_shared) ?
7151  AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS : AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS;
7152  SDValue Aperture = getSegmentAperture(AS, SL, DAG);
7153  SDValue SrcVec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::v2i32,
7154  Op.getOperand(1));
7155 
7156  SDValue SrcHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, SrcVec,
7157  DAG.getConstant(1, SL, MVT::i32));
7158  return DAG.getSetCC(SL, MVT::i1, SrcHi, Aperture, ISD::SETEQ);
7159  }
7160  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_perm:
7161  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PERM, DL, MVT::i32, Op.getOperand(1),
7162  Op.getOperand(2), Op.getOperand(3));
7163  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_reloc_constant: {
7164  Module *M = const_cast<Module *>(MF.getFunction().getParent());
7165  const MDNode *Metadata = cast<MDNodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getMD();
7166  auto SymbolName = cast<MDString>(Metadata->getOperand(0))->getString();
7167  auto RelocSymbol = cast<GlobalVariable>(
7168  M->getOrInsertGlobal(SymbolName, Type::getInt32Ty(M->getContext())));
7169  SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(RelocSymbol, DL, MVT::i32, 0,
7170  SIInstrInfo::MO_ABS32_LO);
7171  return {DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, GA), 0};
7172  }
7173  default:
7174  if (const AMDGPU::ImageDimIntrinsicInfo *ImageDimIntr =
7175  AMDGPU::getImageDimIntrinsicInfo(IntrinsicID))
7176  return lowerImage(Op, ImageDimIntr, DAG, false);
7177 
7178  return Op;
7179  }
7180 }
7181 
7182 /// Update \p MMO based on the offset inputs to an intrinsic.
7183 static void updateBufferMMO(MachineMemOperand *MMO, SDValue VOffset,
7184  SDValue SOffset, SDValue Offset,
7185  SDValue VIndex = SDValue()) {
7186  if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(VOffset) || !isa<ConstantSDNode>(SOffset) ||
7187  !isa<ConstantSDNode>(Offset)) {
7188  // The combined offset is not known to be constant, so we cannot represent
7189  // it in the MMO. Give up.
7190  MMO->setValue((Value *)nullptr);
7191  return;
7192  }
7193 
7194  if (VIndex && (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(VIndex) ||
7195  !cast<ConstantSDNode>(VIndex)->isZero())) {
7196  // The strided index component of the address is not known to be zero, so we
7197  // cannot represent it in the MMO. Give up.
7198  MMO->setValue((Value *)nullptr);
7199  return;
7200  }
7201 
7202  MMO->setOffset(cast<ConstantSDNode>(VOffset)->getSExtValue() +
7203  cast<ConstantSDNode>(SOffset)->getSExtValue() +
7204  cast<ConstantSDNode>(Offset)->getSExtValue());
7205 }
7206 
7207 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(SDValue Op,
7208  SelectionDAG &DAG,
7209  unsigned NewOpcode) const {
7210  SDLoc DL(Op);
7211 
7212  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
7213  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG);
7214  SDValue Ops[] = {
7215  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7216  VData, // vdata
7217  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
7218  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
7219  Offsets.first, // voffset
7220  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
7221  Offsets.second, // offset
7222  Op.getOperand(6), // cachepolicy
7223  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7224  };
7225 
7226  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7227  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6]);
7228 
7229  EVT MemVT = VData.getValueType();
7230  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(NewOpcode, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops, MemVT,
7231  M->getMemOperand());
7232 }
7233 
7234 // Return a value to use for the idxen operand by examining the vindex operand.
7235 static unsigned getIdxEn(SDValue VIndex) {
7236  if (auto VIndexC = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(VIndex))
7237  // No need to set idxen if vindex is known to be zero.
7238  return VIndexC->getZExtValue() != 0;
7239  return 1;
7240 }
7241 
7242 SDValue
7243 SITargetLowering::lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG,
7244  unsigned NewOpcode) const {
7245  SDLoc DL(Op);
7246 
7247  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
7248  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG);
7249  SDValue Ops[] = {
7250  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7251  VData, // vdata
7252  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
7253  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
7254  Offsets.first, // voffset
7255  Op.getOperand(6), // soffset
7256  Offsets.second, // offset
7257  Op.getOperand(7), // cachepolicy
7258  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7259  };
7260 
7261  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7262  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[3]);
7263 
7264  EVT MemVT = VData.getValueType();
7265  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(NewOpcode, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops, MemVT,
7266  M->getMemOperand());
7267 }
7268 
7269 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_W_CHAIN(SDValue Op,
7270  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7271  unsigned IntrID = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
7272  SDLoc DL(Op);
7273 
7274  switch (IntrID) {
7275  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_ordered_add:
7276  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_ordered_swap: {
7277  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7278  SDValue Chain = M->getOperand(0);
7279  SDValue M0 = M->getOperand(2);
7280  SDValue Value = M->getOperand(3);
7281  unsigned IndexOperand = M->getConstantOperandVal(7);
7282  unsigned WaveRelease = M->getConstantOperandVal(8);
7283  unsigned WaveDone = M->getConstantOperandVal(9);
7284 
7285  unsigned OrderedCountIndex = IndexOperand & 0x3f;
7286  IndexOperand &= ~0x3f;
7287  unsigned CountDw = 0;
7288 
7289  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10) {
7290  CountDw = (IndexOperand >> 24) & 0xf;
7291  IndexOperand &= ~(0xf << 24);
7292 
7293  if (CountDw < 1 || CountDw > 4) {
7294  report_fatal_error(
7295  "ds_ordered_count: dword count must be between 1 and 4");
7296  }
7297  }
7298 
7299  if (IndexOperand)
7300  report_fatal_error("ds_ordered_count: bad index operand");
7301 
7302  if (WaveDone && !WaveRelease)
7303  report_fatal_error("ds_ordered_count: wave_done requires wave_release");
7304 
7305  unsigned Instruction = IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_ordered_add ? 0 : 1;
7306  unsigned ShaderType =
7307  SIInstrInfo::getDSShaderTypeValue(DAG.getMachineFunction());
7308  unsigned Offset0 = OrderedCountIndex << 2;
7309  unsigned Offset1 = WaveRelease | (WaveDone << 1) | (Instruction << 4);
7310 
7311  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() >= AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10)
7312  Offset1 |= (CountDw - 1) << 6;
7313 
7314  if (Subtarget->getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX11)
7315  Offset1 |= ShaderType << 2;
7316 
7317  unsigned Offset = Offset0 | (Offset1 << 8);
7318 
7319  SDValue Ops[] = {
7320  Chain,
7321  Value,
7322  DAG.getTargetConstant(Offset, DL, MVT::i16),
7323  copyToM0(DAG, Chain, DL, M0).getValue(1), // Glue
7324  };
7325  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::DS_ORDERED_COUNT, DL,
7326  M->getVTList(), Ops, M->getMemoryVT(),
7327  M->getMemOperand());
7328  }
7329  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_inc:
7330  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_dec:
7331  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fadd: {
7332  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7333  unsigned Opc;
7334  switch (IntrID) {
7335  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fadd:
7336  Opc = ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FADD;
7337  break;
7338  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_inc:
7339  Opc = ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UINC_WRAP;
7340  break;
7341  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_dec:
7342  Opc = ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UDEC_WRAP;
7343  break;
7344  }
7345 
7346  return DAG.getAtomic(Opc, SDLoc(Op), M->getMemoryVT(),
7347  M->getOperand(0), M->getOperand(2), M->getOperand(3),
7348  M->getMemOperand());
7349  }
7350  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fmin:
7351  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fmax: {
7352  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7353  unsigned Opc;
7354  switch (IntrID) {
7355  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_inc:
7356  Opc = ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UINC_WRAP;
7357  break;
7358  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_atomic_dec:
7359  Opc = ISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_UDEC_WRAP;
7360  break;
7361  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fmin:
7362  Opc = AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN;
7363  break;
7364  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ds_fmax:
7365  Opc = AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX;
7366  break;
7367  default:
7368  llvm_unreachable("Unknown intrinsic!");
7369  }
7370  SDValue Ops[] = {
7371  M->getOperand(0), // Chain
7372  M->getOperand(2), // Ptr
7373  M->getOperand(3) // Value
7374  };
7375 
7376  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, SDLoc(Op), M->getVTList(), Ops,
7377  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
7378  }
7379  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_load:
7380  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_load_format: {
7381  unsigned Glc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(5))->getZExtValue();
7382  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(6))->getZExtValue();
7383  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(3));
7384  SDValue Ops[] = {
7385  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7386  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7387  Op.getOperand(3), // vindex
7388  SDValue(), // voffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7389  SDValue(), // soffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7390  SDValue(), // offset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7391  DAG.getTargetConstant(Glc | (Slc << 1), DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
7392  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7393  };
7394  setBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG, &Ops[3]);
7395 
7396  unsigned Opc = (IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_load) ?
7397  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT;
7398 
7399  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7400  EVT IntVT = VT.changeTypeToInteger();
7401  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7402  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[3], Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[2]);
7403  EVT LoadVT = Op.getValueType();
7404 
7405  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16)
7406  return adjustLoadValueType(AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_D16,
7407  M, DAG, Ops);
7408 
7409  // Handle BUFFER_LOAD_BYTE/UBYTE/SHORT/USHORT overloaded intrinsics
7410  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i8 ||
7411  LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i16)
7412  return handleByteShortBufferLoads(DAG, LoadVT, DL, Ops, M);
7413 
7414  return getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops, IntVT,
7415  M->getMemOperand(), DAG);
7416  }
7417  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_load:
7418  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_load_format: {
7419  const bool IsFormat = IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_load_format;
7420 
7421  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(3), DAG);
7422  SDValue Ops[] = {
7423  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7424  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7425  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
7426  Offsets.first, // voffset
7427  Op.getOperand(4), // soffset
7428  Offsets.second, // offset
7429  Op.getOperand(5), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
7430  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7431  };
7432 
7433  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7434  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[3], Ops[4], Ops[5]);
7435  return lowerIntrinsicLoad(M, IsFormat, DAG, Ops);
7436  }
7437  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_load:
7438  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_load_format: {
7439  const bool IsFormat = IntrID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_load_format;
7440 
7441  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG);
7442  SDValue Ops[] = {
7443  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7444  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7445  Op.getOperand(3), // vindex
7446  Offsets.first, // voffset
7447  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
7448  Offsets.second, // offset
7449  Op.getOperand(6), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
7450  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7451  };
7452 
7453  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7454  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[3], Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[2]);
7455  return lowerIntrinsicLoad(cast<MemSDNode>(Op), IsFormat, DAG, Ops);
7456  }
7457  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_tbuffer_load: {
7458  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7459  EVT LoadVT = Op.getValueType();
7460 
7461  unsigned Dfmt = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(7))->getZExtValue();
7462  unsigned Nfmt = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(8))->getZExtValue();
7463  unsigned Glc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(9))->getZExtValue();
7464  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(10))->getZExtValue();
7465  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(3));
7466  SDValue Ops[] = {
7467  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7468  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7469  Op.getOperand(3), // vindex
7470  Op.getOperand(4), // voffset
7471  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
7472  Op.getOperand(6), // offset
7473  DAG.getTargetConstant(Dfmt | (Nfmt << 4), DL, MVT::i32), // format
7474  DAG.getTargetConstant(Glc | (Slc << 1), DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
7475  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1) // idxen
7476  };
7477 
7478  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16)
7479  return adjustLoadValueType(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_D16,
7480  M, DAG, Ops);
7481  return getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT, DL,
7482  Op->getVTList(), Ops, LoadVT, M->getMemOperand(),
7483  DAG);
7484  }
7485  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_tbuffer_load: {
7486  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7487  EVT LoadVT = Op.getValueType();
7488  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(3), DAG);
7489 
7490  SDValue Ops[] = {
7491  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7492  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7493  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
7494  Offsets.first, // voffset
7495  Op.getOperand(4), // soffset
7496  Offsets.second, // offset
7497  Op.getOperand(5), // format
7498  Op.getOperand(6), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
7499  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7500  };
7501 
7502  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16)
7503  return adjustLoadValueType(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_D16,
7504  M, DAG, Ops);
7505  return getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT, DL,
7506  Op->getVTList(), Ops, LoadVT, M->getMemOperand(),
7507  DAG);
7508  }
7509  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_tbuffer_load: {
7510  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7511  EVT LoadVT = Op.getValueType();
7512  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG);
7513 
7514  SDValue Ops[] = {
7515  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7516  Op.getOperand(2), // rsrc
7517  Op.getOperand(3), // vindex
7518  Offsets.first, // voffset
7519  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
7520  Offsets.second, // offset
7521  Op.getOperand(6), // format
7522  Op.getOperand(7), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
7523  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7524  };
7525 
7526  if (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::f16)
7527  return adjustLoadValueType(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT_D16,
7528  M, DAG, Ops);
7529  return getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_LOAD_FORMAT, DL,
7530  Op->getVTList(), Ops, LoadVT, M->getMemOperand(),
7531  DAG);
7532  }
7533  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_swap:
7534  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_add:
7535  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_sub:
7536  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_csub:
7537  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_smin:
7538  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_umin:
7539  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_smax:
7540  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_umax:
7541  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_and:
7542  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_or:
7543  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_xor:
7544  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_fadd: {
7545  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(6))->getZExtValue();
7546  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(4));
7547  SDValue Ops[] = {
7548  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7549  Op.getOperand(2), // vdata
7550  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
7551  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
