7552  SDValue(), // voffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7553  SDValue(), // soffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7554  SDValue(), // offset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7555  DAG.getTargetConstant(Slc << 1, DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
7556  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7557  };
7558  setBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG, &Ops[4]);
7559 
7560  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7561 
7562  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7563  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[3]);
7564  unsigned Opcode = 0;
7565 
7566  switch (IntrID) {
7567  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_swap:
7568  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SWAP;
7569  break;
7570  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_add:
7571  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_ADD;
7572  break;
7573  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_sub:
7574  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SUB;
7575  break;
7576  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_csub:
7577  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CSUB;
7578  break;
7579  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_smin:
7580  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMIN;
7581  break;
7582  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_umin:
7583  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMIN;
7584  break;
7585  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_smax:
7586  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMAX;
7587  break;
7588  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_umax:
7589  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMAX;
7590  break;
7591  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_and:
7592  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_AND;
7593  break;
7594  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_or:
7595  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_OR;
7596  break;
7597  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_xor:
7598  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_XOR;
7599  break;
7600  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_fadd:
7601  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FADD;
7602  break;
7603  default:
7604  llvm_unreachable("unhandled atomic opcode");
7605  }
7606 
7607  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops, VT,
7608  M->getMemOperand());
7609  }
7610  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_fadd:
7611  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FADD);
7612  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_fadd:
7613  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FADD);
7614  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_fmin:
7615  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMIN);
7616  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_fmin:
7617  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMIN);
7618  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_fmax:
7619  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMAX);
7620  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_fmax:
7621  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMAX);
7622  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_swap:
7623  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SWAP);
7624  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_add:
7625  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_ADD);
7626  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_sub:
7627  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SUB);
7628  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_smin:
7629  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMIN);
7630  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_umin:
7631  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMIN);
7632  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_smax:
7633  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMAX);
7634  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_umax:
7635  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMAX);
7636  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_and:
7637  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_AND);
7638  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_or:
7639  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_OR);
7640  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_xor:
7641  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_XOR);
7642  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_inc:
7643  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_INC);
7644  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_dec:
7645  return lowerRawBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_DEC);
7646  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_swap:
7647  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG,
7648  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SWAP);
7649  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_add:
7650  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_ADD);
7651  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_sub:
7652  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SUB);
7653  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_smin:
7654  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG,
7655  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMIN);
7656  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_umin:
7657  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG,
7658  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMIN);
7659  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_smax:
7660  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG,
7661  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMAX);
7662  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_umax:
7663  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG,
7664  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMAX);
7665  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_and:
7666  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_AND);
7667  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_or:
7668  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_OR);
7669  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_xor:
7670  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_XOR);
7671  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_inc:
7672  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_INC);
7673  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_dec:
7674  return lowerStructBufferAtomicIntrin(Op, DAG, AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_DEC);
7675 
7676  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_atomic_cmpswap: {
7677  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(7))->getZExtValue();
7678  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(5));
7679  SDValue Ops[] = {
7680  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7681  Op.getOperand(2), // src
7682  Op.getOperand(3), // cmp
7683  Op.getOperand(4), // rsrc
7684  Op.getOperand(5), // vindex
7685  SDValue(), // voffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7686  SDValue(), // soffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7687  SDValue(), // offset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
7688  DAG.getTargetConstant(Slc << 1, DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
7689  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7690  };
7691  setBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(6), DAG, &Ops[5]);
7692 
7693  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7694  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7695  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[7], Ops[4]);
7696 
7697  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CMPSWAP, DL,
7698  Op->getVTList(), Ops, VT, M->getMemOperand());
7699  }
7700  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_atomic_cmpswap: {
7701  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG);
7702  SDValue Ops[] = {
7703  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7704  Op.getOperand(2), // src
7705  Op.getOperand(3), // cmp
7706  Op.getOperand(4), // rsrc
7707  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
7708  Offsets.first, // voffset
7709  Op.getOperand(6), // soffset
7710  Offsets.second, // offset
7711  Op.getOperand(7), // cachepolicy
7712  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7713  };
7714  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7715  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7716  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[7]);
7717 
7718  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CMPSWAP, DL,
7719  Op->getVTList(), Ops, VT, M->getMemOperand());
7720  }
7721  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_atomic_cmpswap: {
7722  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(6), DAG);
7723  SDValue Ops[] = {
7724  Op.getOperand(0), // Chain
7725  Op.getOperand(2), // src
7726  Op.getOperand(3), // cmp
7727  Op.getOperand(4), // rsrc
7728  Op.getOperand(5), // vindex
7729  Offsets.first, // voffset
7730  Op.getOperand(7), // soffset
7731  Offsets.second, // offset
7732  Op.getOperand(8), // cachepolicy
7733  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
7734  };
7735  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
7736  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7737  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[7], Ops[4]);
7738 
7739  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CMPSWAP, DL,
7740  Op->getVTList(), Ops, VT, M->getMemOperand());
7741  }
7742  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_image_bvh_intersect_ray: {
7743  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7744  SDValue NodePtr = M->getOperand(2);
7745  SDValue RayExtent = M->getOperand(3);
7746  SDValue RayOrigin = M->getOperand(4);
7747  SDValue RayDir = M->getOperand(5);
7748  SDValue RayInvDir = M->getOperand(6);
7749  SDValue TDescr = M->getOperand(7);
7750 
7751  assert(NodePtr.getValueType() == MVT::i32 ||
7752  NodePtr.getValueType() == MVT::i64);
7753  assert(RayDir.getValueType() == MVT::v3f16 ||
7754  RayDir.getValueType() == MVT::v3f32);
7755 
7756  if (!Subtarget->hasGFX10_AEncoding()) {
7757  emitRemovedIntrinsicError(DAG, DL, Op.getValueType());
7758  return SDValue();
7759  }
7760 
7761  const bool IsGFX11Plus = AMDGPU::isGFX11Plus(*Subtarget);
7762  const bool IsA16 = RayDir.getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::f16;
7763  const bool Is64 = NodePtr.getValueType() == MVT::i64;
7764  const unsigned NumVDataDwords = 4;
7765  const unsigned NumVAddrDwords = IsA16 ? (Is64 ? 9 : 8) : (Is64 ? 12 : 11);
7766  const unsigned NumVAddrs = IsGFX11Plus ? (IsA16 ? 4 : 5) : NumVAddrDwords;
7767  const bool UseNSA =
7768  Subtarget->hasNSAEncoding() && NumVAddrs <= Subtarget->getNSAMaxSize();
7769  const unsigned BaseOpcodes[2][2] = {
7770  {AMDGPU::IMAGE_BVH_INTERSECT_RAY, AMDGPU::IMAGE_BVH_INTERSECT_RAY_a16},
7771  {AMDGPU::IMAGE_BVH64_INTERSECT_RAY,
7772  AMDGPU::IMAGE_BVH64_INTERSECT_RAY_a16}};
7773  int Opcode;
7774  if (UseNSA) {
7775  Opcode = AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(BaseOpcodes[Is64][IsA16],
7776  IsGFX11Plus ? AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx11NSA
7777  : AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx10NSA,
7778  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
7779  } else {
7780  Opcode =
7781  AMDGPU::getMIMGOpcode(BaseOpcodes[Is64][IsA16],
7782  IsGFX11Plus ? AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx11Default
7783  : AMDGPU::MIMGEncGfx10Default,
7784  NumVDataDwords, NumVAddrDwords);
7785  }
7786  assert(Opcode != -1);
7787 
7788  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
7789 
7790  auto packLanes = [&DAG, &Ops, &DL] (SDValue Op, bool IsAligned) {
7791  SmallVector<SDValue, 3> Lanes;
7792  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(Op, Lanes, 0, 3);
7793  if (Lanes[0].getValueSizeInBits() == 32) {
7794  for (unsigned I = 0; I < 3; ++I)
7795  Ops.push_back(DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32, Lanes[I]));
7796  } else {
7797  if (IsAligned) {
7798  Ops.push_back(
7799  DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32,
7800  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2f16, DL,
7801  { Lanes[0], Lanes[1] })));
7802  Ops.push_back(Lanes[2]);
7803  } else {
7804  SDValue Elt0 = Ops.pop_back_val();
7805  Ops.push_back(
7806  DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32,
7807  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2f16, DL,
7808  { Elt0, Lanes[0] })));
7809  Ops.push_back(
7810  DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32,
7811  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2f16, DL,
7812  { Lanes[1], Lanes[2] })));
7813  }
7814  }
7815  };
7816 
7817  if (UseNSA && IsGFX11Plus) {
7818  Ops.push_back(NodePtr);
7819  Ops.push_back(DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32, RayExtent));
7820  Ops.push_back(RayOrigin);
7821  if (IsA16) {
7822  SmallVector<SDValue, 3> DirLanes, InvDirLanes, MergedLanes;
7823  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(RayDir, DirLanes, 0, 3);
7824  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(RayInvDir, InvDirLanes, 0, 3);
7825  for (unsigned I = 0; I < 3; ++I) {
7826  MergedLanes.push_back(DAG.getBitcast(
7827  MVT::i32, DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2f16, DL,
7828  {DirLanes[I], InvDirLanes[I]})));
7829  }
7830  Ops.push_back(DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v3i32, DL, MergedLanes));
7831  } else {
7832  Ops.push_back(RayDir);
7833  Ops.push_back(RayInvDir);
7834  }
7835  } else {
7836  if (Is64)
7837  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v2i32, NodePtr), Ops, 0,
7838  2);
7839  else
7840  Ops.push_back(NodePtr);
7841 
7842  Ops.push_back(DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32, RayExtent));
7843  packLanes(RayOrigin, true);
7844  packLanes(RayDir, true);
7845  packLanes(RayInvDir, false);
7846  }
7847 
7848  if (!UseNSA) {
7849  // Build a single vector containing all the operands so far prepared.
7850  if (NumVAddrDwords > 12) {
7851  SDValue Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32);
7852  Ops.append(16 - Ops.size(), Undef);
7853  }
7854  assert(Ops.size() >= 8 && Ops.size() <= 12);
7855  SDValue MergedOps = DAG.getBuildVector(
7856  MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i32, Ops.size()), DL, Ops);
7857  Ops.clear();
7858  Ops.push_back(MergedOps);
7859  }
7860 
7861  Ops.push_back(TDescr);
7862  if (IsA16)
7863  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1));
7864  Ops.push_back(M->getChain());
7865 
7866  auto *NewNode = DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, M->getVTList(), Ops);
7867  MachineMemOperand *MemRef = M->getMemOperand();
7868  DAG.setNodeMemRefs(NewNode, {MemRef});
7869  return SDValue(NewNode, 0);
7870  }
7871  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_atomic_fadd: {
7872  if (!Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddNoRtnInsts())
7873  return makeV_ILLEGAL(Op, DAG);
7874  return SDValue();
7875  }
7876  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_atomic_fmin:
7877  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_atomic_fmax:
7878  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_flat_atomic_fmin:
7879  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_flat_atomic_fmax: {
7880  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
7881  SDValue Ops[] = {
7882  M->getOperand(0), // Chain
7883  M->getOperand(2), // Ptr
7884  M->getOperand(3) // Value
7885  };
7886  unsigned Opcode = 0;
7887  switch (IntrID) {
7888  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_atomic_fmin:
7889  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_flat_atomic_fmin: {
7890  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN;
7891  break;
7892  }
7893  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_atomic_fmax:
7894  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_flat_atomic_fmax: {
7895  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX;
7896  break;
7897  }
7898  default:
7899  llvm_unreachable("unhandled atomic opcode");
7900  }
7901  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, SDLoc(Op),
7902  M->getVTList(), Ops, M->getMemoryVT(),
7903  M->getMemOperand());
7904  }
7905  default:
7906 
7907  if (const AMDGPU::ImageDimIntrinsicInfo *ImageDimIntr =
7908  AMDGPU::getImageDimIntrinsicInfo(IntrID))
7909  return lowerImage(Op, ImageDimIntr, DAG, true);
7910 
7911  return SDValue();
7912  }
7913 }
7914 
7915 // Call DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode for a load, but first widen a dwordx3 type to
7916 // dwordx4 if on SI and handle TFE loads.
7917 SDValue SITargetLowering::getMemIntrinsicNode(unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &DL,
7918  SDVTList VTList,
7919  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops, EVT MemVT,
7920  MachineMemOperand *MMO,
7921  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
7922  LLVMContext &C = *DAG.getContext();
7923  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
7924  EVT VT = VTList.VTs[0];
7925 
7926  assert(VTList.NumVTs == 2 || VTList.NumVTs == 3);
7927  bool IsTFE = VTList.NumVTs == 3;
7928  if (IsTFE) {
7929  unsigned NumValueDWords = divideCeil(VT.getSizeInBits(), 32);
7930  unsigned NumOpDWords = NumValueDWords + 1;
7931  EVT OpDWordsVT = EVT::getVectorVT(C, MVT::i32, NumOpDWords);
7932  SDVTList OpDWordsVTList = DAG.getVTList(OpDWordsVT, VTList.VTs[2]);
7933  MachineMemOperand *OpDWordsMMO =
7934  MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO, 0, NumOpDWords * 4);
7935  SDValue Op = getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, OpDWordsVTList, Ops,
7936  OpDWordsVT, OpDWordsMMO, DAG);
7937  SDValue Status = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, Op,
7938  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(NumValueDWords, DL));
7939  SDValue ZeroIdx = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL);
7940  SDValue ValueDWords =
7941  NumValueDWords == 1
7942  ? DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, Op, ZeroIdx)
7943  : DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL,
7944  EVT::getVectorVT(C, MVT::i32, NumValueDWords), Op,
7945  ZeroIdx);
7946  SDValue Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, ValueDWords);
7947  return DAG.getMergeValues({Value, Status, SDValue(Op.getNode(), 1)}, DL);
7948  }
7949 
7950  if (!Subtarget->hasDwordx3LoadStores() &&
7951  (VT == MVT::v3i32 || VT == MVT::v3f32)) {
7952  EVT WidenedVT = EVT::getVectorVT(C, VT.getVectorElementType(), 4);
7953  EVT WidenedMemVT = EVT::getVectorVT(C, MemVT.getVectorElementType(), 4);
7954  MachineMemOperand *WidenedMMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO, 0, 16);
7955  SDVTList WidenedVTList = DAG.getVTList(WidenedVT, VTList.VTs[1]);
7956  SDValue Op = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, WidenedVTList, Ops,
7957  WidenedMemVT, WidenedMMO);
7958  SDValue Value = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR, DL, VT, Op,
7959  DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(0, DL));
7960  return DAG.getMergeValues({Value, SDValue(Op.getNode(), 1)}, DL);
7961  }
7962 
7963  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opcode, DL, VTList, Ops, MemVT, MMO);
7964 }
7965 
7966 SDValue SITargetLowering::handleD16VData(SDValue VData, SelectionDAG &DAG,
7967  bool ImageStore) const {
7968  EVT StoreVT = VData.getValueType();
7969 
7970  // No change for f16 and legal vector D16 types.
7971  if (!StoreVT.isVector())
7972  return VData;
7973 
7974  SDLoc DL(VData);
7975  unsigned NumElements = StoreVT.getVectorNumElements();
7976 
7977  if (Subtarget->hasUnpackedD16VMem()) {
7978  // We need to unpack the packed data to store.
7979  EVT IntStoreVT = StoreVT.changeTypeToInteger();
7980  SDValue IntVData = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, IntStoreVT, VData);
7981 
7982  EVT EquivStoreVT =
7983  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i32, NumElements);
7984  SDValue ZExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, EquivStoreVT, IntVData);
7985  return DAG.UnrollVectorOp(ZExt.getNode());
7986  }
7987 
7988  // The sq block of gfx8.1 does not estimate register use correctly for d16
7989  // image store instructions. The data operand is computed as if it were not a
7990  // d16 image instruction.
7991  if (ImageStore && Subtarget->hasImageStoreD16Bug()) {
7992  // Bitcast to i16
7993  EVT IntStoreVT = StoreVT.changeTypeToInteger();
7994  SDValue IntVData = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, IntStoreVT, VData);
7995 
7996  // Decompose into scalars
7997  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> Elts;
7998  DAG.ExtractVectorElements(IntVData, Elts);
7999 
8000  // Group pairs of i16 into v2i16 and bitcast to i32
8001  SmallVector<SDValue, 4> PackedElts;
8002  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Elts.size() / 2; I += 1) {
8003  SDValue Pair =
8004  DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i16, DL, {Elts[I * 2], Elts[I * 2 + 1]});
8005  SDValue IntPair = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Pair);
8006  PackedElts.push_back(IntPair);
8007  }
8008  if ((NumElements % 2) == 1) {
8009  // Handle v3i16
8010  unsigned I = Elts.size() / 2;
8011  SDValue Pair = DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i16, DL,
8012  {Elts[I * 2], DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i16)});
8013  SDValue IntPair = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i32, Pair);
8014  PackedElts.push_back(IntPair);
8015  }
8016 
8017  // Pad using UNDEF
8018  PackedElts.resize(Elts.size(), DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32));
8019 
8020  // Build final vector
8021  EVT VecVT =
8022  EVT::getVectorVT(*DAG.getContext(), MVT::i32, PackedElts.size());
8023  return DAG.getBuildVector(VecVT, DL, PackedElts);
8024  }
8025 
8026  if (NumElements == 3) {
8027  EVT IntStoreVT =
8028  EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), StoreVT.getStoreSizeInBits());
8029  SDValue IntVData = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, IntStoreVT, VData);
8030 
8031  EVT WidenedStoreVT = EVT::getVectorVT(
8032  *DAG.getContext(), StoreVT.getVectorElementType(), NumElements + 1);
8033  EVT WidenedIntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(),
8034  WidenedStoreVT.getStoreSizeInBits());
8035  SDValue ZExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, WidenedIntVT, IntVData);
8036  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, WidenedStoreVT, ZExt);
8037  }
8038 
8039  assert(isTypeLegal(StoreVT));
8040  return VData;
8041 }
8042 
8043 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerINTRINSIC_VOID(SDValue Op,
8044  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8045  SDLoc DL(Op);
8046  SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
8047  unsigned IntrinsicID = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getZExtValue();
8048  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
8049 
8050  switch (IntrinsicID) {
8051  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_exp_compr: {
8052  if (!Subtarget->hasCompressedExport()) {
8053  DiagnosticInfoUnsupported BadIntrin(
8054  DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction(),
8055  "intrinsic not supported on subtarget", DL.getDebugLoc());
8056  DAG.getContext()->diagnose(BadIntrin);
8057  }
8058  SDValue Src0 = Op.getOperand(4);
8059  SDValue Src1 = Op.getOperand(5);
8060  // Hack around illegal type on SI by directly selecting it.
8061  if (isTypeLegal(Src0.getValueType()))
8062  return SDValue();
8063 
8064  const ConstantSDNode *Done = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(6));
8065  SDValue Undef = DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::f32);
8066  const SDValue Ops[] = {
8067  Op.getOperand(2), // tgt
8068  DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Src0), // src0
8069  DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::f32, Src1), // src1
8070  Undef, // src2
8071  Undef, // src3
8072  Op.getOperand(7), // vm
8073  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // compr
8074  Op.getOperand(3), // en
8075  Op.getOperand(0) // Chain
8076  };
8077 
8078  unsigned Opc = Done->isZero() ? AMDGPU::EXP : AMDGPU::EXP_DONE;
8079  return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops), 0);
8080  }
8081  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_s_barrier: {
8082  if (getTargetMachine().getOptLevel() > CodeGenOpt::None) {
8083  const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
8084  unsigned WGSize = ST.getFlatWorkGroupSizes(MF.getFunction()).second;
8085  if (WGSize <= ST.getWavefrontSize())
8086  return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::WAVE_BARRIER, DL, MVT::Other,
8087  Op.getOperand(0)), 0);
8088  }
8089  return SDValue();
8090  };
8091  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_tbuffer_store: {
8092  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8093  bool IsD16 = (VData.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::f16);
8094  if (IsD16)
8095  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8096  unsigned Dfmt = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(8))->getZExtValue();
8097  unsigned Nfmt = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(9))->getZExtValue();
8098  unsigned Glc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(10))->getZExtValue();
8099  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(11))->getZExtValue();
8100  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(4));
8101  SDValue Ops[] = {
8102  Chain,
8103  VData, // vdata
8104  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8105  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
8106  Op.getOperand(5), // voffset
8107  Op.getOperand(6), // soffset
8108  Op.getOperand(7), // offset
8109  DAG.getTargetConstant(Dfmt | (Nfmt << 4), DL, MVT::i32), // format
8110  DAG.getTargetConstant(Glc | (Slc << 1), DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
8111  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8112  };
8113  unsigned Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 :
8114  AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT;
8115  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8116  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8117  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8118  }
8119 
8120  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_tbuffer_store: {
8121  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8122  bool IsD16 = (VData.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::f16);
8123  if (IsD16)
8124  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8125  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG);
8126  SDValue Ops[] = {
8127  Chain,
8128  VData, // vdata
8129  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8130  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
8131  Offsets.first, // voffset
8132  Op.getOperand(6), // soffset
8133  Offsets.second, // offset
8134  Op.getOperand(7), // format
8135  Op.getOperand(8), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
8136  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8137  };
8138  unsigned Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 :
8139  AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT;
8140  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8141  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8142  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8143  }
8144 
8145  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_tbuffer_store: {
8146  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8147  bool IsD16 = (VData.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::f16);
8148  if (IsD16)
8149  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8150  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG);
8151  SDValue Ops[] = {
8152  Chain,
8153  VData, // vdata
8154  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8155  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
8156  Offsets.first, // voffset
8157  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
8158  Offsets.second, // offset
8159  Op.getOperand(6), // format
8160  Op.getOperand(7), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
8161  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8162  };
8163  unsigned Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 :
8164  AMDGPUISD::TBUFFER_STORE_FORMAT;
8165  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8166  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8167  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8168  }
8169 
8170  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_store:
8171  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_store_format: {
8172  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8173  bool IsD16 = (VData.getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::f16);
8174  if (IsD16)
8175  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8176  unsigned Glc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(6))->getZExtValue();
8177  unsigned Slc = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(7))->getZExtValue();
8178  unsigned IdxEn = getIdxEn(Op.getOperand(4));
8179  SDValue Ops[] = {
8180  Chain,
8181  VData,
8182  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8183  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
8184  SDValue(), // voffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
8185  SDValue(), // soffset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
8186  SDValue(), // offset -- will be set by setBufferOffsets
8187  DAG.getTargetConstant(Glc | (Slc << 1), DL, MVT::i32), // cachepolicy
8188  DAG.getTargetConstant(IdxEn, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8189  };
8190  setBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG, &Ops[4]);
8191 
8192  unsigned Opc = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_buffer_store ?
8193  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT;
8194  Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 : Opc;
8195  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8196  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[3]);
8197 
8198  // Handle BUFFER_STORE_BYTE/SHORT overloaded intrinsics
8199  EVT VDataType = VData.getValueType().getScalarType();
8200  if (VDataType == MVT::i8 || VDataType == MVT::i16)
8201  return handleByteShortBufferStores(DAG, VDataType, DL, Ops, M);
8202 
8203  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8204  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8205  }
8206 
8207  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_store:
8208  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_store_format: {
8209  const bool IsFormat =
8210  IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_store_format;
8211 
8212  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8213  EVT VDataVT = VData.getValueType();
8214  EVT EltType = VDataVT.getScalarType();
8215  bool IsD16 = IsFormat && (EltType.getSizeInBits() == 16);
8216  if (IsD16) {
8217  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8218  VDataVT = VData.getValueType();
8219  }
8220 
8221  if (!isTypeLegal(VDataVT)) {
8222  VData =
8223  DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL,
8224  getEquivalentMemType(*DAG.getContext(), VDataVT), VData);
8225  }
8226 
8227  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(4), DAG);
8228  SDValue Ops[] = {
8229  Chain,
8230  VData,
8231  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8232  DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32), // vindex
8233  Offsets.first, // voffset
8234  Op.getOperand(5), // soffset
8235  Offsets.second, // offset
8236  Op.getOperand(6), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
8237  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8238  };
8239  unsigned Opc =
8240  IsFormat ? AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE;
8241  Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 : Opc;
8242  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8243  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6]);
8244 
8245  // Handle BUFFER_STORE_BYTE/SHORT overloaded intrinsics
8246  if (!IsD16 && !VDataVT.isVector() && EltType.getSizeInBits() < 32)
8247  return handleByteShortBufferStores(DAG, VDataVT, DL, Ops, M);
8248 
8249  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8250  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8251  }
8252 
8253  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_store:
8254  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_store_format: {
8255  const bool IsFormat =
8256  IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_store_format;
8257 
8258  SDValue VData = Op.getOperand(2);
8259  EVT VDataVT = VData.getValueType();
8260  EVT EltType = VDataVT.getScalarType();
8261  bool IsD16 = IsFormat && (EltType.getSizeInBits() == 16);
8262 
8263  if (IsD16) {
8264  VData = handleD16VData(VData, DAG);
8265  VDataVT = VData.getValueType();
8266  }
8267 
8268  if (!isTypeLegal(VDataVT)) {
8269  VData =
8270  DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL,
8271  getEquivalentMemType(*DAG.getContext(), VDataVT), VData);
8272  }
8273 
8274  auto Offsets = splitBufferOffsets(Op.getOperand(5), DAG);
8275  SDValue Ops[] = {
8276  Chain,
8277  VData,
8278  Op.getOperand(3), // rsrc
8279  Op.getOperand(4), // vindex
8280  Offsets.first, // voffset
8281  Op.getOperand(6), // soffset
8282  Offsets.second, // offset
8283  Op.getOperand(7), // cachepolicy, swizzled buffer
8284  DAG.getTargetConstant(1, DL, MVT::i1), // idxen
8285  };
8286  unsigned Opc = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_store ?
8287  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT;
8288  Opc = IsD16 ? AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_FORMAT_D16 : Opc;
8289  MemSDNode *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8290  updateBufferMMO(M->getMemOperand(), Ops[4], Ops[5], Ops[6], Ops[3]);
8291 
8292  // Handle BUFFER_STORE_BYTE/SHORT overloaded intrinsics
8293  EVT VDataType = VData.getValueType().getScalarType();
8294  if (!IsD16 && !VDataVT.isVector() && EltType.getSizeInBits() < 32)
8295  return handleByteShortBufferStores(DAG, VDataType, DL, Ops, M);
8296 
8297  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops,
8298  M->getMemoryVT(), M->getMemOperand());
8299  }
8300  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_raw_buffer_load_lds:
8301  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_load_lds: {
8302  unsigned Opc;
8303  bool HasVIndex = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_struct_buffer_load_lds;
8304  unsigned OpOffset = HasVIndex ? 1 : 0;
8305  SDValue VOffset = Op.getOperand(5 + OpOffset);
8306  auto CVOffset = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(VOffset);
8307  bool HasVOffset = !CVOffset || !CVOffset->isZero();
8308  unsigned Size = Op->getConstantOperandVal(4);
8309 
8310  switch (Size) {
8311  default:
8312  return SDValue();
8313  case 1:
8314  Opc = HasVIndex ? HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE_LDS_BOTHEN
8315  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE_LDS_IDXEN
8316  : HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE_LDS_OFFEN
8317  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE_LDS_OFFSET;
8318  break;
8319  case 2:
8320  Opc = HasVIndex ? HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT_LDS_BOTHEN
8321  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT_LDS_IDXEN
8322  : HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT_LDS_OFFEN
8323  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT_LDS_OFFSET;
8324  break;
8325  case 4:
8326  Opc = HasVIndex ? HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_LDS_BOTHEN
8327  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_LDS_IDXEN
8328  : HasVOffset ? AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_LDS_OFFEN
8329  : AMDGPU::BUFFER_LOAD_DWORD_LDS_OFFSET;
8330  break;
8331  }
8332 
8333  SDValue M0Val = copyToM0(DAG, Chain, DL, Op.getOperand(3));
8334 
8335  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
8336 
8337  if (HasVIndex && HasVOffset)
8338  Ops.push_back(DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i32, DL,
8339  { Op.getOperand(5), // VIndex
8340  VOffset }));
8341  else if (HasVIndex)
8342  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(5));
8343  else if (HasVOffset)
8344  Ops.push_back(VOffset);
8345 
8346  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(2)); // rsrc
8347  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(6 + OpOffset)); // soffset
8348  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(7 + OpOffset)); // imm offset
8349  unsigned Aux = Op.getConstantOperandVal(8 + OpOffset);
8350  Ops.push_back(
8351  DAG.getTargetConstant(Aux & AMDGPU::CPol::ALL, DL, MVT::i8)); // cpol
8352  Ops.push_back(
8353  DAG.getTargetConstant((Aux >> 3) & 1, DL, MVT::i8)); // swz
8354  Ops.push_back(M0Val.getValue(0)); // Chain
8355  Ops.push_back(M0Val.getValue(1)); // Glue
8356 
8357  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8358  MachineMemOperand *LoadMMO = M->getMemOperand();
8359  MachinePointerInfo LoadPtrI = LoadMMO->getPointerInfo();
8360  LoadPtrI.Offset = Op->getConstantOperandVal(7 + OpOffset);
8361  MachinePointerInfo StorePtrI = LoadPtrI;
8362  StorePtrI.V = nullptr;
8363  StorePtrI.AddrSpace = AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS;
8364 
8365  auto F = LoadMMO->getFlags() &
8366  ~(MachineMemOperand::MOStore | MachineMemOperand::MOLoad);
8367  LoadMMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(LoadPtrI, F | MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
8368  Size, LoadMMO->getBaseAlign());
8369 
8370  MachineMemOperand *StoreMMO =
8371  MF.getMachineMemOperand(StorePtrI, F | MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
8372  sizeof(int32_t), LoadMMO->getBaseAlign());
8373 
8374  auto Load = DAG.getMachineNode(Opc, DL, M->getVTList(), Ops);
8375  DAG.setNodeMemRefs(Load, {LoadMMO, StoreMMO});
8376 
8377  return SDValue(Load, 0);
8378  }
8379  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_global_load_lds: {
8380  unsigned Opc;
8381  unsigned Size = Op->getConstantOperandVal(4);
8382  switch (Size) {
8383  default:
8384  return SDValue();
8385  case 1:
8386  Opc = AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_LDS_UBYTE;
8387  break;
8388  case 2:
8389  Opc = AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_LDS_USHORT;
8390  break;
8391  case 4:
8392  Opc = AMDGPU::GLOBAL_LOAD_LDS_DWORD;
8393  break;
8394  }
8395 
8396  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Op);
8397  SDValue M0Val = copyToM0(DAG, Chain, DL, Op.getOperand(3));
8398 
8399  SmallVector<SDValue, 6> Ops;
8400 
8401  SDValue Addr = Op.getOperand(2); // Global ptr
8402  SDValue VOffset;
8403  // Try to split SAddr and VOffset. Global and LDS pointers share the same
8404  // immediate offset, so we cannot use a regular SelectGlobalSAddr().
8405  if (Addr->isDivergent() && Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
8406  SDValue LHS = Addr.getOperand(0);
8407  SDValue RHS = Addr.getOperand(1);
8408 
8409  if (LHS->isDivergent())
8410  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
8411 
8412  if (!LHS->isDivergent() && RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND &&
8413  RHS.getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::i32) {
8414  // add (i64 sgpr), (zero_extend (i32 vgpr))
8415  Addr = LHS;
8416  VOffset = RHS.getOperand(0);
8417  }
8418  }
8419 
8420  Ops.push_back(Addr);
8421  if (!Addr->isDivergent()) {
8422  Opc = AMDGPU::getGlobalSaddrOp(Opc);
8423  if (!VOffset)
8424  VOffset = SDValue(
8425  DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32, DL, MVT::i32,
8426  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32)), 0);
8427  Ops.push_back(VOffset);
8428  }
8429 
8430  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(5)); // Offset
8431  Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(6)); // CPol
8432  Ops.push_back(M0Val.getValue(0)); // Chain
8433  Ops.push_back(M0Val.getValue(1)); // Glue
8434 
8435  MachineMemOperand *LoadMMO = M->getMemOperand();
8436  MachinePointerInfo LoadPtrI = LoadMMO->getPointerInfo();
8437  LoadPtrI.Offset = Op->getConstantOperandVal(5);
8438  MachinePointerInfo StorePtrI = LoadPtrI;
8439  LoadPtrI.AddrSpace = AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS;
8440  StorePtrI.AddrSpace = AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS;
8441  auto F = LoadMMO->getFlags() &
8442  ~(MachineMemOperand::MOStore | MachineMemOperand::MOLoad);
8443  LoadMMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(LoadPtrI, F | MachineMemOperand::MOLoad,
8444  Size, LoadMMO->getBaseAlign());
8445  MachineMemOperand *StoreMMO =
8446  MF.getMachineMemOperand(StorePtrI, F | MachineMemOperand::MOStore,
8447  sizeof(int32_t), Align(4));
8448 
8449  auto Load = DAG.getMachineNode(Opc, DL, Op->getVTList(), Ops);
8450  DAG.setNodeMemRefs(Load, {LoadMMO, StoreMMO});
8451 
8452  return SDValue(Load, 0);
8453  }
8454  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_end_cf:
8455  return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::SI_END_CF, DL, MVT::Other,
8456  Op->getOperand(2), Chain), 0);
8457 
8458  default: {
8459  if (const AMDGPU::ImageDimIntrinsicInfo *ImageDimIntr =
8460  AMDGPU::getImageDimIntrinsicInfo(IntrinsicID))
8461  return lowerImage(Op, ImageDimIntr, DAG, true);
8462 
8463  return Op;
8464  }
8465  }
8466 }
8467 
8468 SDValue SITargetLowering::makeV_ILLEGAL(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG & DAG) const {
8469  // Create the V_ILLEGAL node.
8470  SDLoc DL(Op);
8471  auto Opcode = Subtarget->getGeneration() < AMDGPUSubtarget::GFX10 ?
8472  AMDGPU::V_ILLEGAL_gfx6_gfx7_gfx8_gfx9 : AMDGPU::V_ILLEGAL;
8473  auto EntryNode = DAG.getEntryNode();
8474  auto IllegalNode = DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, DL, MVT::Other, EntryNode);
8475  auto IllegalVal = SDValue(IllegalNode, 0u);
8476 
8477  // Add the V_ILLEGAL node to the root chain to prevent its removal.
8478  auto Chains = SmallVector<SDValue, 2u>();
8479  Chains.push_back(IllegalVal);
8480  Chains.push_back(DAG.getRoot());
8481  auto Root = DAG.getTokenFactor(SDLoc(Chains.back()), Chains);
8482  DAG.setRoot(Root);
8483 
8484  // Merge with UNDEF to satisfy return value requirements.
8485  auto UndefVal = DAG.getUNDEF(Op.getValueType());
8486  return DAG.getMergeValues({UndefVal, IllegalVal}, DL);
8487 }
8488 
8489 // The raw.(t)buffer and struct.(t)buffer intrinsics have two offset args:
8490 // offset (the offset that is included in bounds checking and swizzling, to be
8491 // split between the instruction's voffset and immoffset fields) and soffset
8492 // (the offset that is excluded from bounds checking and swizzling, to go in
8493 // the instruction's soffset field). This function takes the first kind of
8494 // offset and figures out how to split it between voffset and immoffset.
8495 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> SITargetLowering::splitBufferOffsets(
8496  SDValue Offset, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8497  SDLoc DL(Offset);
8498  const unsigned MaxImm = 4095;
8499  SDValue N0 = Offset;
8500  ConstantSDNode *C1 = nullptr;
8501 
8502  if ((C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0)))
8503  N0 = SDValue();
8504  else if (DAG.isBaseWithConstantOffset(N0)) {
8505  C1 = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1));
8506  N0 = N0.getOperand(0);
8507  }
8508 
8509  if (C1) {
8510  unsigned ImmOffset = C1->getZExtValue();
8511  // If the immediate value is too big for the immoffset field, put the value
8512  // and -4096 into the immoffset field so that the value that is copied/added
8513  // for the voffset field is a multiple of 4096, and it stands more chance
8514  // of being CSEd with the copy/add for another similar load/store.
8515  // However, do not do that rounding down to a multiple of 4096 if that is a
8516  // negative number, as it appears to be illegal to have a negative offset
8517  // in the vgpr, even if adding the immediate offset makes it positive.
8518  unsigned Overflow = ImmOffset & ~MaxImm;
8519  ImmOffset -= Overflow;
8520  if ((int32_t)Overflow < 0) {
8521  Overflow += ImmOffset;
8522  ImmOffset = 0;
8523  }
8524  C1 = cast<ConstantSDNode>(DAG.getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, DL, MVT::i32));
8525  if (Overflow) {
8526  auto OverflowVal = DAG.getConstant(Overflow, DL, MVT::i32);
8527  if (!N0)
8528  N0 = OverflowVal;
8529  else {
8530  SDValue Ops[] = { N0, OverflowVal };
8531  N0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, DL, MVT::i32, Ops);
8532  }
8533  }
8534  }
8535  if (!N0)
8536  N0 = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
8537  if (!C1)
8538  C1 = cast<ConstantSDNode>(DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
8539  return {N0, SDValue(C1, 0)};
8540 }
8541 
8542 // Analyze a combined offset from an amdgcn_buffer_ intrinsic and store the
8543 // three offsets (voffset, soffset and instoffset) into the SDValue[3] array
8544 // pointed to by Offsets.
8545 void SITargetLowering::setBufferOffsets(SDValue CombinedOffset,
8546  SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue *Offsets,
8547  Align Alignment) const {
8548  SDLoc DL(CombinedOffset);
8549  if (auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(CombinedOffset)) {
8550  uint32_t Imm = C->getZExtValue();
8551  uint32_t SOffset, ImmOffset;
8552  if (AMDGPU::splitMUBUFOffset(Imm, SOffset, ImmOffset, Subtarget,
8553  Alignment)) {
8554  Offsets[0] = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
8555  Offsets[1] = DAG.getConstant(SOffset, DL, MVT::i32);
8556  Offsets[2] = DAG.getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, DL, MVT::i32);
8557  return;
8558  }
8559  }
8560  if (DAG.isBaseWithConstantOffset(CombinedOffset)) {
8561  SDValue N0 = CombinedOffset.getOperand(0);
8562  SDValue N1 = CombinedOffset.getOperand(1);
8563  uint32_t SOffset, ImmOffset;
8564  int Offset = cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1)->getSExtValue();
8565  if (Offset >= 0 && AMDGPU::splitMUBUFOffset(Offset, SOffset, ImmOffset,
8566  Subtarget, Alignment)) {
8567  Offsets[0] = N0;
8568  Offsets[1] = DAG.getConstant(SOffset, DL, MVT::i32);
8569  Offsets[2] = DAG.getTargetConstant(ImmOffset, DL, MVT::i32);
8570  return;
8571  }
8572  }
8573  Offsets[0] = CombinedOffset;
8574  Offsets[1] = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
8575  Offsets[2] = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
8576 }
8577 
8578 // Handle 8 bit and 16 bit buffer loads
8579 SDValue SITargetLowering::handleByteShortBufferLoads(SelectionDAG &DAG,
8580  EVT LoadVT, SDLoc DL,
8581  ArrayRef<SDValue> Ops,
8582  MemSDNode *M) const {
8583  EVT IntVT = LoadVT.changeTypeToInteger();
8584  unsigned Opc = (LoadVT.getScalarType() == MVT::i8) ?
8585  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT;
8586 
8587  SDVTList ResList = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::Other);
8588  SDValue BufferLoad = DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, ResList,
8589  Ops, IntVT,
8590  M->getMemOperand());
8591  SDValue LoadVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, IntVT, BufferLoad);
8592  LoadVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, LoadVT, LoadVal);
8593 
8594  return DAG.getMergeValues({LoadVal, BufferLoad.getValue(1)}, DL);
8595 }
8596 
8597 // Handle 8 bit and 16 bit buffer stores
8598 SDValue SITargetLowering::handleByteShortBufferStores(SelectionDAG &DAG,
8599  EVT VDataType, SDLoc DL,
8600  SDValue Ops[],
8601  MemSDNode *M) const {
8602  if (VDataType == MVT::f16)
8603  Ops[1] = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::i16, Ops[1]);
8604 
8605  SDValue BufferStoreExt = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, DL, MVT::i32, Ops[1]);
8606  Ops[1] = BufferStoreExt;
8607  unsigned Opc = (VDataType == MVT::i8) ? AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_BYTE :
8608  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_STORE_SHORT;
8609  ArrayRef<SDValue> OpsRef = ArrayRef(&Ops[0], 9);
8610  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, DL, M->getVTList(), OpsRef, VDataType,
8611  M->getMemOperand());
8612 }
8613 
8614 static SDValue getLoadExtOrTrunc(SelectionDAG &DAG,
8615  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType, SDValue Op,
8616  const SDLoc &SL, EVT VT) {
8617  if (VT.bitsLT(Op.getValueType()))
8618  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VT, Op);
8619 
8620  switch (ExtType) {
8621  case ISD::SEXTLOAD:
8622  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, SL, VT, Op);
8623  case ISD::ZEXTLOAD:
8624  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, SL, VT, Op);
8625  case ISD::EXTLOAD:
8626  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, VT, Op);
8627  case ISD::NON_EXTLOAD:
8628  return Op;
8629  }
8630 
8631  llvm_unreachable("invalid ext type");
8632 }
8633 
8634 SDValue SITargetLowering::widenLoad(LoadSDNode *Ld, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
8635  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
8636  if (Ld->getAlign() < Align(4) || Ld->isDivergent())
8637  return SDValue();
8638 
8639  // FIXME: Constant loads should all be marked invariant.
8640  unsigned AS = Ld->getAddressSpace();
8641  if (AS != AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS &&
8642  AS != AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT &&
8643  (AS != AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS || !Ld->isInvariant()))
8644  return SDValue();
8645 
8646  // Don't do this early, since it may interfere with adjacent load merging for
8647  // illegal types. We can avoid losing alignment information for exotic types
8648  // pre-legalize.
8649  EVT MemVT = Ld->getMemoryVT();
8650  if ((MemVT.isSimple() && !DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG()) ||
8651  MemVT.getSizeInBits() >= 32)
8652  return SDValue();
8653 
8654  SDLoc SL(Ld);
8655 
8656  assert((!MemVT.isVector() || Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) &&
8657  "unexpected vector extload");
8658 
8659  // TODO: Drop only high part of range.
8660  SDValue Ptr = Ld->getBasePtr();
8661  SDValue NewLoad = DAG.getLoad(
8662  ISD::UNINDEXED, ISD::NON_EXTLOAD, MVT::i32, SL, Ld->getChain(), Ptr,
8663  Ld->getOffset(), Ld->getPointerInfo(), MVT::i32, Ld->getAlign(),
8664  Ld->getMemOperand()->getFlags(), Ld->getAAInfo(),
8665  nullptr); // Drop ranges
8666 
8667  EVT TruncVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), MemVT.getSizeInBits());
8668  if (MemVT.isFloatingPoint()) {
8669  assert(Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD &&
8670  "unexpected fp extload");
8671  TruncVT = MemVT.changeTypeToInteger();
8672  }
8673 
8674  SDValue Cvt = NewLoad;
8675  if (Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::SEXTLOAD) {
8676  Cvt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG, SL, MVT::i32, NewLoad,
8677  DAG.getValueType(TruncVT));
8678  } else if (Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::ZEXTLOAD ||
8679  Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD) {
8680  Cvt = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(NewLoad, SL, TruncVT);
8681  } else {
8682  assert(Ld->getExtensionType() == ISD::EXTLOAD);
8683  }
8684 
8685  EVT VT = Ld->getValueType(0);
8686  EVT IntVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), VT.getSizeInBits());
8687 
8688  DCI.AddToWorklist(Cvt.getNode());
8689 
8690  // We may need to handle exotic cases, such as i16->i64 extloads, so insert
8691  // the appropriate extension from the 32-bit load.
8692  Cvt = getLoadExtOrTrunc(DAG, Ld->getExtensionType(), Cvt, SL, IntVT);
8693  DCI.AddToWorklist(Cvt.getNode());
8694 
8695  // Handle conversion back to floating point if necessary.
8696  Cvt = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Cvt);
8697 
8698  return DAG.getMergeValues({ Cvt, NewLoad.getValue(1) }, SL);
8699 }
8700 
8701 static bool addressMayBeAccessedAsPrivate(const MachineMemOperand *MMO,
8702  const SIMachineFunctionInfo &Info) {
8703  // TODO: Should check if the address can definitely not access stack.
8704  if (Info.isEntryFunction())
8705  return Info.hasFlatScratchInit();
8706  return true;
8707 }
8708 
8709 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerLOAD(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8710  SDLoc DL(Op);
8711  LoadSDNode *Load = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op);
8712  ISD::LoadExtType ExtType = Load->getExtensionType();
8713  EVT MemVT = Load->getMemoryVT();
8714 
8715  if (ExtType == ISD::NON_EXTLOAD && MemVT.getSizeInBits() < 32) {
8716  if (MemVT == MVT::i16 && isTypeLegal(MVT::i16))
8717  return SDValue();
8718 
8719  // FIXME: Copied from PPC
8720  // First, load into 32 bits, then truncate to 1 bit.
8721 
8722  SDValue Chain = Load->getChain();
8723  SDValue BasePtr = Load->getBasePtr();
8724  MachineMemOperand *MMO = Load->getMemOperand();
8725 
8726  EVT RealMemVT = (MemVT == MVT::i1) ? MVT::i8 : MVT::i16;
8727 
8728  SDValue NewLD = DAG.getExtLoad(ISD::EXTLOAD, DL, MVT::i32, Chain,
8729  BasePtr, RealMemVT, MMO);
8730 
8731  if (!MemVT.isVector()) {
8732  SDValue Ops[] = {
8733  DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MemVT, NewLD),
8734  NewLD.getValue(1)
8735  };
8736 
8737  return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
8738  }
8739 
8740  SmallVector<SDValue, 3> Elts;
8741  for (unsigned I = 0, N = MemVT.getVectorNumElements(); I != N; ++I) {
8742  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, DL, MVT::i32, NewLD,
8743  DAG.getConstant(I, DL, MVT::i32));
8744 
8745  Elts.push_back(DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::i1, Elt));
8746  }
8747 
8748  SDValue Ops[] = {
8749  DAG.getBuildVector(MemVT, DL, Elts),
8750  NewLD.getValue(1)
8751  };
8752 
8753  return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
8754  }
8755 
8756  if (!MemVT.isVector())
8757  return SDValue();
8758 
8759  assert(Op.getValueType().getVectorElementType() == MVT::i32 &&
8760  "Custom lowering for non-i32 vectors hasn't been implemented.");
8761 
8762  Align Alignment = Load->getAlign();
8763  unsigned AS = Load->getAddressSpace();
8764  if (Subtarget->hasLDSMisalignedBug() && AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS &&
8765  Alignment.value() < MemVT.getStoreSize() && MemVT.getSizeInBits() > 32) {
8766  return SplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8767  }
8768 
8769  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
8770  SIMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
8771  // If there is a possibility that flat instruction access scratch memory
8772  // then we need to use the same legalization rules we use for private.
8773  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS &&
8774  !Subtarget->hasMultiDwordFlatScratchAddressing())
8775  AS = addressMayBeAccessedAsPrivate(Load->getMemOperand(), *MFI) ?
8776  AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS : AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS;
8777 
8778  unsigned NumElements = MemVT.getVectorNumElements();
8779 
8780  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS ||
8781  AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT) {
8782  if (!Op->isDivergent() && Alignment >= Align(4) && NumElements < 32) {
8783  if (MemVT.isPow2VectorType())
8784  return SDValue();
8785  return WidenOrSplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8786  }
8787  // Non-uniform loads will be selected to MUBUF instructions, so they
8788  // have the same legalization requirements as global and private
8789  // loads.
8790  //
8791  }
8792 
8793  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS ||
8794  AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT ||
8795  AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS) {
8796  if (Subtarget->getScalarizeGlobalBehavior() && !Op->isDivergent() &&
8797  Load->isSimple() && isMemOpHasNoClobberedMemOperand(Load) &&
8798  Alignment >= Align(4) && NumElements < 32) {
8799  if (MemVT.isPow2VectorType())
8800  return SDValue();
8801  return WidenOrSplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8802  }
8803  // Non-uniform loads will be selected to MUBUF instructions, so they
8804  // have the same legalization requirements as global and private
8805  // loads.
8806  //
8807  }
8808  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS ||
8809  AS == AMDGPUAS::CONSTANT_ADDRESS_32BIT ||
8810  AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS ||
8811  AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) {
8812  if (NumElements > 4)
8813  return SplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8814  // v3 loads not supported on SI.
8815  if (NumElements == 3 && !Subtarget->hasDwordx3LoadStores())
8816  return WidenOrSplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8817 
8818  // v3 and v4 loads are supported for private and global memory.
8819  return SDValue();
8820  }
8821  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) {
8822  // Depending on the setting of the private_element_size field in the
8823  // resource descriptor, we can only make private accesses up to a certain
8824  // size.
8825  switch (Subtarget->getMaxPrivateElementSize()) {
8826  case 4: {
8827  SDValue Ops[2];
8828  std::tie(Ops[0], Ops[1]) = scalarizeVectorLoad(Load, DAG);
8829  return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
8830  }
8831  case 8:
8832  if (NumElements > 2)
8833  return SplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8834  return SDValue();
8835  case 16:
8836  // Same as global/flat
8837  if (NumElements > 4)
8838  return SplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8839  // v3 loads not supported on SI.
8840  if (NumElements == 3 && !Subtarget->hasDwordx3LoadStores())
8841  return WidenOrSplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8842 
8843  return SDValue();
8844  default:
8845  llvm_unreachable("unsupported private_element_size");
8846  }
8847  } else if (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS || AS == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS) {
8848  unsigned Fast = 0;
8849  auto Flags = Load->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
8850  if (allowsMisalignedMemoryAccessesImpl(MemVT.getSizeInBits(), AS,
8851  Load->getAlign(), Flags, &Fast) &&
8852  Fast > 1)
8853  return SDValue();
8854 
8855  if (MemVT.isVector())
8856  return SplitVectorLoad(Op, DAG);
8857  }
8858 
8859  if (!allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
8860  MemVT, *Load->getMemOperand())) {
8861  SDValue Ops[2];
8862  std::tie(Ops[0], Ops[1]) = expandUnalignedLoad(Load, DAG);
8863  return DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, DL);
8864  }
8865 
8866  return SDValue();
8867 }
8868 
8869 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8870  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
8871  if (VT.getSizeInBits() == 128 || VT.getSizeInBits() == 256)
8872  return splitTernaryVectorOp(Op, DAG);
8873 
8874  assert(VT.getSizeInBits() == 64);
8875 
8876  SDLoc DL(Op);
8877  SDValue Cond = Op.getOperand(0);
8878 
8879  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
8880  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, DL, MVT::i32);
8881 
8882  SDValue LHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::v2i32, Op.getOperand(1));
8883  SDValue RHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, MVT::v2i32, Op.getOperand(2));
8884 
8885  SDValue Lo0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, LHS, Zero);
8886  SDValue Lo1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, RHS, Zero);
8887 
8888  SDValue Lo = DAG.getSelect(DL, MVT::i32, Cond, Lo0, Lo1);
8889 
8890  SDValue Hi0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, LHS, One);
8891  SDValue Hi1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, DL, MVT::i32, RHS, One);
8892 
8893  SDValue Hi = DAG.getSelect(DL, MVT::i32, Cond, Hi0, Hi1);
8894 
8895  SDValue Res = DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i32, DL, {Lo, Hi});
8896  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, DL, VT, Res);
8897 }
8898 
8899 // Catch division cases where we can use shortcuts with rcp and rsq
8900 // instructions.
8901 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerFastUnsafeFDIV(SDValue Op,
8902  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8903  SDLoc SL(Op);
8904  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
8905  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
8906  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
8907  const SDNodeFlags Flags = Op->getFlags();
8908 
8909  bool AllowInaccurateRcp = Flags.hasApproximateFuncs();
8910 
8911  // Without !fpmath accuracy information, we can't do more because we don't
8912  // know exactly whether rcp is accurate enough to meet !fpmath requirement.
8913  if (!AllowInaccurateRcp)
8914  return SDValue();
8915 
8916  if (const ConstantFPSDNode *CLHS = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(LHS)) {
8917  if (CLHS->isExactlyValue(1.0)) {
8918  // v_rcp_f32 and v_rsq_f32 do not support denormals, and according to
8919  // the CI documentation has a worst case error of 1 ulp.
8920  // OpenCL requires <= 2.5 ulp for 1.0 / x, so it should always be OK to
8921  // use it as long as we aren't trying to use denormals.
8922  //
8923  // v_rcp_f16 and v_rsq_f16 DO support denormals.
8924 
8925  // 1.0 / sqrt(x) -> rsq(x)
8926 
8927  // XXX - Is UnsafeFPMath sufficient to do this for f64? The maximum ULP
8928  // error seems really high at 2^29 ULP.
8929  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FSQRT)
8930  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RSQ, SL, VT, RHS.getOperand(0));
8931 
8932  // 1.0 / x -> rcp(x)
8933  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, VT, RHS);
8934  }
8935 
8936  // Same as for 1.0, but expand the sign out of the constant.
8937  if (CLHS->isExactlyValue(-1.0)) {
8938  // -1.0 / x -> rcp (fneg x)
8939  SDValue FNegRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, VT, RHS);
8940  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, VT, FNegRHS);
8941  }
8942  }
8943 
8944  // Turn into multiply by the reciprocal.
8945  // x / y -> x * (1.0 / y)
8946  SDValue Recip = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, VT, RHS);
8947  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, VT, LHS, Recip, Flags);
8948 }
8949 
8950 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerFastUnsafeFDIV64(SDValue Op,
8951  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
8952  SDLoc SL(Op);
8953  SDValue X = Op.getOperand(0);
8954  SDValue Y = Op.getOperand(1);
8955  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
8956  const SDNodeFlags Flags = Op->getFlags();
8957 
8958  bool AllowInaccurateDiv = Flags.hasApproximateFuncs() ||
8959  DAG.getTarget().Options.UnsafeFPMath;
8960  if (!AllowInaccurateDiv)
8961  return SDValue();
8962 
8963  SDValue NegY = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, VT, Y);
8964  SDValue One = DAG.getConstantFP(1.0, SL, VT);
8965 
8966  SDValue R = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, VT, Y);
8967  SDValue Tmp0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, NegY, R, One);
8968 
8969  R = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, Tmp0, R, R);
8970  SDValue Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, NegY, R, One);
8971  R = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, Tmp1, R, R);
8972  SDValue Ret = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, VT, X, R);
8973  SDValue Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, NegY, Ret, X);
8974  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, VT, Tmp2, R, Ret);
8975 }
8976 
8977 static SDValue getFPBinOp(SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &SL,
8978  EVT VT, SDValue A, SDValue B, SDValue GlueChain,
8979  SDNodeFlags Flags) {
8980  if (GlueChain->getNumValues() <= 1) {
8981  return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SL, VT, A, B, Flags);
8982  }
8983 
8984  assert(GlueChain->getNumValues() == 3);
8985 
8986  SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
8987  switch (Opcode) {
8988  default: llvm_unreachable("no chain equivalent for opcode");
8989  case ISD::FMUL:
8990  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::FMUL_W_CHAIN;
8991  break;
8992  }
8993 
8994  return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SL, VTList,
8995  {GlueChain.getValue(1), A, B, GlueChain.getValue(2)},
8996  Flags);
8997 }
8998 
8999 static SDValue getFPTernOp(SelectionDAG &DAG, unsigned Opcode, const SDLoc &SL,
9000  EVT VT, SDValue A, SDValue B, SDValue C,
9001  SDValue GlueChain, SDNodeFlags Flags) {
9002  if (GlueChain->getNumValues() <= 1) {
9003  return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SL, VT, {A, B, C}, Flags);
9004  }
9005 
9006  assert(GlueChain->getNumValues() == 3);
9007 
9008  SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(VT, MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
9009  switch (Opcode) {
9010  default: llvm_unreachable("no chain equivalent for opcode");
9011  case ISD::FMA:
9012  Opcode = AMDGPUISD::FMA_W_CHAIN;
9013  break;
9014  }
9015 
9016  return DAG.getNode(Opcode, SL, VTList,
9017  {GlueChain.getValue(1), A, B, C, GlueChain.getValue(2)},
9018  Flags);
9019 }
9020 
9021 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerFDIV16(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9022  if (SDValue FastLowered = lowerFastUnsafeFDIV(Op, DAG))
9023  return FastLowered;
9024 
9025  SDLoc SL(Op);
9026  SDValue Src0 = Op.getOperand(0);
9027  SDValue Src1 = Op.getOperand(1);
9028 
9029  SDValue CvtSrc0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, SL, MVT::f32, Src0);
9030  SDValue CvtSrc1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_EXTEND, SL, MVT::f32, Src1);
9031 
9032  SDValue RcpSrc1 = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, MVT::f32, CvtSrc1);
9033  SDValue Quot = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f32, CvtSrc0, RcpSrc1);
9034 
9035  SDValue FPRoundFlag = DAG.getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32);
9036  SDValue BestQuot = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, SL, MVT::f16, Quot, FPRoundFlag);
9037 
9038  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP, SL, MVT::f16, BestQuot, Src1, Src0);
9039 }
9040 
9041 // Faster 2.5 ULP division that does not support denormals.
9042 SDValue SITargetLowering::lowerFDIV_FAST(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9043  SDLoc SL(Op);
9044  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(1);
9045  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(2);
9046 
9047  SDValue r1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FABS, SL, MVT::f32, RHS);
9048 
9049  const APFloat K0Val(llvm::bit_cast<float>(0x6f800000));
9050  const SDValue K0 = DAG.getConstantFP(K0Val, SL, MVT::f32);
9051 
9052  const APFloat K1Val(llvm::bit_cast<float>(0x2f800000));
9053  const SDValue K1 = DAG.getConstantFP(K1Val, SL, MVT::f32);
9054 
9055  const SDValue One = DAG.getConstantFP(1.0, SL, MVT::f32);
9056 
9057  EVT SetCCVT =
9058  getSetCCResultType(DAG.getDataLayout(), *DAG.getContext(), MVT::f32);
9059 
9060  SDValue r2 = DAG.getSetCC(SL, SetCCVT, r1, K0, ISD::SETOGT);
9061 
9062  SDValue r3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SELECT, SL, MVT::f32, r2, K1, One);
9063 
9064  // TODO: Should this propagate fast-math-flags?
9065  r1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f32, RHS, r3);
9066 
9067  // rcp does not support denormals.
9068  SDValue r0 = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, MVT::f32, r1);
9069 
9070  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f32, LHS, r0);
9071 
9072  return DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f32, r3, Mul);
9073 }
9074 
9075 // Returns immediate value for setting the F32 denorm mode when using the
9076 // S_DENORM_MODE instruction.
9077 static SDValue getSPDenormModeValue(int SPDenormMode, SelectionDAG &DAG,
9078  const SDLoc &SL, const GCNSubtarget *ST) {
9079  assert(ST->hasDenormModeInst() && "Requires S_DENORM_MODE");
9080  int DPDenormModeDefault = hasFP64FP16Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction())
9081  ? FP_DENORM_FLUSH_NONE
9082  : FP_DENORM_FLUSH_IN_FLUSH_OUT;
9083 
9084  int Mode = SPDenormMode | (DPDenormModeDefault << 2);
9085  return DAG.getTargetConstant(Mode, SL, MVT::i32);
9086 }
9087 
9088 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerFDIV32(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9089  if (SDValue FastLowered = lowerFastUnsafeFDIV(Op, DAG))
9090  return FastLowered;
9091 
9092  // The selection matcher assumes anything with a chain selecting to a
9093  // mayRaiseFPException machine instruction. Since we're introducing a chain
9094  // here, we need to explicitly report nofpexcept for the regular fdiv
9095  // lowering.
9096  SDNodeFlags Flags = Op->getFlags();
9097  Flags.setNoFPExcept(true);
9098 
9099  SDLoc SL(Op);
9100  SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
9101  SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
9102 
9103  const SDValue One = DAG.getConstantFP(1.0, SL, MVT::f32);
9104 
9105  SDVTList ScaleVT = DAG.getVTList(MVT::f32, MVT::i1);
9106 
9107  SDValue DenominatorScaled = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE, SL, ScaleVT,
9108  {RHS, RHS, LHS}, Flags);
9109  SDValue NumeratorScaled = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE, SL, ScaleVT,
9110  {LHS, RHS, LHS}, Flags);
9111 
9112  // Denominator is scaled to not be denormal, so using rcp is ok.
9113  SDValue ApproxRcp = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, MVT::f32,
9114  DenominatorScaled, Flags);
9115  SDValue NegDivScale0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, MVT::f32,
9116  DenominatorScaled, Flags);
9117 
9118  const unsigned Denorm32Reg = AMDGPU::Hwreg::ID_MODE |
9119  (4 << AMDGPU::Hwreg::OFFSET_SHIFT_) |
9120  (1 << AMDGPU::Hwreg::WIDTH_M1_SHIFT_);
9121  const SDValue BitField = DAG.getTargetConstant(Denorm32Reg, SL, MVT::i32);
9122 
9123  const bool HasFP32Denormals = hasFP32Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction());
9124 
9125  if (!HasFP32Denormals) {
9126  // Note we can't use the STRICT_FMA/STRICT_FMUL for the non-strict FDIV
9127  // lowering. The chain dependence is insufficient, and we need glue. We do
9128  // not need the glue variants in a strictfp function.
9129 
9130  SDVTList BindParamVTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
9131 
9132  SDNode *EnableDenorm;
9133  if (Subtarget->hasDenormModeInst()) {
9134  const SDValue EnableDenormValue =
9135  getSPDenormModeValue(FP_DENORM_FLUSH_NONE, DAG, SL, Subtarget);
9136 
9137  EnableDenorm = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DENORM_MODE, SL, BindParamVTs,
9138  DAG.getEntryNode(), EnableDenormValue).getNode();
9139  } else {
9140  const SDValue EnableDenormValue = DAG.getConstant(FP_DENORM_FLUSH_NONE,
9141  SL, MVT::i32);
9142  EnableDenorm =
9143  DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_SETREG_B32, SL, BindParamVTs,
9144  {EnableDenormValue, BitField, DAG.getEntryNode()});
9145  }
9146 
9147  SDValue Ops[3] = {
9148  NegDivScale0,
9149  SDValue(EnableDenorm, 0),
9150  SDValue(EnableDenorm, 1)
9151  };
9152 
9153  NegDivScale0 = DAG.getMergeValues(Ops, SL);
9154  }
9155 
9156  SDValue Fma0 = getFPTernOp(DAG, ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f32, NegDivScale0,
9157  ApproxRcp, One, NegDivScale0, Flags);
9158 
9159  SDValue Fma1 = getFPTernOp(DAG, ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f32, Fma0, ApproxRcp,
9160  ApproxRcp, Fma0, Flags);
9161 
9162  SDValue Mul = getFPBinOp(DAG, ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f32, NumeratorScaled,
9163  Fma1, Fma1, Flags);
9164 
9165  SDValue Fma2 = getFPTernOp(DAG, ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f32, NegDivScale0, Mul,
9166  NumeratorScaled, Mul, Flags);
9167 
9168  SDValue Fma3 = getFPTernOp(DAG, ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f32,
9169  Fma2, Fma1, Mul, Fma2, Flags);
9170 
9171  SDValue Fma4 = getFPTernOp(DAG, ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f32, NegDivScale0, Fma3,
9172  NumeratorScaled, Fma3, Flags);
9173 
9174  if (!HasFP32Denormals) {
9175  SDNode *DisableDenorm;
9176  if (Subtarget->hasDenormModeInst()) {
9177  const SDValue DisableDenormValue =
9178  getSPDenormModeValue(FP_DENORM_FLUSH_IN_FLUSH_OUT, DAG, SL, Subtarget);
9179 
9180  DisableDenorm = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DENORM_MODE, SL, MVT::Other,
9181  Fma4.getValue(1), DisableDenormValue,
9182  Fma4.getValue(2)).getNode();
9183  } else {
9184  const SDValue DisableDenormValue =
9185  DAG.getConstant(FP_DENORM_FLUSH_IN_FLUSH_OUT, SL, MVT::i32);
9186 
9187  DisableDenorm = DAG.getMachineNode(
9188  AMDGPU::S_SETREG_B32, SL, MVT::Other,
9189  {DisableDenormValue, BitField, Fma4.getValue(1), Fma4.getValue(2)});
9190  }
9191 
9192  SDValue OutputChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, SL, MVT::Other,
9193  SDValue(DisableDenorm, 0), DAG.getRoot());
9194  DAG.setRoot(OutputChain);
9195  }
9196 
9197  SDValue Scale = NumeratorScaled.getValue(1);
9198  SDValue Fmas = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FMAS, SL, MVT::f32,
9199  {Fma4, Fma1, Fma3, Scale}, Flags);
9200 
9201  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP, SL, MVT::f32, Fmas, RHS, LHS, Flags);
9202 }
9203 
9204 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerFDIV64(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9205  if (SDValue FastLowered = lowerFastUnsafeFDIV64(Op, DAG))
9206  return FastLowered;
9207 
9208  SDLoc SL(Op);
9209  SDValue X = Op.getOperand(0);
9210  SDValue Y = Op.getOperand(1);
9211 
9212  const SDValue One = DAG.getConstantFP(1.0, SL, MVT::f64);
9213 
9214  SDVTList ScaleVT = DAG.getVTList(MVT::f64, MVT::i1);
9215 
9216  SDValue DivScale0 = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE, SL, ScaleVT, Y, Y, X);
9217 
9218  SDValue NegDivScale0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, MVT::f64, DivScale0);
9219 
9220  SDValue Rcp = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP, SL, MVT::f64, DivScale0);
9221 
9222  SDValue Fma0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f64, NegDivScale0, Rcp, One);
9223 
9224  SDValue Fma1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f64, Rcp, Fma0, Rcp);
9225 
9226  SDValue Fma2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f64, NegDivScale0, Fma1, One);
9227 
9228  SDValue DivScale1 = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE, SL, ScaleVT, X, Y, X);
9229 
9230  SDValue Fma3 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f64, Fma1, Fma2, Fma1);
9231  SDValue Mul = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, SL, MVT::f64, DivScale1, Fma3);
9232 
9233  SDValue Fma4 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMA, SL, MVT::f64,
9234  NegDivScale0, Mul, DivScale1);
9235 
9236  SDValue Scale;
9237 
9238  if (!Subtarget->hasUsableDivScaleConditionOutput()) {
9239  // Workaround a hardware bug on SI where the condition output from div_scale
9240  // is not usable.
9241 
9242  const SDValue Hi = DAG.getConstant(1, SL, MVT::i32);
9243 
9244  // Figure out if the scale to use for div_fmas.
9245  SDValue NumBC = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i32, X);
9246  SDValue DenBC = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i32, Y);
9247  SDValue Scale0BC = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i32, DivScale0);
9248  SDValue Scale1BC = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::v2i32, DivScale1);
9249 
9250  SDValue NumHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, NumBC, Hi);
9251  SDValue DenHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, DenBC, Hi);
9252 
9253  SDValue Scale0Hi
9254  = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, Scale0BC, Hi);
9255  SDValue Scale1Hi
9256  = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, Scale1BC, Hi);
9257 
9258  SDValue CmpDen = DAG.getSetCC(SL, MVT::i1, DenHi, Scale0Hi, ISD::SETEQ);
9259  SDValue CmpNum = DAG.getSetCC(SL, MVT::i1, NumHi, Scale1Hi, ISD::SETEQ);
9260  Scale = DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, SL, MVT::i1, CmpNum, CmpDen);
9261  } else {
9262  Scale = DivScale1.getValue(1);
9263  }
9264 
9265  SDValue Fmas = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FMAS, SL, MVT::f64,
9266  Fma4, Fma3, Mul, Scale);
9267 
9268  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP, SL, MVT::f64, Fmas, Y, X);
9269 }
9270 
9271 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerFDIV(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9272  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
9273 
9274  if (VT == MVT::f32)
9275  return LowerFDIV32(Op, DAG);
9276 
9277  if (VT == MVT::f64)
9278  return LowerFDIV64(Op, DAG);
9279 
9280  if (VT == MVT::f16)
9281  return LowerFDIV16(Op, DAG);
9282 
9283  llvm_unreachable("Unexpected type for fdiv");
9284 }
9285 
9286 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerSTORE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9287  SDLoc DL(Op);
9288  StoreSDNode *Store = cast<StoreSDNode>(Op);
9289  EVT VT = Store->getMemoryVT();
9290 
9291  if (VT == MVT::i1) {
9292  return DAG.getTruncStore(Store->getChain(), DL,
9293  DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(Store->getValue(), DL, MVT::i32),
9294  Store->getBasePtr(), MVT::i1, Store->getMemOperand());
9295  }
9296 
9297  assert(VT.isVector() &&
9298  Store->getValue().getValueType().getScalarType() == MVT::i32);
9299 
9300  unsigned AS = Store->getAddressSpace();
9301  if (Subtarget->hasLDSMisalignedBug() &&
9302  AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS &&
9303  Store->getAlign().value() < VT.getStoreSize() && VT.getSizeInBits() > 32) {
9304  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9305  }
9306 
9307  MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
9308  SIMachineFunctionInfo *MFI = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
9309  // If there is a possibility that flat instruction access scratch memory
9310  // then we need to use the same legalization rules we use for private.
9311  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS &&
9312  !Subtarget->hasMultiDwordFlatScratchAddressing())
9313  AS = addressMayBeAccessedAsPrivate(Store->getMemOperand(), *MFI) ?
9314  AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS : AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS;
9315 
9316  unsigned NumElements = VT.getVectorNumElements();
9317  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS ||
9318  AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS) {
9319  if (NumElements > 4)
9320  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9321  // v3 stores not supported on SI.
9322  if (NumElements == 3 && !Subtarget->hasDwordx3LoadStores())
9323  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9324 
9325  if (!allowsMemoryAccessForAlignment(*DAG.getContext(), DAG.getDataLayout(),
9326  VT, *Store->getMemOperand()))
9327  return expandUnalignedStore(Store, DAG);
9328 
9329  return SDValue();
9330  } else if (AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS) {
9331  switch (Subtarget->getMaxPrivateElementSize()) {
9332  case 4:
9333  return scalarizeVectorStore(Store, DAG);
9334  case 8:
9335  if (NumElements > 2)
9336  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9337  return SDValue();
9338  case 16:
9339  if (NumElements > 4 ||
9340  (NumElements == 3 && !Subtarget->enableFlatScratch()))
9341  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9342  return SDValue();
9343  default:
9344  llvm_unreachable("unsupported private_element_size");
9345  }
9346  } else if (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS || AS == AMDGPUAS::REGION_ADDRESS) {
9347  unsigned Fast = 0;
9348  auto Flags = Store->getMemOperand()->getFlags();
9349  if (allowsMisalignedMemoryAccessesImpl(VT.getSizeInBits(), AS,
9350  Store->getAlign(), Flags, &Fast) &&
9351  Fast > 1)
9352  return SDValue();
9353 
9354  if (VT.isVector())
9355  return SplitVectorStore(Op, DAG);
9356 
9357  return expandUnalignedStore(Store, DAG);
9358  }
9359 
9360  // Probably an invalid store. If so we'll end up emitting a selection error.
9361  return SDValue();
9362 }
9363 
9364 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerTrig(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9365  SDLoc DL(Op);
9366  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
9367  SDValue Arg = Op.getOperand(0);
9368  SDValue TrigVal;
9369 
9370  // Propagate fast-math flags so that the multiply we introduce can be folded
9371  // if Arg is already the result of a multiply by constant.
9372  auto Flags = Op->getFlags();
9373 
9374  SDValue OneOver2Pi = DAG.getConstantFP(0.5 * numbers::inv_pi, DL, VT);
9375 
9376  if (Subtarget->hasTrigReducedRange()) {
9377  SDValue MulVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, DL, VT, Arg, OneOver2Pi, Flags);
9378  TrigVal = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FRACT, DL, VT, MulVal, Flags);
9379  } else {
9380  TrigVal = DAG.getNode(ISD::FMUL, DL, VT, Arg, OneOver2Pi, Flags);
9381  }
9382 
9383  switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
9384  case ISD::FCOS:
9385  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::COS_HW, SDLoc(Op), VT, TrigVal, Flags);
9386  case ISD::FSIN:
9387  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::SIN_HW, SDLoc(Op), VT, TrigVal, Flags);
9388  default:
9389  llvm_unreachable("Wrong trig opcode");
9390  }
9391 }
9392 
9393 SDValue SITargetLowering::LowerATOMIC_CMP_SWAP(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
9394  AtomicSDNode *AtomicNode = cast<AtomicSDNode>(Op);
9395  assert(AtomicNode->isCompareAndSwap());
9396  unsigned AS = AtomicNode->getAddressSpace();
9397 
9398  // No custom lowering required for local address space
9399  if (!AMDGPU::isFlatGlobalAddrSpace(AS))
9400  return Op;
9401 
9402  // Non-local address space requires custom lowering for atomic compare
9403  // and swap; cmp and swap should be in a v2i32 or v2i64 in case of _X2
9404  SDLoc DL(Op);
9405  SDValue ChainIn = Op.getOperand(0);
9406  SDValue Addr = Op.getOperand(1);
9407  SDValue Old = Op.getOperand(2);
9408  SDValue New = Op.getOperand(3);
9409  EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
9410  MVT SimpleVT = VT.getSimpleVT();
9411  MVT VecType = MVT::getVectorVT(SimpleVT, 2);
9412 
9413  SDValue NewOld = DAG.getBuildVector(VecType, DL, {New, Old});
9414  SDValue Ops[] = { ChainIn, Addr, NewOld };
9415 
9416  return DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP, DL, Op->getVTList(),
9417  Ops, VT, AtomicNode->getMemOperand());
9418 }

9420 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9421 // Custom DAG optimizations
9422 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
9423 
9424 SDValue SITargetLowering::performUCharToFloatCombine(SDNode *N,
9425  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9426  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9427  EVT ScalarVT = VT.getScalarType();
9428  if (ScalarVT != MVT::f32 && ScalarVT != MVT::f16)
9429  return SDValue();
9430 
9431  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9432  SDLoc DL(N);
9433 
9434  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
9435  EVT SrcVT = Src.getValueType();
9436 
9437  // TODO: We could try to match extracting the higher bytes, which would be
9438  // easier if i8 vectors weren't promoted to i32 vectors, particularly after
9439  // types are legalized. v4i8 -> v4f32 is probably the only case to worry
9440  // about in practice.
9441  if (DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG() && SrcVT == MVT::i32) {
9442  if (DAG.MaskedValueIsZero(Src, APInt::getHighBitsSet(32, 24))) {
9443  SDValue Cvt = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0, DL, MVT::f32, Src);
9444  DCI.AddToWorklist(Cvt.getNode());
9445 
9446  // For the f16 case, fold to a cast to f32 and then cast back to f16.
9447  if (ScalarVT != MVT::f32) {
9448  Cvt = DAG.getNode(ISD::FP_ROUND, DL, VT, Cvt,
9449  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32));
9450  }
9451  return Cvt;
9452  }
9453  }
9454 
9455  return SDValue();
9456 }
9457 
9458 // (shl (add x, c1), c2) -> add (shl x, c2), (shl c1, c2)
9459 
9460 // This is a variant of
9461 // (mul (add x, c1), c2) -> add (mul x, c2), (mul c1, c2),
9462 //
9463 // The normal DAG combiner will do this, but only if the add has one use since
9464 // that would increase the number of instructions.
9465 //
9466 // This prevents us from seeing a constant offset that can be folded into a
9467 // memory instruction's addressing mode. If we know the resulting add offset of
9468 // a pointer can be folded into an addressing offset, we can replace the pointer
9469 // operand with the add of new constant offset. This eliminates one of the uses,
9470 // and may allow the remaining use to also be simplified.
9471 //
9472 SDValue SITargetLowering::performSHLPtrCombine(SDNode *N,
9473  unsigned AddrSpace,
9474  EVT MemVT,
9475  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9476  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
9477  SDValue N1 = N->getOperand(1);
9478 
9479  // We only do this to handle cases where it's profitable when there are
9480  // multiple uses of the add, so defer to the standard combine.
9481  if ((N0.getOpcode() != ISD::ADD && N0.getOpcode() != ISD::OR) ||
9482  N0->hasOneUse())
9483  return SDValue();
9484 
9485  const ConstantSDNode *CN1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N1);
9486  if (!CN1)
9487  return SDValue();
9488 
9489  const ConstantSDNode *CAdd = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1));
9490  if (!CAdd)
9491  return SDValue();
9492 
9493  // If the resulting offset is too large, we can't fold it into the addressing
9494  // mode offset.
9495  APInt Offset = CAdd->getAPIntValue() << CN1->getAPIntValue();
9496  Type *Ty = MemVT.getTypeForEVT(*DCI.DAG.getContext());
9497 
9498  AddrMode AM;
9499  AM.HasBaseReg = true;
9500  AM.BaseOffs = Offset.getSExtValue();
9501  if (!isLegalAddressingMode(DCI.DAG.getDataLayout(), AM, Ty, AddrSpace))
9502  return SDValue();
9503 
9504  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9505  SDLoc SL(N);
9506  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9507 
9508  SDValue ShlX = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SL, VT, N0.getOperand(0), N1);
9509  SDValue COffset = DAG.getConstant(Offset, SL, VT);
9510 
9511  SDNodeFlags Flags;
9512  Flags.setNoUnsignedWrap(N->getFlags().hasNoUnsignedWrap() &&
9513  (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::OR ||
9514  N0->getFlags().hasNoUnsignedWrap()));
9515 
9516  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, SL, VT, ShlX, COffset, Flags);
9517 }
9518 
9519 /// MemSDNode::getBasePtr() does not work for intrinsics, which needs to offset
9520 /// by the chain and intrinsic ID. Theoretically we would also need to check the
9521 /// specific intrinsic, but they all place the pointer operand first.
9522 static unsigned getBasePtrIndex(const MemSDNode *N) {
9523  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
9524  case ISD::STORE:
9525  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
9526  case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID:
9527  return 2;
9528  default:
9529  return 1;
9530  }
9531 }
9532 
9533 SDValue SITargetLowering::performMemSDNodeCombine(MemSDNode *N,
9534  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9535  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9536  SDLoc SL(N);
9537 
9538  unsigned PtrIdx = getBasePtrIndex(N);
9539  SDValue Ptr = N->getOperand(PtrIdx);
9540 
9541  // TODO: We could also do this for multiplies.
9542  if (Ptr.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
9543  SDValue NewPtr = performSHLPtrCombine(Ptr.getNode(), N->getAddressSpace(),
9544  N->getMemoryVT(), DCI);
9545  if (NewPtr) {
9546  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> NewOps(N->op_begin(), N->op_end());
9547 
9548  NewOps[PtrIdx] = NewPtr;
9549  return SDValue(DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(N, NewOps), 0);
9550  }
9551  }
9552 
9553  return SDValue();
9554 }
9555 
9556 static bool bitOpWithConstantIsReducible(unsigned Opc, uint32_t Val) {
9557  return (Opc == ISD::AND && (Val == 0 || Val == 0xffffffff)) ||
9558  (Opc == ISD::OR && (Val == 0xffffffff || Val == 0)) ||
9559  (Opc == ISD::XOR && Val == 0);
9560 }
9561 
9562 // Break up 64-bit bit operation of a constant into two 32-bit and/or/xor. This
9563 // will typically happen anyway for a VALU 64-bit and. This exposes other 32-bit
9564 // integer combine opportunities since most 64-bit operations are decomposed
9565 // this way. TODO: We won't want this for SALU especially if it is an inline
9566 // immediate.
9567 SDValue SITargetLowering::splitBinaryBitConstantOp(
9568  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI,
9569  const SDLoc &SL,
9570  unsigned Opc, SDValue LHS,
9571  const ConstantSDNode *CRHS) const {
9572  uint64_t Val = CRHS->getZExtValue();
9573  uint32_t ValLo = Lo_32(Val);
9574  uint32_t ValHi = Hi_32(Val);
9575  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9576 
9577  if ((bitOpWithConstantIsReducible(Opc, ValLo) ||
9578  bitOpWithConstantIsReducible(Opc, ValHi)) ||
9579  (CRHS->hasOneUse() && !TII->isInlineConstant(CRHS->getAPIntValue()))) {
9580  // If we need to materialize a 64-bit immediate, it will be split up later
9581  // anyway. Avoid creating the harder to understand 64-bit immediate
9582  // materialization.
9583  return splitBinaryBitConstantOpImpl(DCI, SL, Opc, LHS, ValLo, ValHi);
9584  }
9585 
9586  return SDValue();
9587 }
