9588 
9589 // Returns true if argument is a boolean value which is not serialized into
9590 // memory or argument and does not require v_cndmask_b32 to be deserialized.
9591 static bool isBoolSGPR(SDValue V) {
9592  if (V.getValueType() != MVT::i1)
9593  return false;
9594  switch (V.getOpcode()) {
9595  default:
9596  break;
9597  case ISD::SETCC:
9598  case AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS:
9599  return true;
9600  case ISD::AND:
9601  case ISD::OR:
9602  case ISD::XOR:
9603  return isBoolSGPR(V.getOperand(0)) && isBoolSGPR(V.getOperand(1));
9604  }
9605  return false;
9606 }
9607 
9608 // If a constant has all zeroes or all ones within each byte return it.
9609 // Otherwise return 0.
9610 static uint32_t getConstantPermuteMask(uint32_t C) {
9611  // 0xff for any zero byte in the mask
9612  uint32_t ZeroByteMask = 0;
9613  if (!(C & 0x000000ff)) ZeroByteMask |= 0x000000ff;
9614  if (!(C & 0x0000ff00)) ZeroByteMask |= 0x0000ff00;
9615  if (!(C & 0x00ff0000)) ZeroByteMask |= 0x00ff0000;
9616  if (!(C & 0xff000000)) ZeroByteMask |= 0xff000000;
9617  uint32_t NonZeroByteMask = ~ZeroByteMask; // 0xff for any non-zero byte
9618  if ((NonZeroByteMask & C) != NonZeroByteMask)
9619  return 0; // Partial bytes selected.
9620  return C;
9621 }
9622 
9623 // Check if a node selects whole bytes from its operand 0 starting at a byte
9624 // boundary while masking the rest. Returns select mask as in the v_perm_b32
9625 // or -1 if not succeeded.
9626 // Note byte select encoding:
9627 // value 0-3 selects corresponding source byte;
9628 // value 0xc selects zero;
9629 // value 0xff selects 0xff.
9630 static uint32_t getPermuteMask(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue V) {
9631  assert(V.getValueSizeInBits() == 32);
9632 
9633  if (V.getNumOperands() != 2)
9634  return ~0;
9635 
9636  ConstantSDNode *N1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getOperand(1));
9637  if (!N1)
9638  return ~0;
9639 
9640  uint32_t C = N1->getZExtValue();
9641 
9642  switch (V.getOpcode()) {
9643  default:
9644  break;
9645  case ISD::AND:
9646  if (uint32_t ConstMask = getConstantPermuteMask(C)) {
9647  return (0x03020100 & ConstMask) | (0x0c0c0c0c & ~ConstMask);
9648  }
9649  break;
9650 
9651  case ISD::OR:
9652  if (uint32_t ConstMask = getConstantPermuteMask(C)) {
9653  return (0x03020100 & ~ConstMask) | ConstMask;
9654  }
9655  break;
9656 
9657  case ISD::SHL:
9658  if (C % 8)
9659  return ~0;
9660 
9661  return uint32_t((0x030201000c0c0c0cull << C) >> 32);
9662 
9663  case ISD::SRL:
9664  if (C % 8)
9665  return ~0;
9666 
9667  return uint32_t(0x0c0c0c0c03020100ull >> C);
9668  }
9669 
9670  return ~0;
9671 }
9672 
9673 SDValue SITargetLowering::performAndCombine(SDNode *N,
9674  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9675  if (DCI.isBeforeLegalize())
9676  return SDValue();
9677 
9678  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9679  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9680  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
9681  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
9682 
9683 
9684  const ConstantSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
9685  if (VT == MVT::i64 && CRHS) {
9686  if (SDValue Split
9687  = splitBinaryBitConstantOp(DCI, SDLoc(N), ISD::AND, LHS, CRHS))
9688  return Split;
9689  }
9690 
9691  if (CRHS && VT == MVT::i32) {
9692  // and (srl x, c), mask => shl (bfe x, nb + c, mask >> nb), nb
9693  // nb = number of trailing zeroes in mask
9694  // It can be optimized out using SDWA for GFX8+ in the SDWA peephole pass,
9695  // given that we are selecting 8 or 16 bit fields starting at byte boundary.
9696  uint64_t Mask = CRHS->getZExtValue();
9697  unsigned Bits = llvm::popcount(Mask);
9698  if (getSubtarget()->hasSDWA() && LHS->getOpcode() == ISD::SRL &&
9699  (Bits == 8 || Bits == 16) && isShiftedMask_64(Mask) && !(Mask & 1)) {
9700  if (auto *CShift = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS->getOperand(1))) {
9701  unsigned Shift = CShift->getZExtValue();
9702  unsigned NB = CRHS->getAPIntValue().countTrailingZeros();
9703  unsigned Offset = NB + Shift;
9704  if ((Offset & (Bits - 1)) == 0) { // Starts at a byte or word boundary.
9705  SDLoc SL(N);
9706  SDValue BFE = DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::BFE_U32, SL, MVT::i32,
9707  LHS->getOperand(0),
9708  DAG.getConstant(Offset, SL, MVT::i32),
9709  DAG.getConstant(Bits, SL, MVT::i32));
9710  EVT NarrowVT = EVT::getIntegerVT(*DAG.getContext(), Bits);
9711  SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::AssertZext, SL, VT, BFE,
9712  DAG.getValueType(NarrowVT));
9713  SDValue Shl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, SDLoc(LHS), VT, Ext,
9714  DAG.getConstant(NB, SDLoc(CRHS), MVT::i32));
9715  return Shl;
9716  }
9717  }
9718  }
9719 
9720  // and (perm x, y, c1), c2 -> perm x, y, permute_mask(c1, c2)
9721  if (LHS.hasOneUse() && LHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::PERM &&
9722  isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))) {
9723  uint32_t Sel = getConstantPermuteMask(Mask);
9724  if (!Sel)
9725  return SDValue();
9726 
9727  // Select 0xc for all zero bytes
9728  Sel = (LHS.getConstantOperandVal(2) & Sel) | (~Sel & 0x0c0c0c0c);
9729  SDLoc DL(N);
9730  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PERM, DL, MVT::i32, LHS.getOperand(0),
9731  LHS.getOperand(1), DAG.getConstant(Sel, DL, MVT::i32));
9732  }
9733  }
9734 
9735  // (and (fcmp ord x, x), (fcmp une (fabs x), inf)) ->
9736  // fp_class x, ~(s_nan | q_nan | n_infinity | p_infinity)
9737  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC) {
9738  ISD::CondCode LCC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->get();
9739  ISD::CondCode RCC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(RHS.getOperand(2))->get();
9740 
9741  SDValue X = LHS.getOperand(0);
9742  SDValue Y = RHS.getOperand(0);
9743  if (Y.getOpcode() != ISD::FABS || Y.getOperand(0) != X ||
9744  !isTypeLegal(X.getValueType()))
9745  return SDValue();
9746 
9747  if (LCC == ISD::SETO) {
9748  if (X != LHS.getOperand(1))
9749  return SDValue();
9750 
9751  if (RCC == ISD::SETUNE) {
9752  const ConstantFPSDNode *C1 = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(RHS.getOperand(1));
9753  if (!C1 || !C1->isInfinity() || C1->isNegative())
9754  return SDValue();
9755 
9756  const uint32_t Mask = SIInstrFlags::N_NORMAL |
9757  SIInstrFlags::N_SUBNORMAL |
9758  SIInstrFlags::N_ZERO |
9759  SIInstrFlags::P_ZERO |
9760  SIInstrFlags::P_SUBNORMAL |
9761  SIInstrFlags::P_NORMAL;
9762 
9763  static_assert(((~(SIInstrFlags::S_NAN |
9764  SIInstrFlags::Q_NAN |
9765  SIInstrFlags::N_INFINITY |
9766  SIInstrFlags::P_INFINITY)) & 0x3ff) == Mask,
9767  "mask not equal");
9768 
9769  SDLoc DL(N);
9770  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, DL, MVT::i1,
9771  X, DAG.getConstant(Mask, DL, MVT::i32));
9772  }
9773  }
9774  }
9775 
9776  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && LHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS)
9777  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9778 
9779  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SETCC && RHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS &&
9780  RHS.hasOneUse()) {
9781  ISD::CondCode LCC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))->get();
9782  // and (fcmp seto), (fp_class x, mask) -> fp_class x, mask & ~(p_nan | n_nan)
9783  // and (fcmp setuo), (fp_class x, mask) -> fp_class x, mask & (p_nan | n_nan)
9784  const ConstantSDNode *Mask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS.getOperand(1));
9785  if ((LCC == ISD::SETO || LCC == ISD::SETUO) && Mask &&
9786  (RHS.getOperand(0) == LHS.getOperand(0) &&
9787  LHS.getOperand(0) == LHS.getOperand(1))) {
9788  const unsigned OrdMask = SIInstrFlags::S_NAN | SIInstrFlags::Q_NAN;
9789  unsigned NewMask = LCC == ISD::SETO ?
9790  Mask->getZExtValue() & ~OrdMask :
9791  Mask->getZExtValue() & OrdMask;
9792 
9793  SDLoc DL(N);
9794  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, DL, MVT::i1, RHS.getOperand(0),
9795  DAG.getConstant(NewMask, DL, MVT::i32));
9796  }
9797  }
9798 
9799  if (VT == MVT::i32 &&
9800  (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND || LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)) {
9801  // and x, (sext cc from i1) => select cc, x, 0
9802  if (RHS.getOpcode() != ISD::SIGN_EXTEND)
9803  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9804  if (isBoolSGPR(RHS.getOperand(0)))
9805  return DAG.getSelect(SDLoc(N), MVT::i32, RHS.getOperand(0),
9806  LHS, DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(N), MVT::i32));
9807  }
9808 
9809  // and (op x, c1), (op y, c2) -> perm x, y, permute_mask(c1, c2)
9810  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9811  if (VT == MVT::i32 && LHS.hasOneUse() && RHS.hasOneUse() &&
9812  N->isDivergent() && TII->pseudoToMCOpcode(AMDGPU::V_PERM_B32_e64) != -1) {
9813  uint32_t LHSMask = getPermuteMask(DAG, LHS);
9814  uint32_t RHSMask = getPermuteMask(DAG, RHS);
9815  if (LHSMask != ~0u && RHSMask != ~0u) {
9816  // Canonicalize the expression in an attempt to have fewer unique masks
9817  // and therefore fewer registers used to hold the masks.
9818  if (LHSMask > RHSMask) {
9819  std::swap(LHSMask, RHSMask);
9820  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9821  }
9822 
9823  // Select 0xc for each lane used from source operand. Zero has 0xc mask
9824  // set, 0xff have 0xff in the mask, actual lanes are in the 0-3 range.
9825  uint32_t LHSUsedLanes = ~(LHSMask & 0x0c0c0c0c) & 0x0c0c0c0c;
9826  uint32_t RHSUsedLanes = ~(RHSMask & 0x0c0c0c0c) & 0x0c0c0c0c;
9827 
9828  // Check of we need to combine values from two sources within a byte.
9829  if (!(LHSUsedLanes & RHSUsedLanes) &&
9830  // If we select high and lower word keep it for SDWA.
9831  // TODO: teach SDWA to work with v_perm_b32 and remove the check.
9832  !(LHSUsedLanes == 0x0c0c0000 && RHSUsedLanes == 0x00000c0c)) {
9833  // Each byte in each mask is either selector mask 0-3, or has higher
9834  // bits set in either of masks, which can be 0xff for 0xff or 0x0c for
9835  // zero. If 0x0c is in either mask it shall always be 0x0c. Otherwise
9836  // mask which is not 0xff wins. By anding both masks we have a correct
9837  // result except that 0x0c shall be corrected to give 0x0c only.
9838  uint32_t Mask = LHSMask & RHSMask;
9839  for (unsigned I = 0; I < 32; I += 8) {
9840  uint32_t ByteSel = 0xff << I;
9841  if ((LHSMask & ByteSel) == 0x0c || (RHSMask & ByteSel) == 0x0c)
9842  Mask &= (0x0c << I) & 0xffffffff;
9843  }
9844 
9845  // Add 4 to each active LHS lane. It will not affect any existing 0xff
9846  // or 0x0c.
9847  uint32_t Sel = Mask | (LHSUsedLanes & 0x04040404);
9848  SDLoc DL(N);
9849 
9850  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PERM, DL, MVT::i32,
9851  LHS.getOperand(0), RHS.getOperand(0),
9852  DAG.getConstant(Sel, DL, MVT::i32));
9853  }
9854  }
9855  }
9856 
9857  return SDValue();
9858 }
9859 
9860 SDValue SITargetLowering::performOrCombine(SDNode *N,
9861  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9862  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
9863  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
9864  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
9865 
9866  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9867  if (VT == MVT::i1) {
9868  // or (fp_class x, c1), (fp_class x, c2) -> fp_class x, (c1 | c2)
9869  if (LHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS &&
9870  RHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS) {
9871  SDValue Src = LHS.getOperand(0);
9872  if (Src != RHS.getOperand(0))
9873  return SDValue();
9874 
9875  const ConstantSDNode *CLHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1));
9876  const ConstantSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS.getOperand(1));
9877  if (!CLHS || !CRHS)
9878  return SDValue();
9879 
9880  // Only 10 bits are used.
9881  static const uint32_t MaxMask = 0x3ff;
9882 
9883  uint32_t NewMask = (CLHS->getZExtValue() | CRHS->getZExtValue()) & MaxMask;
9884  SDLoc DL(N);
9885  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, DL, MVT::i1,
9886  Src, DAG.getConstant(NewMask, DL, MVT::i32));
9887  }
9888 
9889  return SDValue();
9890  }
9891 
9892  // or (perm x, y, c1), c2 -> perm x, y, permute_mask(c1, c2)
9893  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(RHS) && LHS.hasOneUse() &&
9894  LHS.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::PERM &&
9895  isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2))) {
9896  uint32_t Sel = getConstantPermuteMask(N->getConstantOperandVal(1));
9897  if (!Sel)
9898  return SDValue();
9899 
9900  Sel |= LHS.getConstantOperandVal(2);
9901  SDLoc DL(N);
9902  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PERM, DL, MVT::i32, LHS.getOperand(0),
9903  LHS.getOperand(1), DAG.getConstant(Sel, DL, MVT::i32));
9904  }
9905 
9906  // or (op x, c1), (op y, c2) -> perm x, y, permute_mask(c1, c2)
9907  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
9908  if (VT == MVT::i32 && LHS.hasOneUse() && RHS.hasOneUse() &&
9909  N->isDivergent() && TII->pseudoToMCOpcode(AMDGPU::V_PERM_B32_e64) != -1) {
9910  uint32_t LHSMask = getPermuteMask(DAG, LHS);
9911  uint32_t RHSMask = getPermuteMask(DAG, RHS);
9912  if (LHSMask != ~0u && RHSMask != ~0u) {
9913  // Canonicalize the expression in an attempt to have fewer unique masks
9914  // and therefore fewer registers used to hold the masks.
9915  if (LHSMask > RHSMask) {
9916  std::swap(LHSMask, RHSMask);
9917  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9918  }
9919 
9920  // Select 0xc for each lane used from source operand. Zero has 0xc mask
9921  // set, 0xff have 0xff in the mask, actual lanes are in the 0-3 range.
9922  uint32_t LHSUsedLanes = ~(LHSMask & 0x0c0c0c0c) & 0x0c0c0c0c;
9923  uint32_t RHSUsedLanes = ~(RHSMask & 0x0c0c0c0c) & 0x0c0c0c0c;
9924 
9925  // Check of we need to combine values from two sources within a byte.
9926  if (!(LHSUsedLanes & RHSUsedLanes) &&
9927  // If we select high and lower word keep it for SDWA.
9928  // TODO: teach SDWA to work with v_perm_b32 and remove the check.
9929  !(LHSUsedLanes == 0x0c0c0000 && RHSUsedLanes == 0x00000c0c)) {
9930  // Kill zero bytes selected by other mask. Zero value is 0xc.
9931  LHSMask &= ~RHSUsedLanes;
9932  RHSMask &= ~LHSUsedLanes;
9933  // Add 4 to each active LHS lane
9934  LHSMask |= LHSUsedLanes & 0x04040404;
9935  // Combine masks
9936  uint32_t Sel = LHSMask | RHSMask;
9937  SDLoc DL(N);
9938 
9939  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::PERM, DL, MVT::i32,
9940  LHS.getOperand(0), RHS.getOperand(0),
9941  DAG.getConstant(Sel, DL, MVT::i32));
9942  }
9943  }
9944  }
9945 
9946  if (VT != MVT::i64 || DCI.isBeforeLegalizeOps())
9947  return SDValue();
9948 
9949  // TODO: This could be a generic combine with a predicate for extracting the
9950  // high half of an integer being free.
9951 
9952  // (or i64:x, (zero_extend i32:y)) ->
9953  // i64 (bitcast (v2i32 build_vector (or i32:y, lo_32(x)), hi_32(x)))
9954  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND &&
9955  RHS.getOpcode() != ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
9956  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
9957 
9958  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND) {
9959  SDValue ExtSrc = RHS.getOperand(0);
9960  EVT SrcVT = ExtSrc.getValueType();
9961  if (SrcVT == MVT::i32) {
9962  SDLoc SL(N);
9963  SDValue LowLHS, HiBits;
9964  std::tie(LowLHS, HiBits) = split64BitValue(LHS, DAG);
9965  SDValue LowOr = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, SL, MVT::i32, LowLHS, ExtSrc);
9966 
9967  DCI.AddToWorklist(LowOr.getNode());
9968  DCI.AddToWorklist(HiBits.getNode());
9969 
9970  SDValue Vec = DAG.getNode(ISD::BUILD_VECTOR, SL, MVT::v2i32,
9971  LowOr, HiBits);
9972  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i64, Vec);
9973  }
9974  }
9975 
9976  const ConstantSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
9977  if (CRHS) {
9978  if (SDValue Split
9979  = splitBinaryBitConstantOp(DCI, SDLoc(N), ISD::OR,
9980  N->getOperand(0), CRHS))
9981  return Split;
9982  }
9983 
9984  return SDValue();
9985 }
9986 
9987 SDValue SITargetLowering::performXorCombine(SDNode *N,
9988  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
9989  if (SDValue RV = reassociateScalarOps(N, DCI.DAG))
9990  return RV;
9991 
9992  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
9993  if (VT != MVT::i64)
9994  return SDValue();
9995 
9996  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
9997  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
9998 
9999  const ConstantSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
10000  if (CRHS) {
10001  if (SDValue Split
10002  = splitBinaryBitConstantOp(DCI, SDLoc(N), ISD::XOR, LHS, CRHS))
10003  return Split;
10004  }
10005 
10006  return SDValue();
10007 }
10008 
10009 SDValue SITargetLowering::performZeroExtendCombine(SDNode *N,
10010  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10011  if (!Subtarget->has16BitInsts() ||
10012  DCI.getDAGCombineLevel() < AfterLegalizeDAG)
10013  return SDValue();
10014 
10015  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10016  if (VT != MVT::i32)
10017  return SDValue();
10018 
10019  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
10020  if (Src.getValueType() != MVT::i16)
10021  return SDValue();
10022 
10023  return SDValue();
10024 }
10025 
10026 SDValue SITargetLowering::performSignExtendInRegCombine(SDNode *N,
10027  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI)
10028  const {
10029  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
10030  auto *VTSign = cast<VTSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
10031 
10032  if (((Src.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE &&
10033  VTSign->getVT() == MVT::i8) ||
10034  (Src.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT &&
10035  VTSign->getVT() == MVT::i16)) &&
10036  Src.hasOneUse()) {
10037  auto *M = cast<MemSDNode>(Src);
10038  SDValue Ops[] = {
10039  Src.getOperand(0), // Chain
10040  Src.getOperand(1), // rsrc
10041  Src.getOperand(2), // vindex
10042  Src.getOperand(3), // voffset
10043  Src.getOperand(4), // soffset
10044  Src.getOperand(5), // offset
10045  Src.getOperand(6),
10046  Src.getOperand(7)
10047  };
10048  // replace with BUFFER_LOAD_BYTE/SHORT
10049  SDVTList ResList = DCI.DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32,
10050  Src.getOperand(0).getValueType());
10051  unsigned Opc = (Src.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE) ?
10052  AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_BYTE : AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_LOAD_SHORT;
10053  SDValue BufferLoadSignExt = DCI.DAG.getMemIntrinsicNode(Opc, SDLoc(N),
10054  ResList,
10055  Ops, M->getMemoryVT(),
10056  M->getMemOperand());
10057  return DCI.DAG.getMergeValues({BufferLoadSignExt,
10058  BufferLoadSignExt.getValue(1)}, SDLoc(N));
10059  }
10060  return SDValue();
10061 }
10062 
10063 SDValue SITargetLowering::performClassCombine(SDNode *N,
10064  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10065  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10066  SDValue Mask = N->getOperand(1);
10067 
10068  // fp_class x, 0 -> false
10069  if (const ConstantSDNode *CMask = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Mask)) {
10070  if (CMask->isZero())
10071  return DAG.getConstant(0, SDLoc(N), MVT::i1);
10072  }
10073 
10074  if (N->getOperand(0).isUndef())
10075  return DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i1);
10076 
10077  return SDValue();
10078 }
10079 
10080 SDValue SITargetLowering::performRcpCombine(SDNode *N,
10081  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10082  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10083  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
10084 
10085  if (N0.isUndef()) {
10086  return DCI.DAG.getConstantFP(
10087  APFloat::getQNaN(SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT)), SDLoc(N),
10088  VT);
10089  }
10090 
10091  if (VT == MVT::f32 && (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::UINT_TO_FP ||
10092  N0.getOpcode() == ISD::SINT_TO_FP)) {
10093  return DCI.DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RCP_IFLAG, SDLoc(N), VT, N0,
10094  N->getFlags());
10095  }
10096 
10097  if ((VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f16) && N0.getOpcode() == ISD::FSQRT) {
10098  return DCI.DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::RSQ, SDLoc(N), VT,
10099  N0.getOperand(0), N->getFlags());
10100  }
10101 
10102  return AMDGPUTargetLowering::performRcpCombine(N, DCI);
10103 }
10104 
10105 bool SITargetLowering::isCanonicalized(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Op,
10106  unsigned MaxDepth) const {
10107  unsigned Opcode = Op.getOpcode();
10108  if (Opcode == ISD::FCANONICALIZE)
10109  return true;
10110 
10111  if (auto *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
10112  auto F = CFP->getValueAPF();
10113  if (F.isNaN() && F.isSignaling())
10114  return false;
10115  return !F.isDenormal() || denormalsEnabledForType(DAG, Op.getValueType());
10116  }
10117 
10118  // If source is a result of another standard FP operation it is already in
10119  // canonical form.
10120  if (MaxDepth == 0)
10121  return false;
10122 
10123  switch (Opcode) {
10124  // These will flush denorms if required.
10125  case ISD::FADD:
10126  case ISD::FSUB:
10127  case ISD::FMUL:
10128  case ISD::FCEIL:
10129  case ISD::FFLOOR:
10130  case ISD::FMA:
10131  case ISD::FMAD:
10132  case ISD::FSQRT:
10133  case ISD::FDIV:
10134  case ISD::FREM:
10135  case ISD::FP_ROUND:
10136  case ISD::FP_EXTEND:
10137  case AMDGPUISD::FMUL_LEGACY:
10138  case AMDGPUISD::FMAD_FTZ:
10139  case AMDGPUISD::RCP:
10140  case AMDGPUISD::RSQ:
10141  case AMDGPUISD::RSQ_CLAMP:
10142  case AMDGPUISD::RCP_LEGACY:
10143  case AMDGPUISD::RCP_IFLAG:
10144  case AMDGPUISD::DIV_SCALE:
10145  case AMDGPUISD::DIV_FMAS:
10146  case AMDGPUISD::DIV_FIXUP:
10147  case AMDGPUISD::FRACT:
10148  case AMDGPUISD::LDEXP:
10149  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32:
10150  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0:
10151  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE1:
10152  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE2:
10153  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE3:
10154  return true;
10155 
10156  // It can/will be lowered or combined as a bit operation.
10157  // Need to check their input recursively to handle.
10158  case ISD::FNEG:
10159  case ISD::FABS:
10160  case ISD::FCOPYSIGN:
10161  return isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(0), MaxDepth - 1);
10162 
10163  case ISD::FSIN:
10164  case ISD::FCOS:
10165  case ISD::FSINCOS:
10166  return Op.getValueType().getScalarType() != MVT::f16;
10167 
10168  case ISD::FMINNUM:
10169  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
10170  case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
10171  case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
10172  case AMDGPUISD::CLAMP:
10173  case AMDGPUISD::FMED3:
10174  case AMDGPUISD::FMAX3:
10175  case AMDGPUISD::FMIN3: {
10176  // FIXME: Shouldn't treat the generic operations different based these.
10177  // However, we aren't really required to flush the result from
10178  // minnum/maxnum..
10179 
10180  // snans will be quieted, so we only need to worry about denormals.
10181  if (Subtarget->supportsMinMaxDenormModes() ||
10182  denormalsEnabledForType(DAG, Op.getValueType()))
10183  return true;
10184 
10185  // Flushing may be required.
10186  // In pre-GFX9 targets V_MIN_F32 and others do not flush denorms. For such
10187  // targets need to check their input recursively.
10188 
10189  // FIXME: Does this apply with clamp? It's implemented with max.
10190  for (unsigned I = 0, E = Op.getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
10191  if (!isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(I), MaxDepth - 1))
10192  return false;
10193  }
10194 
10195  return true;
10196  }
10197  case ISD::SELECT: {
10198  return isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(1), MaxDepth - 1) &&
10199  isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(2), MaxDepth - 1);
10200  }
10201  case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: {
10202  for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
10203  SDValue SrcOp = Op.getOperand(i);
10204  if (!isCanonicalized(DAG, SrcOp, MaxDepth - 1))
10205  return false;
10206  }
10207 
10208  return true;
10209  }
10210  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
10211  case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: {
10212  return isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(0), MaxDepth - 1);
10213  }
10214  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: {
10215  return isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(0), MaxDepth - 1) &&
10216  isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(1), MaxDepth - 1);
10217  }
10218  case ISD::UNDEF:
10219  // Could be anything.
10220  return false;
10221 
10222  case ISD::BITCAST:
10223  return isCanonicalized(DAG, Op.getOperand(0), MaxDepth - 1);
10224  case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
10225  // Hack round the mess we make when legalizing extract_vector_elt
10226  if (Op.getValueType() == MVT::i16) {
10227  SDValue TruncSrc = Op.getOperand(0);
10228  if (TruncSrc.getValueType() == MVT::i32 &&
10229  TruncSrc.getOpcode() == ISD::BITCAST &&
10230  TruncSrc.getOperand(0).getValueType() == MVT::v2f16) {
10231  return isCanonicalized(DAG, TruncSrc.getOperand(0), MaxDepth - 1);
10232  }
10233  }
10234  return false;
10235  }
10236  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: {
10237  unsigned IntrinsicID
10238  = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
10239  // TODO: Handle more intrinsics
10240  switch (IntrinsicID) {
10241  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pkrtz:
10242  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubeid:
10243  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_frexp_mant:
10244  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fdot2:
10245  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp:
10246  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq:
10247  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_clamp:
10248  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp_legacy:
10249  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_legacy:
10250  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_trig_preop:
10251  return true;
10252  default:
10253  break;
10254  }
10255 
10256  [[fallthrough]];
10257  }
10258  default:
10259  return denormalsEnabledForType(DAG, Op.getValueType()) &&
10260  DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Op);
10261  }
10262 
10263  llvm_unreachable("invalid operation");
10264 }
10265 
10266 bool SITargetLowering::isCanonicalized(Register Reg, MachineFunction &MF,
10267  unsigned MaxDepth) const {
10268  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
10269  MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(Reg);
10270  unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode();
10271 
10272  if (Opcode == AMDGPU::G_FCANONICALIZE)
10273  return true;
10274 
10275  std::optional<FPValueAndVReg> FCR;
10276  // Constant splat (can be padded with undef) or scalar constant.
10277  if (mi_match(Reg, MRI, MIPatternMatch::m_GFCstOrSplat(FCR))) {
10278  if (FCR->Value.isSignaling())
10279  return false;
10280  return !FCR->Value.isDenormal() ||
10281  denormalsEnabledForType(MRI.getType(FCR->VReg), MF);
10282  }
10283 
10284  if (MaxDepth == 0)
10285  return false;
10286 
10287  switch (Opcode) {
10288  case AMDGPU::G_FADD:
10289  case AMDGPU::G_FSUB:
10290  case AMDGPU::G_FMUL:
10291  case AMDGPU::G_FCEIL:
10292  case AMDGPU::G_FFLOOR:
10293  case AMDGPU::G_FRINT:
10294  case AMDGPU::G_FNEARBYINT:
10295  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC_FPTRUNC_ROUND:
10296  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC_TRUNC:
10297  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC_ROUNDEVEN:
10298  case AMDGPU::G_FMA:
10299  case AMDGPU::G_FMAD:
10300  case AMDGPU::G_FSQRT:
10301  case AMDGPU::G_FDIV:
10302  case AMDGPU::G_FREM:
10303  case AMDGPU::G_FPOW:
10304  case AMDGPU::G_FPEXT:
10305  case AMDGPU::G_FLOG:
10306  case AMDGPU::G_FLOG2:
10307  case AMDGPU::G_FLOG10:
10308  case AMDGPU::G_FPTRUNC:
10309  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_RCP_IFLAG:
10310  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_CVT_F32_UBYTE0:
10311  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_CVT_F32_UBYTE1:
10312  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_CVT_F32_UBYTE2:
10313  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_CVT_F32_UBYTE3:
10314  return true;
10315  case AMDGPU::G_FNEG:
10316  case AMDGPU::G_FABS:
10317  case AMDGPU::G_FCOPYSIGN:
10318  return isCanonicalized(MI->getOperand(1).getReg(), MF, MaxDepth - 1);
10319  case AMDGPU::G_FMINNUM:
10320  case AMDGPU::G_FMAXNUM:
10321  case AMDGPU::G_FMINNUM_IEEE:
10322  case AMDGPU::G_FMAXNUM_IEEE: {
10323  if (Subtarget->supportsMinMaxDenormModes() ||
10324  denormalsEnabledForType(MRI.getType(Reg), MF))
10325  return true;
10326 
10327  [[fallthrough]];
10328  }
10329  case AMDGPU::G_BUILD_VECTOR:
10330  for (const MachineOperand &MO : llvm::drop_begin(MI->operands()))
10331  if (!isCanonicalized(MO.getReg(), MF, MaxDepth - 1))
10332  return false;
10333  return true;
10334  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC:
10335  switch (MI->getIntrinsicID()) {
10336  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmul_legacy:
10337  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmad_ftz:
10338  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sqrt:
10339  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmed3:
10340  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sin:
10341  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cos:
10342  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_log_clamp:
10343  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp:
10344  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rcp_legacy:
10345  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq:
10346  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_clamp:
10347  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_rsq_legacy:
10348  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_scale:
10349  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fmas:
10350  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_div_fixup:
10351  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fract:
10352  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_ldexp:
10353  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cvt_pkrtz:
10354  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubeid:
10355  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubema:
10356  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubesc:
10357  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubetc:
10358  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_frexp_mant:
10359  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fdot2:
10360  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_trig_preop:
10361  return true;
10362  default:
10363  break;
10364  }
10365 
10366  [[fallthrough]];
10367  default:
10368  return false;
10369  }
10370 
10371  llvm_unreachable("invalid operation");
10372 }
10373 
10374 // Constant fold canonicalize.
10375 SDValue SITargetLowering::getCanonicalConstantFP(
10376  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &SL, EVT VT, const APFloat &C) const {
10377  // Flush denormals to 0 if not enabled.
10378  if (C.isDenormal() && !denormalsEnabledForType(DAG, VT)) {
10379  return DAG.getConstantFP(APFloat::getZero(C.getSemantics(),
10380  C.isNegative()), SL, VT);
10381  }
10382 
10383  if (C.isNaN()) {
10384  APFloat CanonicalQNaN = APFloat::getQNaN(C.getSemantics());
10385  if (C.isSignaling()) {
10386  // Quiet a signaling NaN.
10387  // FIXME: Is this supposed to preserve payload bits?
10388  return DAG.getConstantFP(CanonicalQNaN, SL, VT);
10389  }
10390 
10391  // Make sure it is the canonical NaN bitpattern.
10392  //
10393  // TODO: Can we use -1 as the canonical NaN value since it's an inline
10394  // immediate?
10395  if (C.bitcastToAPInt() != CanonicalQNaN.bitcastToAPInt())
10396  return DAG.getConstantFP(CanonicalQNaN, SL, VT);
10397  }
10398 
10399  // Already canonical.
10400  return DAG.getConstantFP(C, SL, VT);
10401 }
10402 
10403 static bool vectorEltWillFoldAway(SDValue Op) {
10404  return Op.isUndef() || isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op);
10405 }
10406 
10407 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFCanonicalizeCombine(
10408  SDNode *N,
10409  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10410  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10411  SDValue N0 = N->getOperand(0);
10412  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10413 
10414  // fcanonicalize undef -> qnan
10415  if (N0.isUndef()) {
10416  APFloat QNaN = APFloat::getQNaN(SelectionDAG::EVTToAPFloatSemantics(VT));
10417  return DAG.getConstantFP(QNaN, SDLoc(N), VT);
10418  }
10419 
10420  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = isConstOrConstSplatFP(N0)) {
10421  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10422  return getCanonicalConstantFP(DAG, SDLoc(N), VT, CFP->getValueAPF());
10423  }
10424 
10425  // fcanonicalize (build_vector x, k) -> build_vector (fcanonicalize x),
10426  // (fcanonicalize k)
10427  //
10428  // fcanonicalize (build_vector x, undef) -> build_vector (fcanonicalize x), 0
10429 
10430  // TODO: This could be better with wider vectors that will be split to v2f16,
10431  // and to consider uses since there aren't that many packed operations.
10432  if (N0.getOpcode() == ISD::BUILD_VECTOR && VT == MVT::v2f16 &&
10433  isTypeLegal(MVT::v2f16)) {
10434  SDLoc SL(N);
10435  SDValue NewElts[2];
10436  SDValue Lo = N0.getOperand(0);
10437  SDValue Hi = N0.getOperand(1);
10438  EVT EltVT = Lo.getValueType();
10439 
10440  if (vectorEltWillFoldAway(Lo) || vectorEltWillFoldAway(Hi)) {
10441  for (unsigned I = 0; I != 2; ++I) {
10442  SDValue Op = N0.getOperand(I);
10443  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
10444  NewElts[I] = getCanonicalConstantFP(DAG, SL, EltVT,
10445  CFP->getValueAPF());
10446  } else if (Op.isUndef()) {
10447  // Handled below based on what the other operand is.
10448  NewElts[I] = Op;
10449  } else {
10450  NewElts[I] = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, SL, EltVT, Op);
10451  }
10452  }
10453 
10454  // If one half is undef, and one is constant, prefer a splat vector rather
10455  // than the normal qNaN. If it's a register, prefer 0.0 since that's
10456  // cheaper to use and may be free with a packed operation.
10457  if (NewElts[0].isUndef()) {
10458  if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(NewElts[1]))
10459  NewElts[0] = isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(NewElts[1]) ?
10460  NewElts[1]: DAG.getConstantFP(0.0f, SL, EltVT);
10461  }
10462 
10463  if (NewElts[1].isUndef()) {
10464  NewElts[1] = isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(NewElts[0]) ?
10465  NewElts[0] : DAG.getConstantFP(0.0f, SL, EltVT);
10466  }
10467 
10468  return DAG.getBuildVector(VT, SL, NewElts);
10469  }
10470  }
10471 
10472  unsigned SrcOpc = N0.getOpcode();
10473 
10474  // If it's free to do so, push canonicalizes further up the source, which may
10475  // find a canonical source.
10476  //
10477  // TODO: More opcodes. Note this is unsafe for the _ieee minnum/maxnum for
10478  // sNaNs.
10479  if (SrcOpc == ISD::FMINNUM || SrcOpc == ISD::FMAXNUM) {
10480  auto *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N0.getOperand(1));
10481  if (CRHS && N0.hasOneUse()) {
10482  SDLoc SL(N);
10483  SDValue Canon0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::FCANONICALIZE, SL, VT,
10484  N0.getOperand(0));
10485  SDValue Canon1 = getCanonicalConstantFP(DAG, SL, VT, CRHS->getValueAPF());
10486  DCI.AddToWorklist(Canon0.getNode());
10487 
10488  return DAG.getNode(N0.getOpcode(), SL, VT, Canon0, Canon1);
10489  }
10490  }
10491 
10492  return isCanonicalized(DAG, N0) ? N0 : SDValue();
10493 }
10494 
10495 static unsigned minMaxOpcToMin3Max3Opc(unsigned Opc) {
10496  switch (Opc) {
10497  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
10498  case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
10499  return AMDGPUISD::FMAX3;
10500  case ISD::SMAX:
10501  return AMDGPUISD::SMAX3;
10502  case ISD::UMAX:
10503  return AMDGPUISD::UMAX3;
10504  case ISD::FMINNUM:
10505  case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
10506  return AMDGPUISD::FMIN3;
10507  case ISD::SMIN:
10508  return AMDGPUISD::SMIN3;
10509  case ISD::UMIN:
10510  return AMDGPUISD::UMIN3;
10511  default:
10512  llvm_unreachable("Not a min/max opcode");
10513  }
10514 }
10515 
10516 SDValue SITargetLowering::performIntMed3ImmCombine(
10517  SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &SL,
10518  SDValue Op0, SDValue Op1, bool Signed) const {
10519  ConstantSDNode *K1 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op1);
10520  if (!K1)
10521  return SDValue();
10522 
10523  ConstantSDNode *K0 = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op0.getOperand(1));
10524  if (!K0)
10525  return SDValue();
10526 
10527  if (Signed) {
10528  if (K0->getAPIntValue().sge(K1->getAPIntValue()))
10529  return SDValue();
10530  } else {
10531  if (K0->getAPIntValue().uge(K1->getAPIntValue()))
10532  return SDValue();
10533  }
10534 
10535  EVT VT = K0->getValueType(0);
10536  unsigned Med3Opc = Signed ? AMDGPUISD::SMED3 : AMDGPUISD::UMED3;
10537  if (VT == MVT::i32 || (VT == MVT::i16 && Subtarget->hasMed3_16())) {
10538  return DAG.getNode(Med3Opc, SL, VT,
10539  Op0.getOperand(0), SDValue(K0, 0), SDValue(K1, 0));
10540  }
10541 
10542  // If there isn't a 16-bit med3 operation, convert to 32-bit.
10543  if (VT == MVT::i16) {
10544  MVT NVT = MVT::i32;
10545  unsigned ExtOp = Signed ? ISD::SIGN_EXTEND : ISD::ZERO_EXTEND;
10546 
10547  SDValue Tmp1 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, SL, NVT, Op0->getOperand(0));
10548  SDValue Tmp2 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, SL, NVT, Op0->getOperand(1));
10549  SDValue Tmp3 = DAG.getNode(ExtOp, SL, NVT, Op1);
10550 
10551  SDValue Med3 = DAG.getNode(Med3Opc, SL, NVT, Tmp1, Tmp2, Tmp3);
10552  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VT, Med3);
10553  }
10554 
10555  return SDValue();
10556 }
10557 
10558 static ConstantFPSDNode *getSplatConstantFP(SDValue Op) {
10559  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op))
10560  return C;
10561 
10562  if (BuildVectorSDNode *BV = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op)) {
10563  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = BV->getConstantFPSplatNode())
10564  return C;
10565  }
10566 
10567  return nullptr;
10568 }
10569 
10570 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFPMed3ImmCombine(SelectionDAG &DAG,
10571  const SDLoc &SL,
10572  SDValue Op0,
10573  SDValue Op1) const {
10574  ConstantFPSDNode *K1 = getSplatConstantFP(Op1);
10575  if (!K1)
10576  return SDValue();
10577 
10578  ConstantFPSDNode *K0 = getSplatConstantFP(Op0.getOperand(1));
10579  if (!K0)
10580  return SDValue();
10581 
10582  // Ordered >= (although NaN inputs should have folded away by now).
10583  if (K0->getValueAPF() > K1->getValueAPF())
10584  return SDValue();
10585 
10586  const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
10587  const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
10588 
10589  // TODO: Check IEEE bit enabled?
10590  EVT VT = Op0.getValueType();
10591  if (Info->getMode().DX10Clamp) {
10592  // If dx10_clamp is enabled, NaNs clamp to 0.0. This is the same as the
10593  // hardware fmed3 behavior converting to a min.
10594  // FIXME: Should this be allowing -0.0?
10595  if (K1->isExactlyValue(1.0) && K0->isExactlyValue(0.0))
10596  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CLAMP, SL, VT, Op0.getOperand(0));
10597  }
10598 
10599  // med3 for f16 is only available on gfx9+, and not available for v2f16.
10600  if (VT == MVT::f32 || (VT == MVT::f16 && Subtarget->hasMed3_16())) {
10601  // This isn't safe with signaling NaNs because in IEEE mode, min/max on a
10602  // signaling NaN gives a quiet NaN. The quiet NaN input to the min would
10603  // then give the other result, which is different from med3 with a NaN
10604  // input.
10605  SDValue Var = Op0.getOperand(0);
10606  if (!DAG.isKnownNeverSNaN(Var))
10607  return SDValue();
10608 
10609  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
10610 
10611  if ((!K0->hasOneUse() ||
10612  TII->isInlineConstant(K0->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt())) &&
10613  (!K1->hasOneUse() ||
10614  TII->isInlineConstant(K1->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt()))) {
10615  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FMED3, SL, K0->getValueType(0),
10616  Var, SDValue(K0, 0), SDValue(K1, 0));
10617  }
10618  }
10619 
10620  return SDValue();
10621 }
10622 
10623 SDValue SITargetLowering::performMinMaxCombine(SDNode *N,
10624  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10625  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10626 
10627  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10628  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
10629  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
10630  SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
10631 
10632  // Only do this if the inner op has one use since this will just increases
10633  // register pressure for no benefit.
10634 
10635  if (Opc != AMDGPUISD::FMIN_LEGACY && Opc != AMDGPUISD::FMAX_LEGACY &&
10636  !VT.isVector() &&
10637  (VT == MVT::i32 || VT == MVT::f32 ||
10638  ((VT == MVT::f16 || VT == MVT::i16) && Subtarget->hasMin3Max3_16()))) {
10639  // max(max(a, b), c) -> max3(a, b, c)
10640  // min(min(a, b), c) -> min3(a, b, c)
10641  if (Op0.getOpcode() == Opc && Op0.hasOneUse()) {
10642  SDLoc DL(N);
10643  return DAG.getNode(minMaxOpcToMin3Max3Opc(Opc),
10644  DL,
10645  N->getValueType(0),
10646  Op0.getOperand(0),
10647  Op0.getOperand(1),
10648  Op1);
10649  }
10650 
10651  // Try commuted.
10652  // max(a, max(b, c)) -> max3(a, b, c)
10653  // min(a, min(b, c)) -> min3(a, b, c)
10654  if (Op1.getOpcode() == Opc && Op1.hasOneUse()) {
10655  SDLoc DL(N);
10656  return DAG.getNode(minMaxOpcToMin3Max3Opc(Opc),
10657  DL,
10658  N->getValueType(0),
10659  Op0,
10660  Op1.getOperand(0),
10661  Op1.getOperand(1));
10662  }
10663  }
10664 
10665  // min(max(x, K0), K1), K0 < K1 -> med3(x, K0, K1)
10666  if (Opc == ISD::SMIN && Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::SMAX && Op0.hasOneUse()) {
10667  if (SDValue Med3 = performIntMed3ImmCombine(DAG, SDLoc(N), Op0, Op1, true))
10668  return Med3;
10669  }
10670 
10671  if (Opc == ISD::UMIN && Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::UMAX && Op0.hasOneUse()) {
10672  if (SDValue Med3 = performIntMed3ImmCombine(DAG, SDLoc(N), Op0, Op1, false))
10673  return Med3;
10674  }
10675 
10676  // fminnum(fmaxnum(x, K0), K1), K0 < K1 && !is_snan(x) -> fmed3(x, K0, K1)
10677  if (((Opc == ISD::FMINNUM && Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FMAXNUM) ||
10678  (Opc == ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE && Op0.getOpcode() == ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE) ||
10679  (Opc == AMDGPUISD::FMIN_LEGACY &&
10680  Op0.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::FMAX_LEGACY)) &&
10681  (VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64 ||
10682  (VT == MVT::f16 && Subtarget->has16BitInsts()) ||
10683  (VT == MVT::v2f16 && Subtarget->hasVOP3PInsts())) &&
10684  Op0.hasOneUse()) {
10685  if (SDValue Res = performFPMed3ImmCombine(DAG, SDLoc(N), Op0, Op1))
10686  return Res;
10687  }
10688 
10689  return SDValue();
10690 }
10691 
10692 static bool isClampZeroToOne(SDValue A, SDValue B) {
10693  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CA = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(A)) {
10694  if (ConstantFPSDNode *CB = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(B)) {
10695  // FIXME: Should this be allowing -0.0?
10696  return (CA->isExactlyValue(0.0) && CB->isExactlyValue(1.0)) ||
10697  (CA->isExactlyValue(1.0) && CB->isExactlyValue(0.0));
10698  }
10699  }
10700 
10701  return false;
10702 }
10703 
10704 // FIXME: Should only worry about snans for version with chain.
10705 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFMed3Combine(SDNode *N,
10706  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10707  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10708  // v_med3_f32 and v_max_f32 behave identically wrt denorms, exceptions and
10709  // NaNs. With a NaN input, the order of the operands may change the result.
10710 
10711  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10712  SDLoc SL(N);
10713 
10714  SDValue Src0 = N->getOperand(0);
10715  SDValue Src1 = N->getOperand(1);
10716  SDValue Src2 = N->getOperand(2);
10717 
10718  if (isClampZeroToOne(Src0, Src1)) {
10719  // const_a, const_b, x -> clamp is safe in all cases including signaling
10720  // nans.
10721  // FIXME: Should this be allowing -0.0?
10722  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CLAMP, SL, VT, Src2);
10723  }
10724 
10725  const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
10726  const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
10727 
10728  // FIXME: dx10_clamp behavior assumed in instcombine. Should we really bother
10729  // handling no dx10-clamp?
10730  if (Info->getMode().DX10Clamp) {
10731  // If NaNs is clamped to 0, we are free to reorder the inputs.
10732 
10733  if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src0) && !isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src1))
10734  std::swap(Src0, Src1);
10735 
10736  if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src1) && !isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src2))
10737  std::swap(Src1, Src2);
10738 
10739  if (isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src0) && !isa<ConstantFPSDNode>(Src1))
10740  std::swap(Src0, Src1);
10741 
10742  if (isClampZeroToOne(Src1, Src2))
10743  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CLAMP, SL, VT, Src0);
10744  }
10745 
10746  return SDValue();
10747 }
10748 
10749 SDValue SITargetLowering::performCvtPkRTZCombine(SDNode *N,
10750  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10751  SDValue Src0 = N->getOperand(0);
10752  SDValue Src1 = N->getOperand(1);
10753  if (Src0.isUndef() && Src1.isUndef())
10754  return DCI.DAG.getUNDEF(N->getValueType(0));
10755  return SDValue();
10756 }
10757 
10758 // Check if EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT/INSERT_VECTOR_ELT (<n x e>, var-idx) should be
10759 // expanded into a set of cmp/select instructions.
10760 bool SITargetLowering::shouldExpandVectorDynExt(unsigned EltSize,
10761  unsigned NumElem,
10762  bool IsDivergentIdx,
10763  const GCNSubtarget *Subtarget) {
10764  if (UseDivergentRegisterIndexing)
10765  return false;
10766 
10767  unsigned VecSize = EltSize * NumElem;
10768 
10769  // Sub-dword vectors of size 2 dword or less have better implementation.
10770  if (VecSize <= 64 && EltSize < 32)
10771  return false;
10772 
10773  // Always expand the rest of sub-dword instructions, otherwise it will be
10774  // lowered via memory.
10775  if (EltSize < 32)
10776  return true;
10777 
10778  // Always do this if var-idx is divergent, otherwise it will become a loop.
10779  if (IsDivergentIdx)
10780  return true;
10781 
10782  // Large vectors would yield too many compares and v_cndmask_b32 instructions.
10783  unsigned NumInsts = NumElem /* Number of compares */ +
10784  ((EltSize + 31) / 32) * NumElem /* Number of cndmasks */;
10785 
10786  // On some architectures (GFX9) movrel is not available and it's better
10787  // to expand.
10788  if (!Subtarget->hasMovrel())
10789  return NumInsts <= 16;
10790 
10791  // If movrel is available, use it instead of expanding for vector of 8
10792  // elements.
10793  return NumInsts <= 15;
10794 }
10795 
10796 bool SITargetLowering::shouldExpandVectorDynExt(SDNode *N) const {
10797  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(N->getNumOperands() - 1);
10798  if (isa<ConstantSDNode>(Idx))
10799  return false;
10800 
10801  SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
10802  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
10803  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
10804  unsigned EltSize = EltVT.getSizeInBits();
10805  unsigned NumElem = VecVT.getVectorNumElements();
10806 
10807  return SITargetLowering::shouldExpandVectorDynExt(
10808  EltSize, NumElem, Idx->isDivergent(), getSubtarget());
10809 }
10810 
10811 SDValue SITargetLowering::performExtractVectorEltCombine(
10812  SDNode *N, DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10813  SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
10814  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10815 
10816  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
10817  EVT VecEltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
10818  EVT ResVT = N->getValueType(0);
10819 
10820  unsigned VecSize = VecVT.getSizeInBits();
10821  unsigned VecEltSize = VecEltVT.getSizeInBits();
10822 
10823  if ((Vec.getOpcode() == ISD::FNEG ||
10824  Vec.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) && allUsesHaveSourceMods(N)) {
10825  SDLoc SL(N);
10826  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
10827  SDValue Elt =
10828  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, ResVT, Vec.getOperand(0), Idx);
10829  return DAG.getNode(Vec.getOpcode(), SL, ResVT, Elt);
10830  }
10831 
10832  // ScalarRes = EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ((vector-BINOP Vec1, Vec2), Idx)
10833  // =>
10834  // Vec1Elt = EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(Vec1, Idx)
10835  // Vec2Elt = EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(Vec2, Idx)
10836  // ScalarRes = scalar-BINOP Vec1Elt, Vec2Elt
10837  if (Vec.hasOneUse() && DCI.isBeforeLegalize() && VecEltVT == ResVT) {
10838  SDLoc SL(N);
10839  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
10840  unsigned Opc = Vec.getOpcode();
10841 
10842  switch(Opc) {
10843  default:
10844  break;
10845  // TODO: Support other binary operations.
10846  case ISD::FADD:
10847  case ISD::FSUB:
10848  case ISD::FMUL:
10849  case ISD::ADD:
10850  case ISD::UMIN:
10851  case ISD::UMAX:
10852  case ISD::SMIN:
10853  case ISD::SMAX:
10854  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
10855  case ISD::FMINNUM:
10856  case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
10857  case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE: {
10858  SDValue Elt0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, ResVT,
10859  Vec.getOperand(0), Idx);
10860  SDValue Elt1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, ResVT,
10861  Vec.getOperand(1), Idx);
10862 
10863  DCI.AddToWorklist(Elt0.getNode());
10864  DCI.AddToWorklist(Elt1.getNode());
10865  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SL, ResVT, Elt0, Elt1, Vec->getFlags());
10866  }
10867  }
10868  }
10869 
10870  // EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT (<n x e>, var-idx) => n x select (e, const-idx)
10871  if (shouldExpandVectorDynExt(N)) {
10872  SDLoc SL(N);
10873  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(1);
10874  SDValue V;
10875  for (unsigned I = 0, E = VecVT.getVectorNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
10876  SDValue IC = DAG.getVectorIdxConstant(I, SL);
10877  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, ResVT, Vec, IC);
10878  if (I == 0)
10879  V = Elt;
10880  else
10881  V = DAG.getSelectCC(SL, Idx, IC, Elt, V, ISD::SETEQ);
10882  }
10883  return V;
10884  }
10885 
10886  if (!DCI.isBeforeLegalize())
10887  return SDValue();
10888 
10889  // Try to turn sub-dword accesses of vectors into accesses of the same 32-bit
10890  // elements. This exposes more load reduction opportunities by replacing
10891  // multiple small extract_vector_elements with a single 32-bit extract.
10892  auto *Idx = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
10893  if (isa<MemSDNode>(Vec) && VecEltSize <= 16 && VecEltVT.isByteSized() &&
10894  VecSize > 32 && VecSize % 32 == 0 && Idx) {
10895  EVT NewVT = getEquivalentMemType(*DAG.getContext(), VecVT);
10896 
10897  unsigned BitIndex = Idx->getZExtValue() * VecEltSize;
10898  unsigned EltIdx = BitIndex / 32;
10899  unsigned LeftoverBitIdx = BitIndex % 32;
10900  SDLoc SL(N);
10901 
10902  SDValue Cast = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, NewVT, Vec);
10903  DCI.AddToWorklist(Cast.getNode());
10904 
10905  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, MVT::i32, Cast,
10906  DAG.getConstant(EltIdx, SL, MVT::i32));
10907  DCI.AddToWorklist(Elt.getNode());
10908  SDValue Srl = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, SL, MVT::i32, Elt,
10909  DAG.getConstant(LeftoverBitIdx, SL, MVT::i32));
10910  DCI.AddToWorklist(Srl.getNode());
10911 
10912  EVT VecEltAsIntVT = VecEltVT.changeTypeToInteger();
10913  SDValue Trunc = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VecEltAsIntVT, Srl);
10914  DCI.AddToWorklist(Trunc.getNode());
10915 
10916  if (VecEltVT == ResVT) {
10917  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VecEltVT, Trunc);
10918  }
10919 
10920  assert(ResVT.isScalarInteger());
10921  return DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(Trunc, SL, ResVT);
10922  }
10923 
10924  return SDValue();
10925 }
10926 
10927 SDValue
10928 SITargetLowering::performInsertVectorEltCombine(SDNode *N,
10929  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
10930  SDValue Vec = N->getOperand(0);
10931  SDValue Idx = N->getOperand(2);
10932  EVT VecVT = Vec.getValueType();
10933  EVT EltVT = VecVT.getVectorElementType();
10934 
10935  // INSERT_VECTOR_ELT (<n x e>, var-idx)
10936  // => BUILD_VECTOR n x select (e, const-idx)
10937  if (!shouldExpandVectorDynExt(N))
10938  return SDValue();
10939 
10940  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
10941  SDLoc SL(N);
10942  SDValue Ins = N->getOperand(1);
10943  EVT IdxVT = Idx.getValueType();
10944 
10945  SmallVector<SDValue, 16> Ops;
10946  for (unsigned I = 0, E = VecVT.getVectorNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
10947  SDValue IC = DAG.getConstant(I, SL, IdxVT);
10948  SDValue Elt = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT, SL, EltVT, Vec, IC);
10949  SDValue V = DAG.getSelectCC(SL, Idx, IC, Ins, Elt, ISD::SETEQ);
10950  Ops.push_back(V);
10951  }
10952 
10953  return DAG.getBuildVector(VecVT, SL, Ops);
10954 }
10955 
10956 unsigned SITargetLowering::getFusedOpcode(const SelectionDAG &DAG,
10957  const SDNode *N0,
10958  const SDNode *N1) const {
10959  EVT VT = N0->getValueType(0);
10960 
10961  // Only do this if we are not trying to support denormals. v_mad_f32 does not
10962  // support denormals ever.
10963  if (((VT == MVT::f32 && !hasFP32Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction())) ||
10964  (VT == MVT::f16 && !hasFP64FP16Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction()) &&
10965  getSubtarget()->hasMadF16())) &&
10966  isOperationLegal(ISD::FMAD, VT))
10967  return ISD::FMAD;
10968 
10969  const TargetOptions &Options = DAG.getTarget().Options;
10970  if ((Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Fast || Options.UnsafeFPMath ||
10971  (N0->getFlags().hasAllowContract() &&
10972  N1->getFlags().hasAllowContract())) &&
10973  isFMAFasterThanFMulAndFAdd(DAG.getMachineFunction(), VT)) {
10974  return ISD::FMA;
10975  }
10976 
10977  return 0;
10978 }
10979 
10980 // For a reassociatable opcode perform:
10981 // op x, (op y, z) -> op (op x, z), y, if x and z are uniform
10982 SDValue SITargetLowering::reassociateScalarOps(SDNode *N,
10983  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
10984  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
10985  if (VT != MVT::i32 && VT != MVT::i64)
10986  return SDValue();
10987 
10988  if (DAG.isBaseWithConstantOffset(SDValue(N, 0)))
10989  return SDValue();
10990 
10991  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
10992  SDValue Op0 = N->getOperand(0);
10993  SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(1);
10994 
10995  if (!(Op0->isDivergent() ^ Op1->isDivergent()))
10996  return SDValue();
10997 
10998  if (Op0->isDivergent())
10999  std::swap(Op0, Op1);
11000 
11001  if (Op1.getOpcode() != Opc || !Op1.hasOneUse())
11002  return SDValue();
11003 
11004  SDValue Op2 = Op1.getOperand(1);
11005  Op1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
11006  if (!(Op1->isDivergent() ^ Op2->isDivergent()))
11007  return SDValue();
11008 
11009  if (Op1->isDivergent())
11010  std::swap(Op1, Op2);
11011 
11012  SDLoc SL(N);
11013  SDValue Add1 = DAG.getNode(Opc, SL, VT, Op0, Op1);
11014  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SL, VT, Add1, Op2);
11015 }
11016 
11017 static SDValue getMad64_32(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &SL,
11018  EVT VT,
11019  SDValue N0, SDValue N1, SDValue N2,
11020  bool Signed) {
11021  unsigned MadOpc = Signed ? AMDGPUISD::MAD_I64_I32 : AMDGPUISD::MAD_U64_U32;
11022  SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i64, MVT::i1);
11023  SDValue Mad = DAG.getNode(MadOpc, SL, VTs, N0, N1, N2);
11024  return DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VT, Mad);
11025 }
11026 
11027 // Fold (add (mul x, y), z) --> (mad_[iu]64_[iu]32 x, y, z) plus high
11028 // multiplies, if any.
11029 //
11030 // Full 64-bit multiplies that feed into an addition are lowered here instead
11031 // of using the generic expansion. The generic expansion ends up with
11032 // a tree of ADD nodes that prevents us from using the "add" part of the
11033 // MAD instruction. The expansion produced here results in a chain of ADDs
11034 // instead of a tree.
11035 SDValue SITargetLowering::tryFoldToMad64_32(SDNode *N,
11036  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11037  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::ADD);
11038 
11039  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11040  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11041  SDLoc SL(N);
11042  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11043  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11044 
11045  if (VT.isVector())
11046  return SDValue();
11047 
11048  // S_MUL_HI_[IU]32 was added in gfx9, which allows us to keep the overall
11049  // result in scalar registers for uniform values.
11050  if (!N->isDivergent() && Subtarget->hasSMulHi())
11051  return SDValue();
11052 
11053  unsigned NumBits = VT.getScalarSizeInBits();
11054  if (NumBits <= 32 || NumBits > 64)
11055  return SDValue();
11056 
11057  if (LHS.getOpcode() != ISD::MUL) {
11058  assert(RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL);
11059  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
11060  }
11061 
11062  // Avoid the fold if it would unduly increase the number of multiplies due to
11063  // multiple uses, except on hardware with full-rate multiply-add (which is
11064  // part of full-rate 64-bit ops).
11065  if (!Subtarget->hasFullRate64Ops()) {
11066  unsigned NumUsers = 0;
11067  for (SDNode *Use : LHS->uses()) {
11068  // There is a use that does not feed into addition, so the multiply can't
11069  // be removed. We prefer MUL + ADD + ADDC over MAD + MUL.
11070  if (Use->getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
11071  return SDValue();
11072 
11073  // We prefer 2xMAD over MUL + 2xADD + 2xADDC (code density), and prefer
11074  // MUL + 3xADD + 3xADDC over 3xMAD.
11075  ++NumUsers;
11076  if (NumUsers >= 3)
11077  return SDValue();
11078  }
11079  }
11080 
11081  SDValue MulLHS = LHS.getOperand(0);
11082  SDValue MulRHS = LHS.getOperand(1);
11083  SDValue AddRHS = RHS;
11084 
11085  // Always check whether operands are small unsigned values, since that
11086  // knowledge is useful in more cases. Check for small signed values only if
11087  // doing so can unlock a shorter code sequence.
11088  bool MulLHSUnsigned32 = numBitsUnsigned(MulLHS, DAG) <= 32;
11089  bool MulRHSUnsigned32 = numBitsUnsigned(MulRHS, DAG) <= 32;
11090 
11091  bool MulSignedLo = false;
11092  if (!MulLHSUnsigned32 || !MulRHSUnsigned32) {
11093  MulSignedLo = numBitsSigned(MulLHS, DAG) <= 32 &&
11094  numBitsSigned(MulRHS, DAG) <= 32;
11095  }
11096 
11097  // The operands and final result all have the same number of bits. If
11098  // operands need to be extended, they can be extended with garbage. The
11099  // resulting garbage in the high bits of the mad_[iu]64_[iu]32 result is
11100  // truncated away in the end.
11101  if (VT != MVT::i64) {
11102  MulLHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i64, MulLHS);
11103  MulRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i64, MulRHS);
11104  AddRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i64, AddRHS);
11105  }
11106 
11107  // The basic code generated is conceptually straightforward. Pseudo code:
11108  //
11109  // accum = mad_64_32 lhs.lo, rhs.lo, accum
11110  // accum.hi = add (mul lhs.hi, rhs.lo), accum.hi
11111  // accum.hi = add (mul lhs.lo, rhs.hi), accum.hi
11112  //
11113  // The second and third lines are optional, depending on whether the factors
11114  // are {sign,zero}-extended or not.
11115  //
11116  // The actual DAG is noisier than the pseudo code, but only due to
11117  // instructions that disassemble values into low and high parts, and
11118  // assemble the final result.
11119  SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32);
11120  SDValue One = DAG.getConstant(1, SL, MVT::i32);
11121 
11122  auto MulLHSLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MVT::i32, MulLHS);
11123  auto MulRHSLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, MVT::i32, MulRHS);
11124  SDValue Accum =
11125  getMad64_32(DAG, SL, MVT::i64, MulLHSLo, MulRHSLo, AddRHS, MulSignedLo);
11126 
11127  if (!MulSignedLo && (!MulLHSUnsigned32 || !MulRHSUnsigned32)) {
11128  auto AccumLo = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, SL, MVT::i32, Accum, Zero);
11129  auto AccumHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, SL, MVT::i32, Accum, One);
11130 
11131  if (!MulLHSUnsigned32) {
11132  auto MulLHSHi =
11133  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, SL, MVT::i32, MulLHS, One);
11134  SDValue MulHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, SL, MVT::i32, MulLHSHi, MulRHSLo);
11135  AccumHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, SL, MVT::i32, MulHi, AccumHi);
11136  }
11137 
11138  if (!MulRHSUnsigned32) {
11139  auto MulRHSHi =
11140  DAG.getNode(ISD::EXTRACT_ELEMENT, SL, MVT::i32, MulRHS, One);
11141  SDValue MulHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, SL, MVT::i32, MulLHSLo, MulRHSHi);
11142  AccumHi = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, SL, MVT::i32, MulHi, AccumHi);
11143  }
11144 
11145  Accum = DAG.getBuildVector(MVT::v2i32, SL, {AccumLo, AccumHi});
11146  Accum = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i64, Accum);
11147  }
11148 
11149  if (VT != MVT::i64)
11150  Accum = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, SL, VT, Accum);
11151  return Accum;
11152 }
11153 
11154 SDValue SITargetLowering::performAddCombine(SDNode *N,
11155  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11156  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11157  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11158  SDLoc SL(N);
11159  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11160  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11161 
11162  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL || RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::MUL) {
11163  if (Subtarget->hasMad64_32()) {
11164  if (SDValue Folded = tryFoldToMad64_32(N, DCI))
11165  return Folded;
11166  }
11167 
11168  return SDValue();
11169  }
11170 
11171  if (SDValue V = reassociateScalarOps(N, DAG)) {
11172  return V;
11173  }
11174 
11175  if (VT != MVT::i32 || !DCI.isAfterLegalizeDAG())
11176  return SDValue();
11177 
11178  // add x, zext (setcc) => addcarry x, 0, setcc
11179  // add x, sext (setcc) => subcarry x, 0, setcc
11180  unsigned Opc = LHS.getOpcode();
11181  if (Opc == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND || Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND ||
11182  Opc == ISD::ANY_EXTEND || Opc == ISD::ADDCARRY)
11183  std::swap(RHS, LHS);
11184 
11185  Opc = RHS.getOpcode();
11186  switch (Opc) {
11187  default: break;
11188  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
11189  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
11190  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: {
11191  auto Cond = RHS.getOperand(0);
11192  // If this won't be a real VOPC output, we would still need to insert an
11193  // extra instruction anyway.
11194  if (!isBoolSGPR(Cond))
11195  break;
11196  SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i1);
11197  SDValue Args[] = { LHS, DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32), Cond };
11198  Opc = (Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND) ? ISD::SUBCARRY : ISD::ADDCARRY;
11199  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SL, VTList, Args);
11200  }
11201  case ISD::ADDCARRY: {
11202  // add x, (addcarry y, 0, cc) => addcarry x, y, cc
11203  auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS.getOperand(1));
11204  if (!C || C->getZExtValue() != 0) break;
11205  SDValue Args[] = { LHS, RHS.getOperand(0), RHS.getOperand(2) };
11206  return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADDCARRY, SDLoc(N), RHS->getVTList(), Args);
11207  }
11208  }
11209  return SDValue();
11210 }
11211 
11212 SDValue SITargetLowering::performSubCombine(SDNode *N,
11213  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11214  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11215  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11216 
11217  if (VT != MVT::i32)
11218  return SDValue();
11219 
11220  SDLoc SL(N);
11221  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11222  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11223 
11224  // sub x, zext (setcc) => subcarry x, 0, setcc
11225  // sub x, sext (setcc) => addcarry x, 0, setcc
11226  unsigned Opc = RHS.getOpcode();
11227  switch (Opc) {
11228  default: break;
11229  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
11230  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND:
11231  case ISD::ANY_EXTEND: {
11232  auto Cond = RHS.getOperand(0);
11233  // If this won't be a real VOPC output, we would still need to insert an
11234  // extra instruction anyway.
11235  if (!isBoolSGPR(Cond))
11236  break;
11237  SDVTList VTList = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::i1);
11238  SDValue Args[] = { LHS, DAG.getConstant(0, SL, MVT::i32), Cond };
11239  Opc = (Opc == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND) ? ISD::ADDCARRY : ISD::SUBCARRY;
11240  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SL, VTList, Args);
11241  }
11242  }
11243 
11244  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SUBCARRY) {
11245  // sub (subcarry x, 0, cc), y => subcarry x, y, cc
11246  auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1));
11247  if (!C || !C->isZero())
11248  return SDValue();
11249  SDValue Args[] = { LHS.getOperand(0), RHS, LHS.getOperand(2) };
11250  return DAG.getNode(ISD::SUBCARRY, SDLoc(N), LHS->getVTList(), Args);
11251  }
11252  return SDValue();
11253 }
11254 
11255 SDValue SITargetLowering::performAddCarrySubCarryCombine(SDNode *N,
11256  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11257 
11258  if (N->getValueType(0) != MVT::i32)
11259  return SDValue();
11260 
11261  auto C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
11262  if (!C || C->getZExtValue() != 0)
11263  return SDValue();
11264 
11265  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11266  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11267 
11268  // addcarry (add x, y), 0, cc => addcarry x, y, cc
11269  // subcarry (sub x, y), 0, cc => subcarry x, y, cc
11270  unsigned LHSOpc = LHS.getOpcode();
11271  unsigned Opc = N->getOpcode();
11272  if ((LHSOpc == ISD::ADD && Opc == ISD::ADDCARRY) ||
11273  (LHSOpc == ISD::SUB && Opc == ISD::SUBCARRY)) {
11274  SDValue Args[] = { LHS.getOperand(0), LHS.getOperand(1), N->getOperand(2) };
11275  return DAG.getNode(Opc, SDLoc(N), N->getVTList(), Args);
11276  }
11277  return SDValue();
11278 }
11279 
11280 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFAddCombine(SDNode *N,
11281  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11282  if (DCI.getDAGCombineLevel() < AfterLegalizeDAG)
11283  return SDValue();
11284 
11285  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11286  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11287 
11288  SDLoc SL(N);
11289  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11290  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11291 
11292  // These should really be instruction patterns, but writing patterns with
11293  // source modifiers is a pain.
11294 
11295  // fadd (fadd (a, a), b) -> mad 2.0, a, b
11296  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
11297  SDValue A = LHS.getOperand(0);
11298  if (A == LHS.getOperand(1)) {
11299  unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, LHS.getNode());
11300  if (FusedOp != 0) {
11301  const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
11302  return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, RHS);
11303  }
11304  }
11305  }
11306 
11307  // fadd (b, fadd (a, a)) -> mad 2.0, a, b
11308  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
11309  SDValue A = RHS.getOperand(0);
11310  if (A == RHS.getOperand(1)) {
11311  unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, RHS.getNode());
11312  if (FusedOp != 0) {
11313  const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
11314  return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, LHS);
11315  }
11316  }
11317  }
11318 
11319  return SDValue();
11320 }
11321 
11322 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFSubCombine(SDNode *N,
11323  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11324  if (DCI.getDAGCombineLevel() < AfterLegalizeDAG)
11325  return SDValue();
11326 
11327  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11328  SDLoc SL(N);
11329  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11330  assert(!VT.isVector());
11331 
11332  // Try to get the fneg to fold into the source modifier. This undoes generic
11333  // DAG combines and folds them into the mad.
11334  //
11335  // Only do this if we are not trying to support denormals. v_mad_f32 does
11336  // not support denormals ever.
11337  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11338  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11339  if (LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
11340  // (fsub (fadd a, a), c) -> mad 2.0, a, (fneg c)
11341  SDValue A = LHS.getOperand(0);
11342  if (A == LHS.getOperand(1)) {
11343  unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, LHS.getNode());
11344  if (FusedOp != 0){
11345  const SDValue Two = DAG.getConstantFP(2.0, SL, VT);
11346  SDValue NegRHS = DAG.getNode(ISD::FNEG, SL, VT, RHS);
11347 
11348  return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, Two, NegRHS);
11349  }
11350  }
11351  }
11352 
11353  if (RHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FADD) {
11354  // (fsub c, (fadd a, a)) -> mad -2.0, a, c
11355 
11356  SDValue A = RHS.getOperand(0);
11357  if (A == RHS.getOperand(1)) {
11358  unsigned FusedOp = getFusedOpcode(DAG, N, RHS.getNode());
11359  if (FusedOp != 0){
11360  const SDValue NegTwo = DAG.getConstantFP(-2.0, SL, VT);
11361  return DAG.getNode(FusedOp, SL, VT, A, NegTwo, LHS);
11362  }
11363  }
11364  }
11365 
11366  return SDValue();
11367 }
11368 
11369 SDValue SITargetLowering::performFMACombine(SDNode *N,
11370  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11371  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11372  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11373  SDLoc SL(N);
11374 
11375  if (!Subtarget->hasDot7Insts() || VT != MVT::f32)
11376  return SDValue();
11377 
11378  // FMA((F32)S0.x, (F32)S1. x, FMA((F32)S0.y, (F32)S1.y, (F32)z)) ->
11379  // FDOT2((V2F16)S0, (V2F16)S1, (F32)z))
11380  SDValue Op1 = N->getOperand(0);
11381  SDValue Op2 = N->getOperand(1);
11382  SDValue FMA = N->getOperand(2);
11383 
11384  if (FMA.getOpcode() != ISD::FMA ||
11385  Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND ||
11386  Op2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND)
11387  return SDValue();
11388 
11389  // fdot2_f32_f16 always flushes fp32 denormal operand and output to zero,
11390  // regardless of the denorm mode setting. Therefore,
11391  // unsafe-fp-math/fp-contract is sufficient to allow generating fdot2.
11392  const TargetOptions &Options = DAG.getTarget().Options;
11393  if (Options.AllowFPOpFusion == FPOpFusion::Fast || Options.UnsafeFPMath ||
11394  (N->getFlags().hasAllowContract() &&
11395  FMA->getFlags().hasAllowContract())) {
11396  Op1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
11397  Op2 = Op2.getOperand(0);
11398  if (Op1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
11399  Op2.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
11400  return SDValue();
11401 
11402  SDValue Vec1 = Op1.getOperand(0);
11403  SDValue Idx1 = Op1.getOperand(1);
11404  SDValue Vec2 = Op2.getOperand(0);
11405 
11406  SDValue FMAOp1 = FMA.getOperand(0);
11407  SDValue FMAOp2 = FMA.getOperand(1);
11408  SDValue FMAAcc = FMA.getOperand(2);
11409 
11410  if (FMAOp1.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND ||
11411  FMAOp2.getOpcode() != ISD::FP_EXTEND)
11412  return SDValue();
11413 
11414  FMAOp1 = FMAOp1.getOperand(0);
11415  FMAOp2 = FMAOp2.getOperand(0);
11416  if (FMAOp1.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT ||
11417  FMAOp2.getOpcode() != ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT)
11418  return SDValue();
11419 
11420  SDValue Vec3 = FMAOp1.getOperand(0);
11421  SDValue Vec4 = FMAOp2.getOperand(0);
11422  SDValue Idx2 = FMAOp1.getOperand(1);
11423 
11424  if (Idx1 != Op2.getOperand(1) || Idx2 != FMAOp2.getOperand(1) ||
11425  // Idx1 and Idx2 cannot be the same.
11426  Idx1 == Idx2)
11427  return SDValue();
11428 
11429  if (Vec1 == Vec2 || Vec3 == Vec4)
11430  return SDValue();
11431 
11432  if (Vec1.getValueType() != MVT::v2f16 || Vec2.getValueType() != MVT::v2f16)
11433  return SDValue();
11434 
11435  if ((Vec1 == Vec3 && Vec2 == Vec4) ||
11436  (Vec1 == Vec4 && Vec2 == Vec3)) {
11437  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FDOT2, SL, MVT::f32, Vec1, Vec2, FMAAcc,
11438  DAG.getTargetConstant(0, SL, MVT::i1));
11439  }
11440  }
11441  return SDValue();
11442 }
11443 
11444 SDValue SITargetLowering::performSetCCCombine(SDNode *N,
11445  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11446  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11447  SDLoc SL(N);
11448 
11449  SDValue LHS = N->getOperand(0);
11450  SDValue RHS = N->getOperand(1);
11451  EVT VT = LHS.getValueType();
11452  ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(N->getOperand(2))->get();
11453 
11454  auto CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
11455  if (!CRHS) {
11456  CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(LHS);
11457  if (CRHS) {
11458  std::swap(LHS, RHS);
11459  CC = getSetCCSwappedOperands(CC);
11460  }
11461  }
11462 
11463  if (CRHS) {
11464  if (VT == MVT::i32 && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SIGN_EXTEND &&
11465  isBoolSGPR(LHS.getOperand(0))) {
11466  // setcc (sext from i1 cc), -1, ne|sgt|ult) => not cc => xor cc, -1
11467  // setcc (sext from i1 cc), -1, eq|sle|uge) => cc
11468  // setcc (sext from i1 cc), 0, eq|sge|ule) => not cc => xor cc, -1
11469  // setcc (sext from i1 cc), 0, ne|ugt|slt) => cc
11470  if ((CRHS->isAllOnes() &&
11471  (CC == ISD::SETNE || CC == ISD::SETGT || CC == ISD::SETULT)) ||
11472  (CRHS->isZero() &&
11473  (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETGE || CC == ISD::SETULE)))
11474  return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
11475  DAG.getConstant(-1, SL, MVT::i1));
11476  if ((CRHS->isAllOnes() &&
11477  (CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETLE || CC == ISD::SETUGE)) ||
11478  (CRHS->isZero() &&
11479  (CC == ISD::SETNE || CC == ISD::SETUGT || CC == ISD::SETLT)))
11480  return LHS.getOperand(0);
11481  }
11482 
11483  const APInt &CRHSVal = CRHS->getAPIntValue();
11484  if ((CC == ISD::SETEQ || CC == ISD::SETNE) &&
11485  LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::SELECT &&
11486  isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(1)) &&
11487  isa<ConstantSDNode>(LHS.getOperand(2)) &&
11488  LHS.getConstantOperandVal(1) != LHS.getConstantOperandVal(2) &&
11489  isBoolSGPR(LHS.getOperand(0))) {
11490  // Given CT != FT:
11491  // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CF, eq => xor cc, -1
11492  // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CF, ne => cc
11493  // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CT, ne => xor cc, -1
11494  // setcc (select cc, CT, CF), CT, eq => cc
11495  const APInt &CT = LHS.getConstantOperandAPInt(1);
11496  const APInt &CF = LHS.getConstantOperandAPInt(2);
11497 
11498  if ((CF == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETEQ) ||
11499  (CT == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETNE))
11500  return DAG.getNode(ISD::XOR, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
11501  DAG.getConstant(-1, SL, MVT::i1));
11502  if ((CF == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETNE) ||
11503  (CT == CRHSVal && CC == ISD::SETEQ))
11504  return LHS.getOperand(0);
11505  }
11506  }
11507 
11508  if (VT != MVT::f32 && VT != MVT::f64 &&
11509  (!Subtarget->has16BitInsts() || VT != MVT::f16))
11510  return SDValue();
11511 
11512  // Match isinf/isfinite pattern
11513  // (fcmp oeq (fabs x), inf) -> (fp_class x, (p_infinity | n_infinity))
11514  // (fcmp one (fabs x), inf) -> (fp_class x,
11515  // (p_normal | n_normal | p_subnormal | n_subnormal | p_zero | n_zero)
11516  if ((CC == ISD::SETOEQ || CC == ISD::SETONE) && LHS.getOpcode() == ISD::FABS) {
11517  const ConstantFPSDNode *CRHS = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(RHS);
11518  if (!CRHS)
11519  return SDValue();
11520 
11521  const APFloat &APF = CRHS->getValueAPF();
11522  if (APF.isInfinity() && !APF.isNegative()) {
11523  const unsigned IsInfMask = SIInstrFlags::P_INFINITY |
11524  SIInstrFlags::N_INFINITY;
11525  const unsigned IsFiniteMask = SIInstrFlags::N_ZERO |
11526  SIInstrFlags::P_ZERO |
11527  SIInstrFlags::N_NORMAL |
11528  SIInstrFlags::P_NORMAL |
11529  SIInstrFlags::N_SUBNORMAL |
11530  SIInstrFlags::P_SUBNORMAL;
11531  unsigned Mask = CC == ISD::SETOEQ ? IsInfMask : IsFiniteMask;
11532  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS, SL, MVT::i1, LHS.getOperand(0),
11533  DAG.getConstant(Mask, SL, MVT::i32));
11534  }
11535  }
11536 
11537  return SDValue();
11538 }
11539 
11540 SDValue SITargetLowering::performCvtF32UByteNCombine(SDNode *N,
11541  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11542  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11543  SDLoc SL(N);
11544  unsigned Offset = N->getOpcode() - AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0;
11545 
11546  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
11547  SDValue Shift = N->getOperand(0);
11548 
11549  // TODO: Extend type shouldn't matter (assuming legal types).
11550  if (Shift.getOpcode() == ISD::ZERO_EXTEND)
11551  Shift = Shift.getOperand(0);
11552 
11553  if (Shift.getOpcode() == ISD::SRL || Shift.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL) {
11554  // cvt_f32_ubyte1 (shl x, 8) -> cvt_f32_ubyte0 x
11555  // cvt_f32_ubyte3 (shl x, 16) -> cvt_f32_ubyte1 x
11556  // cvt_f32_ubyte0 (srl x, 16) -> cvt_f32_ubyte2 x
11557  // cvt_f32_ubyte1 (srl x, 16) -> cvt_f32_ubyte3 x
11558  // cvt_f32_ubyte0 (srl x, 8) -> cvt_f32_ubyte1 x
11559  if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Shift.getOperand(1))) {
11560  SDValue Shifted = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Shift.getOperand(0),
11561  SDLoc(Shift.getOperand(0)), MVT::i32);
11562 
11563  unsigned ShiftOffset = 8 * Offset;
11564  if (Shift.getOpcode() == ISD::SHL)
11565  ShiftOffset -= C->getZExtValue();
11566  else
11567  ShiftOffset += C->getZExtValue();
11568 
11569  if (ShiftOffset < 32 && (ShiftOffset % 8) == 0) {
11570  return DAG.getNode(AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0 + ShiftOffset / 8, SL,
11571  MVT::f32, Shifted);
11572  }
11573  }
11574  }
11575 
11576  const TargetLowering &TLI = DAG.getTargetLoweringInfo();
11577  APInt DemandedBits = APInt::getBitsSet(32, 8 * Offset, 8 * Offset + 8);
11578  if (TLI.SimplifyDemandedBits(Src, DemandedBits, DCI)) {
11579  // We simplified Src. If this node is not dead, visit it again so it is
11580  // folded properly.
11581  if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::DELETED_NODE)
11582  DCI.AddToWorklist(N);
11583  return SDValue(N, 0);
11584  }
11585 
11586  // Handle (or x, (srl y, 8)) pattern when known bits are zero.
11587  if (SDValue DemandedSrc =
11588  TLI.SimplifyMultipleUseDemandedBits(Src, DemandedBits, DAG))
11589  return DAG.getNode(N->getOpcode(), SL, MVT::f32, DemandedSrc);
11590 
11591  return SDValue();
11592 }
11593 
11594 SDValue SITargetLowering::performClampCombine(SDNode *N,
11595  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11596  ConstantFPSDNode *CSrc = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(N->getOperand(0));
11597  if (!CSrc)
11598  return SDValue();
11599 
11600  const MachineFunction &MF = DCI.DAG.getMachineFunction();
11601  const APFloat &F = CSrc->getValueAPF();
11602  APFloat Zero = APFloat::getZero(F.getSemantics());
11603  if (F < Zero ||
11604  (F.isNaN() && MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>()->getMode().DX10Clamp)) {
11605  return DCI.DAG.getConstantFP(Zero, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0));
11606  }
11607 
11608  APFloat One(F.getSemantics(), "1.0");
11609  if (F > One)
11610  return DCI.DAG.getConstantFP(One, SDLoc(N), N->getValueType(0));
11611 
11612  return SDValue(CSrc, 0);
11613 }
11614 
11615 
11616 SDValue SITargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(SDNode *N,
11617  DAGCombinerInfo &DCI) const {
11618  if (getTargetMachine().getOptLevel() == CodeGenOpt::None)
11619  return SDValue();
11620  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
11621  case ISD::ADD:
11622  return performAddCombine(N, DCI);
11623  case ISD::SUB:
11624  return performSubCombine(N, DCI);
11625  case ISD::ADDCARRY:
11626  case ISD::SUBCARRY:
11627  return performAddCarrySubCarryCombine(N, DCI);
11628  case ISD::FADD:
11629  return performFAddCombine(N, DCI);
11630  case ISD::FSUB:
11631  return performFSubCombine(N, DCI);
11632  case ISD::SETCC:
11633  return performSetCCCombine(N, DCI);
11634  case ISD::FMAXNUM:
11635  case ISD::FMINNUM:
11636  case ISD::FMAXNUM_IEEE:
11637  case ISD::FMINNUM_IEEE:
11638  case ISD::SMAX:
11639  case ISD::SMIN:
11640  case ISD::UMAX:
11641  case ISD::UMIN:
11642  case AMDGPUISD::FMIN_LEGACY:
11643  case AMDGPUISD::FMAX_LEGACY:
11644  return performMinMaxCombine(N, DCI);
11645  case ISD::FMA:
11646  return performFMACombine(N, DCI);
11647  case ISD::AND:
11648  return performAndCombine(N, DCI);
11649  case ISD::OR:
11650  return performOrCombine(N, DCI);
11651  case ISD::XOR:
11652  return performXorCombine(N, DCI);
11653  case ISD::ZERO_EXTEND:
11654  return performZeroExtendCombine(N, DCI);
11655  case ISD::SIGN_EXTEND_INREG:
11656  return performSignExtendInRegCombine(N , DCI);
11657  case AMDGPUISD::FP_CLASS:
11658  return performClassCombine(N, DCI);
11659  case ISD::FCANONICALIZE:
11660  return performFCanonicalizeCombine(N, DCI);
11661  case AMDGPUISD::RCP:
11662  return performRcpCombine(N, DCI);
11663  case AMDGPUISD::FRACT:
11664  case AMDGPUISD::RSQ:
11665  case AMDGPUISD::RCP_LEGACY:
11666  case AMDGPUISD::RCP_IFLAG:
11667  case AMDGPUISD::RSQ_CLAMP:
11668  case AMDGPUISD::LDEXP: {
11669  // FIXME: This is probably wrong. If src is an sNaN, it won't be quieted
11670  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
11671  if (Src.isUndef())
11672  return Src;
11673  break;
11674  }
11675  case ISD::SINT_TO_FP:
11676  case ISD::UINT_TO_FP:
11677  return performUCharToFloatCombine(N, DCI);
11678  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE0:
11679  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE1:
11680  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE2:
11681  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_F32_UBYTE3:
11682  return performCvtF32UByteNCombine(N, DCI);
11683  case AMDGPUISD::FMED3:
11684  return performFMed3Combine(N, DCI);
11685  case AMDGPUISD::CVT_PKRTZ_F16_F32:
11686  return performCvtPkRTZCombine(N, DCI);
11687  case AMDGPUISD::CLAMP:
11688  return performClampCombine(N, DCI);
11689  case ISD::SCALAR_TO_VECTOR: {
11690  SelectionDAG &DAG = DCI.DAG;
11691  EVT VT = N->getValueType(0);
11692 
11693  // v2i16 (scalar_to_vector i16:x) -> v2i16 (bitcast (any_extend i16:x))
11694  if (VT == MVT::v2i16 || VT == MVT::v2f16) {
11695  SDLoc SL(N);
11696  SDValue Src = N->getOperand(0);
11697  EVT EltVT = Src.getValueType();
11698  if (EltVT == MVT::f16)
11699  Src = DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, MVT::i16, Src);
11700 
11701  SDValue Ext = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, SL, MVT::i32, Src);
11702  return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, SL, VT, Ext);
11703  }
11704 
11705  break;
11706  }
11707  case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT:
11708  return performExtractVectorEltCombine(N, DCI);
11709  case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT:
11710  return performInsertVectorEltCombine(N, DCI);
11711  case ISD::LOAD: {
11712  if (SDValue Widended = widenLoad(cast<LoadSDNode>(N), DCI))
11713  return Widended;
11714  [[fallthrough]];
11715  }
11716  default: {
11717  if (!DCI.isBeforeLegalize()) {
11718  if (MemSDNode *MemNode = dyn_cast<MemSDNode>(N))
11719  return performMemSDNodeCombine(MemNode, DCI);
11720  }
11721 
11722  break;
11723  }
11724  }
11725 
11726  return AMDGPUTargetLowering::PerformDAGCombine(N, DCI);
11727 }
11728 
11729 /// Helper function for adjustWritemask
11730 static unsigned SubIdx2Lane(unsigned Idx) {
11731  switch (Idx) {
11732  default: return ~0u;
11733  case AMDGPU::sub0: return 0;
11734  case AMDGPU::sub1: return 1;
11735  case AMDGPU::sub2: return 2;
11736  case AMDGPU::sub3: return 3;
11737  case AMDGPU::sub4: return 4; // Possible with TFE/LWE
11738  }
11739 }
11740 
11741 /// Adjust the writemask of MIMG instructions
11742 SDNode *SITargetLowering::adjustWritemask(MachineSDNode *&Node,
11743  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
11744  unsigned Opcode = Node->getMachineOpcode();
11745 
11746  // Subtract 1 because the vdata output is not a MachineSDNode operand.
11747  int D16Idx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::d16) - 1;
11748  if (D16Idx >= 0 && Node->getConstantOperandVal(D16Idx))
11749  return Node; // not implemented for D16
11750 
11751  SDNode *Users[5] = { nullptr };
11752  unsigned Lane = 0;
11753  unsigned DmaskIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask) - 1;
11754  unsigned OldDmask = Node->getConstantOperandVal(DmaskIdx);
11755  unsigned NewDmask = 0;
11756  unsigned TFEIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe) - 1;
11757  unsigned LWEIdx = AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::lwe) - 1;
11758  bool UsesTFC = ((int(TFEIdx) >= 0 && Node->getConstantOperandVal(TFEIdx)) ||
11759  Node->getConstantOperandVal(LWEIdx))
11760  ? true
11761  : false;
11762  unsigned TFCLane = 0;
11763  bool HasChain = Node->getNumValues() > 1;
11764 
11765  if (OldDmask == 0) {
11766  // These are folded out, but on the chance it happens don't assert.
11767  return Node;
11768  }
11769 
11770  unsigned OldBitsSet = llvm::popcount(OldDmask);
11771  // Work out which is the TFE/LWE lane if that is enabled.
11772  if (UsesTFC) {
11773  TFCLane = OldBitsSet;
11774  }
11775 
11776  // Try to figure out the used register components
11777  for (SDNode::use_iterator I = Node->use_begin(), E = Node->use_end();
11778  I != E; ++I) {
11779 
11780  // Don't look at users of the chain.
11781  if (I.getUse().getResNo() != 0)
11782  continue;
11783 
11784  // Abort if we can't understand the usage
11785  if (!I->isMachineOpcode() ||
11786  I->getMachineOpcode() != TargetOpcode::EXTRACT_SUBREG)
11787  return Node;
11788
