11789  // Lane means which subreg of %vgpra_vgprb_vgprc_vgprd is used.
11790  // Note that subregs are packed, i.e. Lane==0 is the first bit set
11791  // in OldDmask, so it can be any of X,Y,Z,W; Lane==1 is the second bit
11792  // set, etc.
11793  Lane = SubIdx2Lane(I->getConstantOperandVal(1));
11794  if (Lane == ~0u)
11795  return Node;
11796 
11797  // Check if the use is for the TFE/LWE generated result at VGPRn+1.
11798  if (UsesTFC && Lane == TFCLane) {
11799  Users[Lane] = *I;
11800  } else {
11801  // Set which texture component corresponds to the lane.
11802  unsigned Comp;
11803  for (unsigned i = 0, Dmask = OldDmask; (i <= Lane) && (Dmask != 0); i++) {
11804  Comp = llvm::countr_zero(Dmask);
11805  Dmask &= ~(1 << Comp);
11806  }
11807 
11808  // Abort if we have more than one user per component.
11809  if (Users[Lane])
11810  return Node;
11811 
11812  Users[Lane] = *I;
11813  NewDmask |= 1 << Comp;
11814  }
11815  }
11816 
11817  // Don't allow 0 dmask, as hardware assumes one channel enabled.
11818  bool NoChannels = !NewDmask;
11819  if (NoChannels) {
11820  if (!UsesTFC) {
11821  // No uses of the result and not using TFC. Then do nothing.
11822  return Node;
11823  }
11824  // If the original dmask has one channel - then nothing to do
11825  if (OldBitsSet == 1)
11826  return Node;
11827  // Use an arbitrary dmask - required for the instruction to work
11828  NewDmask = 1;
11829  }
11830  // Abort if there's no change
11831  if (NewDmask == OldDmask)
11832  return Node;
11833 
11834  unsigned BitsSet = llvm::popcount(NewDmask);
11835 
11836  // Check for TFE or LWE - increase the number of channels by one to account
11837  // for the extra return value
11838  // This will need adjustment for D16 if this is also included in
11839  // adjustWriteMask (this function) but at present D16 are excluded.
11840  unsigned NewChannels = BitsSet + UsesTFC;
11841 
11842  int NewOpcode =
11843  AMDGPU::getMaskedMIMGOp(Node->getMachineOpcode(), NewChannels);
11844  assert(NewOpcode != -1 &&
11845  NewOpcode != static_cast<int>(Node->getMachineOpcode()) &&
11846  "failed to find equivalent MIMG op");
11847 
11848  // Adjust the writemask in the node
11849  SmallVector<SDValue, 12> Ops;
11850  Ops.insert(Ops.end(), Node->op_begin(), Node->op_begin() + DmaskIdx);
11851  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(NewDmask, SDLoc(Node), MVT::i32));
11852  Ops.insert(Ops.end(), Node->op_begin() + DmaskIdx + 1, Node->op_end());
11853 
11854  MVT SVT = Node->getValueType(0).getVectorElementType().getSimpleVT();
11855 
11856  MVT ResultVT = NewChannels == 1 ?
11857  SVT : MVT::getVectorVT(SVT, NewChannels == 3 ? 4 :
11858  NewChannels == 5 ? 8 : NewChannels);
11859  SDVTList NewVTList = HasChain ?
11860  DAG.getVTList(ResultVT, MVT::Other) : DAG.getVTList(ResultVT);
11861 
11862 
11863  MachineSDNode *NewNode = DAG.getMachineNode(NewOpcode, SDLoc(Node),
11864  NewVTList, Ops);
11865 
11866  if (HasChain) {
11867  // Update chain.
11868  DAG.setNodeMemRefs(NewNode, Node->memoperands());
11869  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(SDValue(Node, 1), SDValue(NewNode, 1));
11870  }
11871 
11872  if (NewChannels == 1) {
11873  assert(Node->hasNUsesOfValue(1, 0));
11874  SDNode *Copy = DAG.getMachineNode(TargetOpcode::COPY,
11875  SDLoc(Node), Users[Lane]->getValueType(0),
11876  SDValue(NewNode, 0));
11877  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Users[Lane], Copy);
11878  return nullptr;
11879  }
11880 
11881  // Update the users of the node with the new indices
11882  for (unsigned i = 0, Idx = AMDGPU::sub0; i < 5; ++i) {
11883  SDNode *User = Users[i];
11884  if (!User) {
11885  // Handle the special case of NoChannels. We set NewDmask to 1 above, but
11886  // Users[0] is still nullptr because channel 0 doesn't really have a use.
11887  if (i || !NoChannels)
11888  continue;
11889  } else {
11890  SDValue Op = DAG.getTargetConstant(Idx, SDLoc(User), MVT::i32);
11891  DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(User, SDValue(NewNode, 0), Op);
11892  }
11893 
11894  switch (Idx) {
11895  default: break;
11896  case AMDGPU::sub0: Idx = AMDGPU::sub1; break;
11897  case AMDGPU::sub1: Idx = AMDGPU::sub2; break;
11898  case AMDGPU::sub2: Idx = AMDGPU::sub3; break;
11899  case AMDGPU::sub3: Idx = AMDGPU::sub4; break;
11900  }
11901  }
11902 
11903  DAG.RemoveDeadNode(Node);
11904  return nullptr;
11905 }
11906 
11907 static bool isFrameIndexOp(SDValue Op) {
11908  if (Op.getOpcode() == ISD::AssertZext)
11909  Op = Op.getOperand(0);
11910 
11911  return isa<FrameIndexSDNode>(Op);
11912 }
11913 
11914 /// Legalize target independent instructions (e.g. INSERT_SUBREG)
11915 /// with frame index operands.
11916 /// LLVM assumes that inputs are to these instructions are registers.
11917 SDNode *SITargetLowering::legalizeTargetIndependentNode(SDNode *Node,
11918  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
11919  if (Node->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyToReg) {
11920  RegisterSDNode *DestReg = cast<RegisterSDNode>(Node->getOperand(1));
11921  SDValue SrcVal = Node->getOperand(2);
11922 
11923  // Insert a copy to a VReg_1 virtual register so LowerI1Copies doesn't have
11924  // to try understanding copies to physical registers.
11925  if (SrcVal.getValueType() == MVT::i1 && DestReg->getReg().isPhysical()) {
11926  SDLoc SL(Node);
11927  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getRegInfo();
11928  SDValue VReg = DAG.getRegister(
11929  MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VReg_1RegClass), MVT::i1);
11930 
11931  SDNode *Glued = Node->getGluedNode();
11932  SDValue ToVReg
11933  = DAG.getCopyToReg(Node->getOperand(0), SL, VReg, SrcVal,
11934  SDValue(Glued, Glued ? Glued->getNumValues() - 1 : 0));
11935  SDValue ToResultReg
11936  = DAG.getCopyToReg(ToVReg, SL, SDValue(DestReg, 0),
11937  VReg, ToVReg.getValue(1));
11938  DAG.ReplaceAllUsesWith(Node, ToResultReg.getNode());
11939  DAG.RemoveDeadNode(Node);
11940  return ToResultReg.getNode();
11941  }
11942  }
11943 
11944  SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
11945  for (unsigned i = 0; i < Node->getNumOperands(); ++i) {
11946  if (!isFrameIndexOp(Node->getOperand(i))) {
11947  Ops.push_back(Node->getOperand(i));
11948  continue;
11949  }
11950 
11951  SDLoc DL(Node);
11952  Ops.push_back(SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL,
11953  Node->getOperand(i).getValueType(),
11954  Node->getOperand(i)), 0));
11955  }
11956 
11957  return DAG.UpdateNodeOperands(Node, Ops);
11958 }
11959 
11960 /// Fold the instructions after selecting them.
11961 /// Returns null if users were already updated.
11962 SDNode *SITargetLowering::PostISelFolding(MachineSDNode *Node,
11963  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
11964  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
11965  unsigned Opcode = Node->getMachineOpcode();
11966 
11967  if (TII->isMIMG(Opcode) && !TII->get(Opcode).mayStore() &&
11968  !TII->isGather4(Opcode) &&
11969  AMDGPU::hasNamedOperand(Opcode, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask)) {
11970  return adjustWritemask(Node, DAG);
11971  }
11972 
11973  if (Opcode == AMDGPU::INSERT_SUBREG ||
11974  Opcode == AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE) {
11975  legalizeTargetIndependentNode(Node, DAG);
11976  return Node;
11977  }
11978 
11979  switch (Opcode) {
11980  case AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F32_e64:
11981  case AMDGPU::V_DIV_SCALE_F64_e64: {
11982  // Satisfy the operand register constraint when one of the inputs is
11983  // undefined. Ordinarily each undef value will have its own implicit_def of
11984  // a vreg, so force these to use a single register.
11985  SDValue Src0 = Node->getOperand(1);
11986  SDValue Src1 = Node->getOperand(3);
11987  SDValue Src2 = Node->getOperand(5);
11988 
11989  if ((Src0.isMachineOpcode() &&
11990  Src0.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF) &&
11991  (Src0 == Src1 || Src0 == Src2))
11992  break;
11993 
11994  MVT VT = Src0.getValueType().getSimpleVT();
11995  const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
11996  getRegClassFor(VT, Src0.getNode()->isDivergent());
11997 
11998  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getRegInfo();
11999  SDValue UndefReg = DAG.getRegister(MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC), VT);
12000 
12001  SDValue ImpDef = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), SDLoc(Node),
12002  UndefReg, Src0, SDValue());
12003 
12004  // src0 must be the same register as src1 or src2, even if the value is
12005  // undefined, so make sure we don't violate this constraint.
12006  if (Src0.isMachineOpcode() &&
12007  Src0.getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF) {
12008  if (Src1.isMachineOpcode() &&
12009  Src1.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF)
12010  Src0 = Src1;
12011  else if (Src2.isMachineOpcode() &&
12012  Src2.getMachineOpcode() != AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF)
12013  Src0 = Src2;
12014  else {
12015  assert(Src1.getMachineOpcode() == AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF);
12016  Src0 = UndefReg;
12017  Src1 = UndefReg;
12018  }
12019  } else
12020  break;
12021 
12022  SmallVector<SDValue, 9> Ops(Node->op_begin(), Node->op_end());
12023  Ops[1] = Src0;
12024  Ops[3] = Src1;
12025  Ops[5] = Src2;
12026  Ops.push_back(ImpDef.getValue(1));
12027  return DAG.getMachineNode(Opcode, SDLoc(Node), Node->getVTList(), Ops);
12028  }
12029  default:
12030  break;
12031  }
12032 
12033  return Node;
12034 }
12035 
12036 // Any MIMG instructions that use tfe or lwe require an initialization of the
12037 // result register that will be written in the case of a memory access failure.
12038 // The required code is also added to tie this init code to the result of the
12039 // img instruction.
12040 void SITargetLowering::AddIMGInit(MachineInstr &MI) const {
12041  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
12042  const SIRegisterInfo &TRI = TII->getRegisterInfo();
12043  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getMF()->getRegInfo();
12044  MachineBasicBlock &MBB = *MI.getParent();
12045 
12046  MachineOperand *TFE = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::tfe);
12047  MachineOperand *LWE = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::lwe);
12048  MachineOperand *D16 = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::d16);
12049 
12050  if (!TFE && !LWE) // intersect_ray
12051  return;
12052 
12053  unsigned TFEVal = TFE ? TFE->getImm() : 0;
12054  unsigned LWEVal = LWE->getImm();
12055  unsigned D16Val = D16 ? D16->getImm() : 0;
12056 
12057  if (!TFEVal && !LWEVal)
12058  return;
12059 
12060  // At least one of TFE or LWE are non-zero
12061  // We have to insert a suitable initialization of the result value and
12062  // tie this to the dest of the image instruction.
12063 
12064  const DebugLoc &DL = MI.getDebugLoc();
12065 
12066  int DstIdx =
12067  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(MI.getOpcode(), AMDGPU::OpName::vdata);
12068 
12069  // Calculate which dword we have to initialize to 0.
12070  MachineOperand *MO_Dmask = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::dmask);
12071 
12072  // check that dmask operand is found.
12073  assert(MO_Dmask && "Expected dmask operand in instruction");
12074 
12075  unsigned dmask = MO_Dmask->getImm();
12076  // Determine the number of active lanes taking into account the
12077  // Gather4 special case
12078  unsigned ActiveLanes = TII->isGather4(MI) ? 4 : llvm::popcount(dmask);
12079 
12080  bool Packed = !Subtarget->hasUnpackedD16VMem();
12081 
12082  unsigned InitIdx =
12083  D16Val && Packed ? ((ActiveLanes + 1) >> 1) + 1 : ActiveLanes + 1;
12084 
12085  // Abandon attempt if the dst size isn't large enough
12086  // - this is in fact an error but this is picked up elsewhere and
12087  // reported correctly.
12088  uint32_t DstSize = TRI.getRegSizeInBits(*TII->getOpRegClass(MI, DstIdx)) / 32;
12089  if (DstSize < InitIdx)
12090  return;
12091 
12092  // Create a register for the initialization value.
12093  Register PrevDst = MRI.createVirtualRegister(TII->getOpRegClass(MI, DstIdx));
12094  unsigned NewDst = 0; // Final initialized value will be in here
12095 
12096  // If PRTStrictNull feature is enabled (the default) then initialize
12097  // all the result registers to 0, otherwise just the error indication
12098  // register (VGPRn+1)
12099  unsigned SizeLeft = Subtarget->usePRTStrictNull() ? InitIdx : 1;
12100  unsigned CurrIdx = Subtarget->usePRTStrictNull() ? 0 : (InitIdx - 1);
12101 
12102  BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::IMPLICIT_DEF), PrevDst);
12103  for (; SizeLeft; SizeLeft--, CurrIdx++) {
12104  NewDst = MRI.createVirtualRegister(TII->getOpRegClass(MI, DstIdx));
12105  // Initialize dword
12106  Register SubReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass);
12107  BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(AMDGPU::V_MOV_B32_e32), SubReg)
12108  .addImm(0);
12109  // Insert into the super-reg
12110  BuildMI(MBB, MI, DL, TII->get(TargetOpcode::INSERT_SUBREG), NewDst)
12111  .addReg(PrevDst)
12112  .addReg(SubReg)
12113  .addImm(SIRegisterInfo::getSubRegFromChannel(CurrIdx));
12114 
12115  PrevDst = NewDst;
12116  }
12117 
12118  // Add as an implicit operand
12119  MI.addOperand(MachineOperand::CreateReg(NewDst, false, true));
12120 
12121  // Tie the just added implicit operand to the dst
12122  MI.tieOperands(DstIdx, MI.getNumOperands() - 1);
12123 }
12124 
12125 /// Assign the register class depending on the number of
12126 /// bits set in the writemask
12127 void SITargetLowering::AdjustInstrPostInstrSelection(MachineInstr &MI,
12128  SDNode *Node) const {
12129  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
12130 
12131  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MI.getParent()->getParent()->getRegInfo();
12132 
12133  if (TII->isVOP3(MI.getOpcode())) {
12134  // Make sure constant bus requirements are respected.
12135  TII->legalizeOperandsVOP3(MRI, MI);
12136 
12137  // Prefer VGPRs over AGPRs in mAI instructions where possible.
12138  // This saves a chain-copy of registers and better balance register
12139  // use between vgpr and agpr as agpr tuples tend to be big.
12140  if (!MI.getDesc().operands().empty()) {
12141  unsigned Opc = MI.getOpcode();
12142  const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
12143  for (auto I : { AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src0),
12144  AMDGPU::getNamedOperandIdx(Opc, AMDGPU::OpName::src1) }) {
12145  if (I == -1)
12146  break;
12147  MachineOperand &Op = MI.getOperand(I);
12148  if (!Op.isReg() || !Op.getReg().isVirtual())
12149  continue;
12150  auto *RC = TRI->getRegClassForReg(MRI, Op.getReg());
12151  if (!TRI->hasAGPRs(RC))
12152  continue;
12153  auto *Src = MRI.getUniqueVRegDef(Op.getReg());
12154  if (!Src || !Src->isCopy() ||
12155  !TRI->isSGPRReg(MRI, Src->getOperand(1).getReg()))
12156  continue;
12157  auto *NewRC = TRI->getEquivalentVGPRClass(RC);
12158  // All uses of agpr64 and agpr32 can also accept vgpr except for
12159  // v_accvgpr_read, but we do not produce agpr reads during selection,
12160  // so no use checks are needed.
12161  MRI.setRegClass(Op.getReg(), NewRC);
12162  }
12163 
12164  // Resolve the rest of AV operands to AGPRs.
12165  if (auto *Src2 = TII->getNamedOperand(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::src2)) {
12166  if (Src2->isReg() && Src2->getReg().isVirtual()) {
12167  auto *RC = TRI->getRegClassForReg(MRI, Src2->getReg());
12168  if (TRI->isVectorSuperClass(RC)) {
12169  auto *NewRC = TRI->getEquivalentAGPRClass(RC);
12170  MRI.setRegClass(Src2->getReg(), NewRC);
12171  if (Src2->isTied())
12172  MRI.setRegClass(MI.getOperand(0).getReg(), NewRC);
12173  }
12174  }
12175  }
12176  }
12177 
12178  return;
12179  }
12180 
12181  if (TII->isMIMG(MI)) {
12182  if (!MI.mayStore())
12183  AddIMGInit(MI);
12184  TII->enforceOperandRCAlignment(MI, AMDGPU::OpName::vaddr);
12185  }
12186 }
12187 
12188 static SDValue buildSMovImm32(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
12189  uint64_t Val) {
12190  SDValue K = DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, DL, MVT::i32);
12191  return SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_MOV_B32, DL, MVT::i32, K), 0);
12192 }
12193 
12194 MachineSDNode *SITargetLowering::wrapAddr64Rsrc(SelectionDAG &DAG,
12195  const SDLoc &DL,
12196  SDValue Ptr) const {
12197  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
12198 
12199  // Build the half of the subregister with the constants before building the
12200  // full 128-bit register. If we are building multiple resource descriptors,
12201  // this will allow CSEing of the 2-component register.
12202  const SDValue Ops0[] = {
12203  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SGPR_64RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
12204  buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, 0),
12205  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32),
12206  buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, TII->getDefaultRsrcDataFormat() >> 32),
12207  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32)
12208  };
12209 
12210  SDValue SubRegHi = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL,
12211  MVT::v2i32, Ops0), 0);
12212 
12213  // Combine the constants and the pointer.
12214  const SDValue Ops1[] = {
12215  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
12216  Ptr,
12217  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0_sub1, DL, MVT::i32),
12218  SubRegHi,
12219  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub2_sub3, DL, MVT::i32)
12220  };
12221 
12222  return DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::v4i32, Ops1);
12223 }
12224 
12225 /// Return a resource descriptor with the 'Add TID' bit enabled
12226 /// The TID (Thread ID) is multiplied by the stride value (bits [61:48]
12227 /// of the resource descriptor) to create an offset, which is added to
12228 /// the resource pointer.
12229 MachineSDNode *SITargetLowering::buildRSRC(SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &DL,
12230  SDValue Ptr, uint32_t RsrcDword1,
12231  uint64_t RsrcDword2And3) const {
12232  SDValue PtrLo = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32, Ptr);
12233  SDValue PtrHi = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32, Ptr);
12234  if (RsrcDword1) {
12235  PtrHi = SDValue(DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::S_OR_B32, DL, MVT::i32, PtrHi,
12236  DAG.getConstant(RsrcDword1, DL, MVT::i32)),
12237  0);
12238  }
12239 
12240  SDValue DataLo = buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL,
12241  RsrcDword2And3 & UINT64_C(0xFFFFFFFF));
12242  SDValue DataHi = buildSMovImm32(DAG, DL, RsrcDword2And3 >> 32);
12243 
12244  const SDValue Ops[] = {
12245  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::SGPR_128RegClassID, DL, MVT::i32),
12246  PtrLo,
12247  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub0, DL, MVT::i32),
12248  PtrHi,
12249  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub1, DL, MVT::i32),
12250  DataLo,
12251  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub2, DL, MVT::i32),
12252  DataHi,
12253  DAG.getTargetConstant(AMDGPU::sub3, DL, MVT::i32)
12254  };
12255 
12256  return DAG.getMachineNode(AMDGPU::REG_SEQUENCE, DL, MVT::v4i32, Ops);
12257 }

12259 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
12260 // SI Inline Assembly Support
12261 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//
12262 
12263 std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass *>
12264 SITargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI_,
12265  StringRef Constraint,
12266  MVT VT) const {
12267  const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = static_cast<const SIRegisterInfo *>(TRI_);
12268 
12269  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = nullptr;
12270  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
12271  const unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
12272  switch (Constraint[0]) {
12273  default:
12274  return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
12275  case 's':
12276  case 'r':
12277  switch (BitWidth) {
12278  case 16:
12279  RC = &AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass;
12280  break;
12281  case 64:
12282  RC = &AMDGPU::SGPR_64RegClass;
12283  break;
12284  default:
12285  RC = SIRegisterInfo::getSGPRClassForBitWidth(BitWidth);
12286  if (!RC)
12287  return std::pair(0U, nullptr);
12288  break;
12289  }
12290  break;
12291  case 'v':
12292  switch (BitWidth) {
12293  case 16:
12294  RC = &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass;
12295  break;
12296  default:
12297  RC = TRI->getVGPRClassForBitWidth(BitWidth);
12298  if (!RC)
12299  return std::pair(0U, nullptr);
12300  break;
12301  }
12302  break;
12303  case 'a':
12304  if (!Subtarget->hasMAIInsts())
12305  break;
12306  switch (BitWidth) {
12307  case 16:
12308  RC = &AMDGPU::AGPR_32RegClass;
12309  break;
12310  default:
12311  RC = TRI->getAGPRClassForBitWidth(BitWidth);
12312  if (!RC)
12313  return std::pair(0U, nullptr);
12314  break;
12315  }
12316  break;
12317  }
12318  // We actually support i128, i16 and f16 as inline parameters
12319  // even if they are not reported as legal
12320  if (RC && (isTypeLegal(VT) || VT.SimpleTy == MVT::i128 ||
12321  VT.SimpleTy == MVT::i16 || VT.SimpleTy == MVT::f16))
12322  return std::pair(0U, RC);
12323  }
12324 
12325  if (Constraint.startswith("{") && Constraint.endswith("}")) {
12326  StringRef RegName(Constraint.data() + 1, Constraint.size() - 2);
12327  if (RegName.consume_front("v")) {
12328  RC = &AMDGPU::VGPR_32RegClass;
12329  } else if (RegName.consume_front("s")) {
12330  RC = &AMDGPU::SGPR_32RegClass;
12331  } else if (RegName.consume_front("a")) {
12332  RC = &AMDGPU::AGPR_32RegClass;
12333  }
12334 
12335  if (RC) {
12336  uint32_t Idx;
12337  if (RegName.consume_front("[")) {
12338  uint32_t End;
12339  bool Failed = RegName.consumeInteger(10, Idx);
12340  Failed |= !RegName.consume_front(":");
12341  Failed |= RegName.consumeInteger(10, End);
12342  Failed |= !RegName.consume_back("]");
12343  if (!Failed) {
12344  uint32_t Width = (End - Idx + 1) * 32;
12345  MCRegister Reg = RC->getRegister(Idx);
12346  if (SIRegisterInfo::isVGPRClass(RC))
12347  RC = TRI->getVGPRClassForBitWidth(Width);
12348  else if (SIRegisterInfo::isSGPRClass(RC))
12349  RC = TRI->getSGPRClassForBitWidth(Width);
12350  else if (SIRegisterInfo::isAGPRClass(RC))
12351  RC = TRI->getAGPRClassForBitWidth(Width);
12352  if (RC) {
12353  Reg = TRI->getMatchingSuperReg(Reg, AMDGPU::sub0, RC);
12354  return std::pair(Reg, RC);
12355  }
12356  }
12357  } else {
12358  bool Failed = RegName.getAsInteger(10, Idx);
12359  if (!Failed && Idx < RC->getNumRegs())
12360  return std::pair(RC->getRegister(Idx), RC);
12361  }
12362  }
12363  }
12364 
12365  auto Ret = TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
12366  if (Ret.first)
12367  Ret.second = TRI->getPhysRegBaseClass(Ret.first);
12368 
12369  return Ret;
12370 }
12371 
12372 static bool isImmConstraint(StringRef Constraint) {
12373  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
12374  switch (Constraint[0]) {
12375  default: break;
12376  case 'I':
12377  case 'J':
12378  case 'A':
12379  case 'B':
12380  case 'C':
12381  return true;
12382  }
12383  } else if (Constraint == "DA" ||
12384  Constraint == "DB") {
12385  return true;
12386  }
12387  return false;
12388 }
12389 
12390 SITargetLowering::ConstraintType
12391 SITargetLowering::getConstraintType(StringRef Constraint) const {
12392  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
12393  switch (Constraint[0]) {
12394  default: break;
12395  case 's':
12396  case 'v':
12397  case 'a':
12398  return C_RegisterClass;
12399  }
12400  }
12401  if (isImmConstraint(Constraint)) {
12402  return C_Other;
12403  }
12404  return TargetLowering::getConstraintType(Constraint);
12405 }
12406 
12407 static uint64_t clearUnusedBits(uint64_t Val, unsigned Size) {
12408  if (!AMDGPU::isInlinableIntLiteral(Val)) {
12409  Val = Val & maskTrailingOnes<uint64_t>(Size);
12410  }
12411  return Val;
12412 }
12413 
12414 void SITargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(SDValue Op,
12415  std::string &Constraint,
12416  std::vector<SDValue> &Ops,
12417  SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
12418  if (isImmConstraint(Constraint)) {
12419  uint64_t Val;
12420  if (getAsmOperandConstVal(Op, Val) &&
12421  checkAsmConstraintVal(Op, Constraint, Val)) {
12422  Val = clearUnusedBits(Val, Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits());
12423  Ops.push_back(DAG.getTargetConstant(Val, SDLoc(Op), MVT::i64));
12424  }
12425  } else {
12426  TargetLowering::LowerAsmOperandForConstraint(Op, Constraint, Ops, DAG);
12427  }
12428 }
12429 
12430 bool SITargetLowering::getAsmOperandConstVal(SDValue Op, uint64_t &Val) const {
12431  unsigned Size = Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits();
12432  if (Size > 64)
12433  return false;
12434 
12435  if (Size == 16 && !Subtarget->has16BitInsts())
12436  return false;
12437 
12438  if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op)) {
12439  Val = C->getSExtValue();
12440  return true;
12441  }
12442  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(Op)) {
12443  Val = C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().getSExtValue();
12444  return true;
12445  }
12446  if (BuildVectorSDNode *V = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op)) {
12447  if (Size != 16 || Op.getNumOperands() != 2)
12448  return false;
12449  if (Op.getOperand(0).isUndef() || Op.getOperand(1).isUndef())
12450  return false;
12451  if (ConstantSDNode *C = V->getConstantSplatNode()) {
12452  Val = C->getSExtValue();
12453  return true;
12454  }
12455  if (ConstantFPSDNode *C = V->getConstantFPSplatNode()) {
12456  Val = C->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt().getSExtValue();
12457  return true;
12458  }
12459  }
12460 
12461  return false;
12462 }
12463 
12464 bool SITargetLowering::checkAsmConstraintVal(SDValue Op,
12465  const std::string &Constraint,
12466  uint64_t Val) const {
12467  if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
12468  switch (Constraint[0]) {
12469  case 'I':
12470  return AMDGPU::isInlinableIntLiteral(Val);
12471  case 'J':
12472  return isInt<16>(Val);
12473  case 'A':
12474  return checkAsmConstraintValA(Op, Val);
12475  case 'B':
12476  return isInt<32>(Val);
12477  case 'C':
12478  return isUInt<32>(clearUnusedBits(Val, Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits())) ||
12479  AMDGPU::isInlinableIntLiteral(Val);
12480  default:
12481  break;
12482  }
12483  } else if (Constraint.size() == 2) {
12484  if (Constraint == "DA") {
12485  int64_t HiBits = static_cast<int32_t>(Val >> 32);
12486  int64_t LoBits = static_cast<int32_t>(Val);
12487  return checkAsmConstraintValA(Op, HiBits, 32) &&
12488  checkAsmConstraintValA(Op, LoBits, 32);
12489  }
12490  if (Constraint == "DB") {
12491  return true;
12492  }
12493  }
12494  llvm_unreachable("Invalid asm constraint");
12495 }
12496 
12497 bool SITargetLowering::checkAsmConstraintValA(SDValue Op,
12498  uint64_t Val,
12499  unsigned MaxSize) const {
12500  unsigned Size = std::min<unsigned>(Op.getScalarValueSizeInBits(), MaxSize);
12501  bool HasInv2Pi = Subtarget->hasInv2PiInlineImm();
12502  if ((Size == 16 && AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral16(Val, HasInv2Pi)) ||
12503  (Size == 32 && AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral32(Val, HasInv2Pi)) ||
12504  (Size == 64 && AMDGPU::isInlinableLiteral64(Val, HasInv2Pi))) {
12505  return true;
12506  }
12507  return false;
12508 }
12509 
12510 static int getAlignedAGPRClassID(unsigned UnalignedClassID) {
12511  switch (UnalignedClassID) {
12512  case AMDGPU::VReg_64RegClassID:
12513  return AMDGPU::VReg_64_Align2RegClassID;
12514  case AMDGPU::VReg_96RegClassID:
12515  return AMDGPU::VReg_96_Align2RegClassID;
12516  case AMDGPU::VReg_128RegClassID:
12517  return AMDGPU::VReg_128_Align2RegClassID;
12518  case AMDGPU::VReg_160RegClassID:
12519  return AMDGPU::VReg_160_Align2RegClassID;
12520  case AMDGPU::VReg_192RegClassID:
12521  return AMDGPU::VReg_192_Align2RegClassID;
12522  case AMDGPU::VReg_224RegClassID:
12523  return AMDGPU::VReg_224_Align2RegClassID;
12524  case AMDGPU::VReg_256RegClassID:
12525  return AMDGPU::VReg_256_Align2RegClassID;
12526  case AMDGPU::VReg_288RegClassID:
12527  return AMDGPU::VReg_288_Align2RegClassID;
12528  case AMDGPU::VReg_320RegClassID:
12529  return AMDGPU::VReg_320_Align2RegClassID;
12530  case AMDGPU::VReg_352RegClassID:
12531  return AMDGPU::VReg_352_Align2RegClassID;
12532  case AMDGPU::VReg_384RegClassID:
12533  return AMDGPU::VReg_384_Align2RegClassID;
12534  case AMDGPU::VReg_512RegClassID:
12535  return AMDGPU::VReg_512_Align2RegClassID;
12536  case AMDGPU::VReg_1024RegClassID:
12537  return AMDGPU::VReg_1024_Align2RegClassID;
12538  case AMDGPU::AReg_64RegClassID:
12539  return AMDGPU::AReg_64_Align2RegClassID;
12540  case AMDGPU::AReg_96RegClassID:
12541  return AMDGPU::AReg_96_Align2RegClassID;
12542  case AMDGPU::AReg_128RegClassID:
12543  return AMDGPU::AReg_128_Align2RegClassID;
12544  case AMDGPU::AReg_160RegClassID:
12545  return AMDGPU::AReg_160_Align2RegClassID;
12546  case AMDGPU::AReg_192RegClassID:
12547  return AMDGPU::AReg_192_Align2RegClassID;
12548  case AMDGPU::AReg_256RegClassID:
12549  return AMDGPU::AReg_256_Align2RegClassID;
12550  case AMDGPU::AReg_512RegClassID:
12551  return AMDGPU::AReg_512_Align2RegClassID;
12552  case AMDGPU::AReg_1024RegClassID:
12553  return AMDGPU::AReg_1024_Align2RegClassID;
12554  default:
12555  return -1;
12556  }
12557 }
12558 
12559 // Figure out which registers should be reserved for stack access. Only after
12560 // the function is legalized do we know all of the non-spill stack objects or if
12561 // calls are present.
12562 void SITargetLowering::finalizeLowering(MachineFunction &MF) const {
12563  MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
12564  SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
12565  const GCNSubtarget &ST = MF.getSubtarget<GCNSubtarget>();
12566  const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
12567  const SIInstrInfo *TII = ST.getInstrInfo();
12568 
12569  if (Info->isEntryFunction()) {
12570  // Callable functions have fixed registers used for stack access.
12571  reservePrivateMemoryRegs(getTargetMachine(), MF, *TRI, *Info);
12572  }
12573 
12574  assert(!TRI->isSubRegister(Info->getScratchRSrcReg(),
12575  Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg()));
12576  if (Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg() != AMDGPU::SP_REG)
12577  MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::SP_REG, Info->getStackPtrOffsetReg());
12578 
12579  // We need to worry about replacing the default register with itself in case
12580  // of MIR testcases missing the MFI.
12581  if (Info->getScratchRSrcReg() != AMDGPU::PRIVATE_RSRC_REG)
12582  MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::PRIVATE_RSRC_REG, Info->getScratchRSrcReg());
12583 
12584  if (Info->getFrameOffsetReg() != AMDGPU::FP_REG)
12585  MRI.replaceRegWith(AMDGPU::FP_REG, Info->getFrameOffsetReg());
12586 
12587  Info->limitOccupancy(MF);
12588 
12589  if (ST.isWave32() && !MF.empty()) {
12590  for (auto &MBB : MF) {
12591  for (auto &MI : MBB) {
12592  TII->fixImplicitOperands(MI);
12593  }
12594  }
12595  }
12596 
12597  // FIXME: This is a hack to fixup AGPR classes to use the properly aligned
12598  // classes if required. Ideally the register class constraints would differ
12599  // per-subtarget, but there's no easy way to achieve that right now. This is
12600  // not a problem for VGPRs because the correctly aligned VGPR class is implied
12601  // from using them as the register class for legal types.
12602  if (ST.needsAlignedVGPRs()) {
12603  for (unsigned I = 0, E = MRI.getNumVirtRegs(); I != E; ++I) {
12604  const Register Reg = Register::index2VirtReg(I);
12605  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI.getRegClassOrNull(Reg);
12606  if (!RC)
12607  continue;
12608  int NewClassID = getAlignedAGPRClassID(RC->getID());
12609  if (NewClassID != -1)
12610  MRI.setRegClass(Reg, TRI->getRegClass(NewClassID));
12611  }
12612  }
12613 
12614  TargetLoweringBase::finalizeLowering(MF);
12615 }
12616 
12617 void SITargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(
12618  const int FI, KnownBits &Known, const MachineFunction &MF) const {
12619  TargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForFrameIndex(FI, Known, MF);
12620 
12621  // Set the high bits to zero based on the maximum allowed scratch size per
12622  // wave. We can't use vaddr in MUBUF instructions if we don't know the address
12623  // calculation won't overflow, so assume the sign bit is never set.
12624  Known.Zero.setHighBits(getSubtarget()->getKnownHighZeroBitsForFrameIndex());
12625 }
12626 
12627 static void knownBitsForWorkitemID(const GCNSubtarget &ST, GISelKnownBits &KB,
12628  KnownBits &Known, unsigned Dim) {
12629  unsigned MaxValue =
12630  ST.getMaxWorkitemID(KB.getMachineFunction().getFunction(), Dim);
12631  Known.Zero.setHighBits(llvm::countl_zero(MaxValue));
12632 }
12633 
12634 void SITargetLowering::computeKnownBitsForTargetInstr(
12635  GISelKnownBits &KB, Register R, KnownBits &Known, const APInt &DemandedElts,
12636  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI, unsigned Depth) const {
12637  const MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(R);
12638  switch (MI->getOpcode()) {
12639  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC: {
12640  switch (MI->getIntrinsicID()) {
12641  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_x:
12642  knownBitsForWorkitemID(*getSubtarget(), KB, Known, 0);
12643  break;
12644  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_y:
12645  knownBitsForWorkitemID(*getSubtarget(), KB, Known, 1);
12646  break;
12647  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_workitem_id_z:
12648  knownBitsForWorkitemID(*getSubtarget(), KB, Known, 2);
12649  break;
12650  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_mbcnt_lo:
12651  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_mbcnt_hi: {
12652  // These return at most the wavefront size - 1.
12653  unsigned Size = MRI.getType(R).getSizeInBits();
12654  Known.Zero.setHighBits(Size - getSubtarget()->getWavefrontSizeLog2());
12655  break;
12656  }
12657  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_groupstaticsize: {
12658  // We can report everything over the maximum size as 0. We can't report
12659  // based on the actual size because we don't know if it's accurate or not
12660  // at any given point.
12661  Known.Zero.setHighBits(
12662  llvm::countl_zero(getSubtarget()->getAddressableLocalMemorySize()));
12663  break;
12664  }
12665  }
12666  break;
12667  }
12668  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_BUFFER_LOAD_UBYTE:
12669  Known.Zero.setHighBits(24);
12670  break;
12671  case AMDGPU::G_AMDGPU_BUFFER_LOAD_USHORT:
12672  Known.Zero.setHighBits(16);
12673  break;
12674  }
12675 }
12676 
12677 Align SITargetLowering::computeKnownAlignForTargetInstr(
12678  GISelKnownBits &KB, Register R, const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI,
12679  unsigned Depth) const {
12680  const MachineInstr *MI = MRI.getVRegDef(R);
12681  switch (MI->getOpcode()) {
12682  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC:
12683  case AMDGPU::G_INTRINSIC_W_SIDE_EFFECTS: {
12684  // FIXME: Can this move to generic code? What about the case where the call
12685  // site specifies a lower alignment?
12686  Intrinsic::ID IID = MI->getIntrinsicID();
12687  LLVMContext &Ctx = KB.getMachineFunction().getFunction().getContext();
12688  AttributeList Attrs = Intrinsic::getAttributes(Ctx, IID);
12689  if (MaybeAlign RetAlign = Attrs.getRetAlignment())
12690  return *RetAlign;
12691  return Align(1);
12692  }
12693  default:
12694  return Align(1);
12695  }
12696 }
12697 
12698 Align SITargetLowering::getPrefLoopAlignment(MachineLoop *ML) const {
12699  const Align PrefAlign = TargetLowering::getPrefLoopAlignment(ML);
12700  const Align CacheLineAlign = Align(64);
12701 
12702  // Pre-GFX10 target did not benefit from loop alignment
12703  if (!ML || DisableLoopAlignment || !getSubtarget()->hasInstPrefetch() ||
12704  getSubtarget()->hasInstFwdPrefetchBug())
12705  return PrefAlign;
12706 
12707  // On GFX10 I$ is 4 x 64 bytes cache lines.
12708  // By default prefetcher keeps one cache line behind and reads two ahead.
12709  // We can modify it with S_INST_PREFETCH for larger loops to have two lines
12710  // behind and one ahead.
12711  // Therefor we can benefit from aligning loop headers if loop fits 192 bytes.
12712  // If loop fits 64 bytes it always spans no more than two cache lines and
12713  // does not need an alignment.
12714  // Else if loop is less or equal 128 bytes we do not need to modify prefetch,
12715  // Else if loop is less or equal 192 bytes we need two lines behind.
12716 
12717  const SIInstrInfo *TII = getSubtarget()->getInstrInfo();
12718  const MachineBasicBlock *Header = ML->getHeader();
12719  if (Header->getAlignment() != PrefAlign)
12720  return Header->getAlignment(); // Already processed.
12721 
12722  unsigned LoopSize = 0;
12723  for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : ML->blocks()) {
12724  // If inner loop block is aligned assume in average half of the alignment
12725  // size to be added as nops.
12726  if (MBB != Header)
12727  LoopSize += MBB->getAlignment().value() / 2;
12728 
12729  for (const MachineInstr &MI : *MBB) {
12730  LoopSize += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(MI);
12731  if (LoopSize > 192)
12732  return PrefAlign;
12733  }
12734  }
12735 
12736  if (LoopSize <= 64)
12737  return PrefAlign;
12738 
12739  if (LoopSize <= 128)
12740  return CacheLineAlign;
12741 
12742  // If any of parent loops is surrounded by prefetch instructions do not
12743  // insert new for inner loop, which would reset parent's settings.
12744  for (MachineLoop *P = ML->getParentLoop(); P; P = P->getParentLoop()) {
12745  if (MachineBasicBlock *Exit = P->getExitBlock()) {
12746  auto I = Exit->getFirstNonDebugInstr();
12747  if (I != Exit->end() && I->getOpcode() == AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH)
12748  return CacheLineAlign;
12749  }
12750  }
12751 
12752  MachineBasicBlock *Pre = ML->getLoopPreheader();
12753  MachineBasicBlock *Exit = ML->getExitBlock();
12754 
12755  if (Pre && Exit) {
12756  auto PreTerm = Pre->getFirstTerminator();
12757  if (PreTerm == Pre->begin() ||
12758  std::prev(PreTerm)->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH)
12759  BuildMI(*Pre, PreTerm, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH))
12760  .addImm(1); // prefetch 2 lines behind PC
12761 
12762  auto ExitHead = Exit->getFirstNonDebugInstr();
12763  if (ExitHead == Exit->end() ||
12764  ExitHead->getOpcode() != AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH)
12765  BuildMI(*Exit, ExitHead, DebugLoc(), TII->get(AMDGPU::S_INST_PREFETCH))
12766  .addImm(2); // prefetch 1 line behind PC
12767  }
12768 
12769  return CacheLineAlign;
12770 }
12771 
12772 LLVM_ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED
12773 static bool isCopyFromRegOfInlineAsm(const SDNode *N) {
12774  assert(N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg);
12775  do {
12776  // Follow the chain until we find an INLINEASM node.
12777  N = N->getOperand(0).getNode();
12778  if (N->getOpcode() == ISD::INLINEASM ||
12779  N->getOpcode() == ISD::INLINEASM_BR)
12780  return true;
12781  } while (N->getOpcode() == ISD::CopyFromReg);
12782  return false;
12783 }
12784 
12785 bool SITargetLowering::isSDNodeSourceOfDivergence(
12786  const SDNode *N, FunctionLoweringInfo *FLI,
12787  LegacyDivergenceAnalysis *KDA) const {
12788  switch (N->getOpcode()) {
12789  case ISD::CopyFromReg: {
12790  const RegisterSDNode *R = cast<RegisterSDNode>(N->getOperand(1));
12791  const MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = FLI->MF->getRegInfo();
12792  const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
12793  Register Reg = R->getReg();
12794 
12795  // FIXME: Why does this need to consider isLiveIn?
12796  if (Reg.isPhysical() || MRI.isLiveIn(Reg))
12797  return !TRI->isSGPRReg(MRI, Reg);
12798 
12799  if (const Value *V = FLI->getValueFromVirtualReg(R->getReg()))
12800  return KDA->isDivergent(V);
12801 
12802  assert(Reg == FLI->DemoteRegister || isCopyFromRegOfInlineAsm(N));
12803  return !TRI->isSGPRReg(MRI, Reg);
12804  }
12805  case ISD::LOAD: {
12806  const LoadSDNode *L = cast<LoadSDNode>(N);
12807  unsigned AS = L->getAddressSpace();
12808  // A flat load may access private memory.
12809  return AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS || AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS;
12810  }
12811  case ISD::CALLSEQ_END:
12812  return true;
12813  case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN:
12814  return AMDGPU::isIntrinsicSourceOfDivergence(
12815  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(0))->getZExtValue());
12816  case ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN:
12817  return AMDGPU::isIntrinsicSourceOfDivergence(
12818  cast<ConstantSDNode>(N->getOperand(1))->getZExtValue());
12819  case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_CMP_SWAP:
12820  case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMIN:
12821  case AMDGPUISD::ATOMIC_LOAD_FMAX:
12822  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SWAP:
12823  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_ADD:
12824  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SUB:
12825  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMIN:
12826  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMIN:
12827  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_SMAX:
12828  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_UMAX:
12829  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_AND:
12830  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_OR:
12831  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_XOR:
12832  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_INC:
12833  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_DEC:
12834  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CMPSWAP:
12835  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_CSUB:
12836  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FADD:
12837  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMIN:
12838  case AMDGPUISD::BUFFER_ATOMIC_FMAX:
12839  // Target-specific read-modify-write atomics are sources of divergence.
12840  return true;
12841  default:
12842  if (auto *A = dyn_cast<AtomicSDNode>(N)) {
12843  // Generic read-modify-write atomics are sources of divergence.
12844  return A->readMem() && A->writeMem();
12845  }
12846  return false;
12847  }
12848 }

12851  EVT VT) const {
12852  switch (VT.getScalarType().getSimpleVT().SimpleTy) {
12853  case MVT::f32:
12854  return hasFP32Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction());
12855  case MVT::f64:
12856  case MVT::f16:
12857  return hasFP64FP16Denormals(DAG.getMachineFunction());
12858  default:
12859  return false;
12860  }
12861 }

12864  MachineFunction &MF) const {
12865  switch (Ty.getScalarSizeInBits()) {
12866  case 32:
12867  return hasFP32Denormals(MF);
12868  case 64:
12869  case 16:
12870  return hasFP64FP16Denormals(MF);
12871  default:
12872  return false;
12873  }

12876 bool SITargetLowering::isKnownNeverNaNForTargetNode(SDValue Op,
12877  const SelectionDAG &DAG,
12878  bool SNaN,
12879  unsigned Depth) const {
12880  if (Op.getOpcode() == AMDGPUISD::CLAMP) {
12881  const MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
12882  const SIMachineFunctionInfo *Info = MF.getInfo<SIMachineFunctionInfo>();
12883 
12884  if (Info->getMode().DX10Clamp)
12885  return true; // Clamped to 0.
12886  return DAG.isKnownNeverNaN(Op.getOperand(0), SNaN, Depth + 1);
12887  }
12888 
12889  return AMDGPUTargetLowering::isKnownNeverNaNForTargetNode(Op, DAG,
12890  SNaN, Depth);
12891 }
12892 
12893 // Global FP atomic instructions have a hardcoded FP mode and do not support
12894 // FP32 denormals, and only support v2f16 denormals.
12895 static bool fpModeMatchesGlobalFPAtomicMode(const AtomicRMWInst *RMW) {
12896  const fltSemantics &Flt = RMW->getType()->getScalarType()->getFltSemantics();
12897  auto DenormMode = RMW->getParent()->getParent()->getDenormalMode(Flt);
12898  if (&Flt == &APFloat::IEEEsingle())
12899  return DenormMode == DenormalMode::getPreserveSign();
12900  return DenormMode == DenormalMode::getIEEE();
12901 }
12902 
12903 // The amdgpu-unsafe-fp-atomics attribute enables generation of unsafe
12904 // floating point atomic instructions. May generate more efficient code,
12905 // but may not respect rounding and denormal modes, and may give incorrect
12906 // results for certain memory destinations.
12907 bool unsafeFPAtomicsDisabled(Function *F) {
12908  return F->getFnAttribute("amdgpu-unsafe-fp-atomics").getValueAsString() !=
12909  "true";
12910 }
12911 
12912 TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind
12913 SITargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(AtomicRMWInst *RMW) const {
12914  unsigned AS = RMW->getPointerAddressSpace();
12915  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS)
12916  return AtomicExpansionKind::NotAtomic;
12917 
12918  auto SSID = RMW->getSyncScopeID();
12919 
12920  auto ReportUnsafeHWInst = [&](TargetLowering::AtomicExpansionKind Kind) {
12921  OptimizationRemarkEmitter ORE(RMW->getFunction());
12922  LLVMContext &Ctx = RMW->getFunction()->getContext();
12923  SmallVector<StringRef> SSNs;
12924  Ctx.getSyncScopeNames(SSNs);
12925  auto MemScope = SSNs[RMW->getSyncScopeID()].empty()
12926  ? "system"
12927  : SSNs[RMW->getSyncScopeID()];
12928  ORE.emit([&]() {
12929  return OptimizationRemark(DEBUG_TYPE, "Passed", RMW)
12930  << "Hardware instruction generated for atomic "
12931  << RMW->getOperationName(RMW->getOperation())
12932  << " operation at memory scope " << MemScope
12933  << " due to an unsafe request.";
12934  });
12935  return Kind;
12936  };
12937 
12938  bool HasSystemScope =
12939  SSID == SyncScope::System ||
12940  SSID == RMW->getContext().getOrInsertSyncScopeID("one-as");
12941 
12942  switch (RMW->getOperation()) {
12943  case AtomicRMWInst::FAdd: {
12944  Type *Ty = RMW->getType();
12945 
12946  if (Ty->isHalfTy())
12947  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
12948 
12949  if (!Ty->isFloatTy() && (!Subtarget->hasGFX90AInsts() || !Ty->isDoubleTy()))
12950  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
12951 
12952  if (AMDGPU::isFlatGlobalAddrSpace(AS) &&
12953  Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddNoRtnInsts()) {
12954  if (Subtarget->hasGFX940Insts())
12955  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
12956 
12957  if (unsafeFPAtomicsDisabled(RMW->getFunction()))
12958  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
12959 
12960  // Always expand system scope fp atomics.
12961  if (HasSystemScope)
12962  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
12963 
12964  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS && Ty->isFloatTy()) {
12965  // global atomic fadd f32 no-rtn: gfx908, gfx90a, gfx940, gfx11+.
12966  if (RMW->use_empty() && Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddNoRtnInsts())
12967  return ReportUnsafeHWInst(AtomicExpansionKind::None);
12968  // global atomic fadd f32 rtn: gfx90a, gfx940, gfx11+.
12969  if (!RMW->use_empty() && Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddRtnInsts())
12970  return ReportUnsafeHWInst(AtomicExpansionKind::None);
12971  }
12972 
12973  // flat atomic fadd f32: gfx940, gfx11+.
12974  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS && Ty->isFloatTy() &&
12975  Subtarget->hasFlatAtomicFaddF32Inst())
12976  return ReportUnsafeHWInst(AtomicExpansionKind::None);
12977 
12978  // global and flat atomic fadd f64: gfx90a, gfx940.
12979  if (Ty->isDoubleTy() && Subtarget->hasGFX90AInsts())
12980  return ReportUnsafeHWInst(AtomicExpansionKind::None);
12981 
12982  // If it is in flat address space, and the type is float, we will try to
12983  // expand it, if the target supports global and lds atomic fadd. The
12984  // reason we need that is, in the expansion, we emit the check of address
12985  // space. If it is in global address space, we emit the global atomic
12986  // fadd; if it is in shared address space, we emit the LDS atomic fadd.
12987  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS && Ty->isFloatTy() &&
12988  Subtarget->hasLDSFPAtomicAdd()) {
12989  if (RMW->use_empty() && Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddNoRtnInsts())
12990  return AtomicExpansionKind::Expand;
12991  if (!RMW->use_empty() && Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddRtnInsts())
12992  return AtomicExpansionKind::Expand;
12993  }
12994 
12995  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
12996  }
12997 
12998  // DS FP atomics do respect the denormal mode, but the rounding mode is
12999  // fixed to round-to-nearest-even.
13000  // The only exception is DS_ADD_F64 which never flushes regardless of mode.
13001  if (AS == AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS && Subtarget->hasLDSFPAtomicAdd()) {
13002  if (!Ty->isDoubleTy())
13003  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13004 
13005  if (fpModeMatchesGlobalFPAtomicMode(RMW))
13006  return AtomicExpansionKind::None;
13007 
13008  return RMW->getFunction()
13009  ->getFnAttribute("amdgpu-unsafe-fp-atomics")
13010  .getValueAsString() == "true"
13011  ? ReportUnsafeHWInst(AtomicExpansionKind::None)
13012  : AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
13013  }
13014 
13015  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
13016  }
13017  case AtomicRMWInst::FMin:
13018  case AtomicRMWInst::FMax:
13019  case AtomicRMWInst::Min:
13020  case AtomicRMWInst::Max:
13021  case AtomicRMWInst::UMin:
13022  case AtomicRMWInst::UMax: {
13023  if (AMDGPU::isFlatGlobalAddrSpace(AS)) {
13024  if (RMW->getType()->isFloatTy() &&
13025  unsafeFPAtomicsDisabled(RMW->getFunction()))
13026  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
13027 
13028  // Always expand system scope min/max atomics.
13029  if (HasSystemScope)
13030  return AtomicExpansionKind::CmpXChg;
13031  }
13032  break;
13033  }
13034  default:
13035  break;
13036  }
13037 
13038  return AMDGPUTargetLowering::shouldExpandAtomicRMWInIR(RMW);
13039 }
13040

13062 const TargetRegisterClass *
13063 SITargetLowering::getRegClassFor(MVT VT, bool isDivergent) const {
13064  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TargetLoweringBase::getRegClassFor(VT, false);
13065  const SIRegisterInfo *TRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
13066  if (RC == &AMDGPU::VReg_1RegClass && !isDivergent)
13067  return Subtarget->getWavefrontSize() == 64 ? &AMDGPU::SReg_64RegClass
13068  : &AMDGPU::SReg_32RegClass;
13069  if (!TRI->isSGPRClass(RC) && !isDivergent)
13070  return TRI->getEquivalentSGPRClass(RC);
13071  else if (TRI->isSGPRClass(RC) && isDivergent)
13072  return TRI->getEquivalentVGPRClass(RC);
13073 
13074  return RC;
13075 }
13076 
13077 // FIXME: This is a workaround for DivergenceAnalysis not understanding always
13078 // uniform values (as produced by the mask results of control flow intrinsics)
13079 // used outside of divergent blocks. The phi users need to also be treated as
13080 // always uniform.
13081 static bool hasCFUser(const Value *V, SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 16> &Visited,
13082  unsigned WaveSize) {
13083  // FIXME: We assume we never cast the mask results of a control flow
13084  // intrinsic.
13085  // Early exit if the type won't be consistent as a compile time hack.
13086  IntegerType *IT = dyn_cast<IntegerType>(V->getType());
13087  if (!IT || IT->getBitWidth() != WaveSize)
13088  return false;
13089 
13090  if (!isa<Instruction>(V))
13091  return false;
13092  if (!Visited.insert(V).second)
13093  return false;
13094  bool Result = false;
13095  for (const auto *U : V->users()) {
13096  if (const IntrinsicInst *Intrinsic = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(U)) {
13097  if (V == U->getOperand(1)) {
13098  switch (Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID()) {
13099  default:
13100  Result = false;
13101  break;
13102  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_if_break:
13103  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_if:
13104  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_else:
13105  Result = true;
13106  break;
13107  }
13108  }
13109  if (V == U->getOperand(0)) {
13110  switch (Intrinsic->getIntrinsicID()) {
13111  default:
13112  Result = false;
13113  break;
13114  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_end_cf:
13115  case Intrinsic::amdgcn_loop:
13116  Result = true;
13117  break;
13118  }
13119  }
13120  } else {
13121  Result = hasCFUser(U, Visited, WaveSize);
13122  }
13123  if (Result)
13124  break;
13125  }
13126  return Result;
13127 }
13128 
13129 bool SITargetLowering::requiresUniformRegister(MachineFunction &MF,
13130  const Value *V) const {
13131  if (const CallInst *CI = dyn_cast<CallInst>(V)) {
13132  if (CI->isInlineAsm()) {
13133  // FIXME: This cannot give a correct answer. This should only trigger in
13134  // the case where inline asm returns mixed SGPR and VGPR results, used
13135  // outside the defining block. We don't have a specific result to
13136  // consider, so this assumes if any value is SGPR, the overall register
13137  // also needs to be SGPR.
13138  const SIRegisterInfo *SIRI = Subtarget->getRegisterInfo();
13139  TargetLowering::AsmOperandInfoVector TargetConstraints = ParseConstraints(
13140  MF.getDataLayout(), Subtarget->getRegisterInfo(), *CI);
13141  for (auto &TC : TargetConstraints) {
13142  if (TC.Type == InlineAsm::isOutput) {
13143  ComputeConstraintToUse(TC, SDValue());
13144  const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(
13145  SIRI, TC.ConstraintCode, TC.ConstraintVT).second;
13146  if (RC && SIRI->isSGPRClass(RC))
13147  return true;
13148  }
13149  }
13150  }
13151  }
13152  SmallPtrSet<const Value *, 16> Visited;
13153  return hasCFUser(V, Visited, Subtarget->getWavefrontSize());
13154 }
13155 
13156 bool SITargetLowering::hasMemSDNodeUser(SDNode *N) const {
13157  SDNode::use_iterator I = N->use_begin(), E = N->use_end();
13158  for (; I != E; ++I) {
13159  if (MemSDNode *M = dyn_cast<MemSDNode>(*I)) {
13160  if (getBasePtrIndex(M) == I.getOperandNo())
13161  return true;
13162  }
13163  }
13164  return false;
13165 }
13166 
13167 bool SITargetLowering::isReassocProfitable(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue N0,
13168  SDValue N1) const {
13169  if (!N0.hasOneUse())
13170  return false;
13171  // Take care of the opportunity to keep N0 uniform
13172  if (N0->isDivergent() || !N1->isDivergent())
13173  return true;
13174  // Check if we have a good chance to form the memory access pattern with the
13175  // base and offset
13176  return (DAG.isBaseWithConstantOffset(N0) &&
13177  hasMemSDNodeUser(*N0->use_begin()));
13178 }

13180 MachineMemOperand::Flags
13181 SITargetLowering::getTargetMMOFlags(const Instruction &I) const {
13182  // Propagate metadata set by AMDGPUAnnotateUniformValues to the MMO of a load.
13183  if (I.getMetadata("amdgpu.noclobber"))
13184  return MONoClobber;
13185  return MachineMemOperand::MONone;
13186 }
13187 
13188 bool SITargetLowering::checkForPhysRegDependency(
13189  SDNode *Def, SDNode *User, unsigned Op, const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
13190  const TargetInstrInfo *TII, unsigned &PhysReg, int &Cost) const {
13191  if (User->getOpcode() != ISD::CopyToReg)
13192  return false;
13193  if (!Def->isMachineOpcode())
13194  return false;
13195  MachineSDNode *MDef = dyn_cast<MachineSDNode>(Def);
13196  if (!MDef)
13197  return false;
13198 
13199  unsigned ResNo = User->getOperand(Op).getResNo();
13200  if (User->getOperand(Op)->getValueType(ResNo) != MVT::i1)
13201  return false;
13202  const MCInstrDesc &II = TII->get(MDef->getMachineOpcode());
13203  if (II.isCompare() && II.hasImplicitDefOfPhysReg(AMDGPU::SCC)) {
13204  PhysReg = AMDGPU::SCC;
13205  const TargetRegisterClass *RC =
13206  TRI->getMinimalPhysRegClass(PhysReg, Def->getSimpleValueType(ResNo));
13207  Cost = RC->getCopyCost();
13208  return true;
13209  }
13210  return false;
13211 }
13212 
13213 void SITargetLowering::emitExpandAtomicRMW(AtomicRMWInst *AI) const {
13214  assert(Subtarget->hasAtomicFaddInsts() &&
13215  "target should have atomic fadd instructions");
13216  assert(AI->getType()->isFloatTy() &&
13217  AI->getPointerAddressSpace() == AMDGPUAS::FLAT_ADDRESS &&
13218  "generic atomicrmw expansion only supports FP32 operand in flat "
13219  "address space");
13220  assert(AI->getOperation() == AtomicRMWInst::FAdd &&
13221  "only fadd is supported for now");
13222 
13223  // Given: atomicrmw fadd float* %addr, float %val ordering
13224  //
13225  // With this expansion we produce the following code:
13226  // [...]
13227  // %int8ptr = bitcast float* %addr to i8*
13228  // br label %atomicrmw.check.shared
13229  //
13230  // atomicrmw.check.shared:
13231  // %is.shared = call i1 @llvm.amdgcn.is.shared(i8* %int8ptr)
13232  // br i1 %is.shared, label %atomicrmw.shared, label %atomicrmw.check.private
13233  //
13234  // atomicrmw.shared:
13235  // %cast.shared = addrspacecast float* %addr to float addrspace(3)*
13236  // %loaded.shared = atomicrmw fadd float addrspace(3)* %cast.shared,
13237  // float %val ordering
13238  // br label %atomicrmw.phi
13239  //
13240  // atomicrmw.check.private:
13241  // %is.private = call i1 @llvm.amdgcn.is.private(i8* %int8ptr)
13242  // br i1 %is.private, label %atomicrmw.private, label %atomicrmw.global
13243  //
13244  // atomicrmw.private:
13245  // %cast.private = addrspacecast float* %addr to float addrspace(5)*
13246  // %loaded.private = load float, float addrspace(5)* %cast.private
13247  // %val.new = fadd float %loaded.private, %val
13248  // store float %val.new, float addrspace(5)* %cast.private
13249  // br label %atomicrmw.phi
13250  //
13251  // atomicrmw.global:
13252  // %cast.global = addrspacecast float* %addr to float addrspace(1)*
13253  // %loaded.global = atomicrmw fadd float addrspace(1)* %cast.global,
13254  // float %val ordering
13255  // br label %atomicrmw.phi
13256  //
13257  // atomicrmw.phi:
13258  // %loaded.phi = phi float [ %loaded.shared, %atomicrmw.shared ],
13259  // [ %loaded.private, %atomicrmw.private ],
13260  // [ %loaded.global, %atomicrmw.global ]
13261  // br label %atomicrmw.end
13262  //
13263  // atomicrmw.end:
13264  // [...]
13265 
13266  IRBuilder<> Builder(AI);
13267  LLVMContext &Ctx = Builder.getContext();
13268 
13269  BasicBlock *BB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
13270  Function *F = BB->getParent();
13271  BasicBlock *ExitBB =
13272  BB->splitBasicBlock(Builder.GetInsertPoint(), "atomicrmw.end");
13273  BasicBlock *CheckSharedBB =
13274  BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.check.shared", F, ExitBB);
13275  BasicBlock *SharedBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.shared", F, ExitBB);
13276  BasicBlock *CheckPrivateBB =
13277  BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.check.private", F, ExitBB);
13278  BasicBlock *PrivateBB =
13279  BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.private", F, ExitBB);
13280  BasicBlock *GlobalBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.global", F, ExitBB);
13281  BasicBlock *PhiBB = BasicBlock::Create(Ctx, "atomicrmw.phi", F, ExitBB);
13282 
13283  Value *Val = AI->getValOperand();
13284  Type *ValTy = Val->getType();
13285  Value *Addr = AI->getPointerOperand();
13286  PointerType *PtrTy = cast<PointerType>(Addr->getType());
13287 
13288  auto CreateNewAtomicRMW = [AI](IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Addr,
13289  Value *Val) -> Value * {
13290  AtomicRMWInst *OldVal =
13291  Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(AI->getOperation(), Addr, Val, AI->getAlign(),
13292  AI->getOrdering(), AI->getSyncScopeID());
13293  SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, MDNode *>> MDs;
13294  AI->getAllMetadata(MDs);
13295  for (auto &P : MDs)
13296  OldVal->setMetadata(P.first, P.second);
13297  return OldVal;
13298  };
13299 
13300  std::prev(BB->end())->eraseFromParent();
13301  Builder.SetInsertPoint(BB);
13302  Value *Int8Ptr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, Builder.getInt8PtrTy());
13303  Builder.CreateBr(CheckSharedBB);
13304 
13305  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CheckSharedBB);
13306  CallInst *IsShared = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_shared, {},
13307  {Int8Ptr}, nullptr, "is.shared");
13308  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsShared, SharedBB, CheckPrivateBB);
13309 
13310  Builder.SetInsertPoint(SharedBB);
13311  Value *CastToLocal = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
13312  Addr,
13313  PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, AMDGPUAS::LOCAL_ADDRESS));
13314  Value *LoadedShared = CreateNewAtomicRMW(Builder, CastToLocal, Val);
13315  Builder.CreateBr(PhiBB);
13316 
13317  Builder.SetInsertPoint(CheckPrivateBB);
13318  CallInst *IsPrivate = Builder.CreateIntrinsic(
13319  Intrinsic::amdgcn_is_private, {}, {Int8Ptr}, nullptr, "is.private");
13320  Builder.CreateCondBr(IsPrivate, PrivateBB, GlobalBB);
13321 
13322  Builder.SetInsertPoint(PrivateBB);
13323  Value *CastToPrivate = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
13324  Addr,
13325  PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, AMDGPUAS::PRIVATE_ADDRESS));
13326  Value *LoadedPrivate =
13327  Builder.CreateLoad(ValTy, CastToPrivate, "loaded.private");
13328  Value *NewVal = Builder.CreateFAdd(LoadedPrivate, Val, "val.new");
13329  Builder.CreateStore(NewVal, CastToPrivate);
13330  Builder.CreateBr(PhiBB);
13331 
13332  Builder.SetInsertPoint(GlobalBB);
13333  Value *CastToGlobal = Builder.CreateAddrSpaceCast(
13334  Addr,
13335  PointerType::getWithSamePointeeType(PtrTy, AMDGPUAS::GLOBAL_ADDRESS));
13336  Value *LoadedGlobal = CreateNewAtomicRMW(Builder, CastToGlobal, Val);
13337  Builder.CreateBr(PhiBB);
13338 
13339  Builder.SetInsertPoint(PhiBB);
13340  PHINode *Loaded = Builder.CreatePHI(ValTy, 3, "loaded.phi");
13341  Loaded->addIncoming(LoadedShared, SharedBB);
13342  Loaded->addIncoming(LoadedPrivate, PrivateBB);
13343  Loaded->addIncoming(LoadedGlobal, GlobalBB);
13344  Builder.CreateBr(ExitBB);
13345 
13346  AI->replaceAllUsesWith(Loaded);
13347  AI->eraseFromParent();
13348 }
